b"Safety issues regarding shopping for prescription medications online pharmacy revolve around issues pertaining to your personal well being, the legality of transactions, and safety of your personal information. On-line pharmacies provide convenience and different advantages akin to privateness and in some cases cheaper costs compared to the traditional brick and mortar pharmacy, however with out due diligence the buying of prescription medication online may be fraught with a number of deleterious pitfalls. <br/><br/>To make sure the protection of prescription medications the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) requires that drugs go through security clinical trials, and that the benefits outweigh the dangers associated with a drug before it is accredited for advertising and sale in the United States. Sadly pharmacists outside the United States that dispense medication manufactured outside of the United States should not certain by federal regulations, posing a health hazard for many who choose to purchase from them. Because some pharmacies, even within the United States, import and distribute non-FDA accepted drugs manufactured outside of the nation, it is important to make it possible for the online pharmacy you choose only dispenses FDA authorized prescription medications. The principle concerns about purchasing prescription remedy from rogue online pharmacies that dispense medication not approved by the FDA permitted are, the drugs you obtain may be counterfeit, contaminated, sub-potent, super potent or the fallacious drug, all of which could jeopardize your health. Within the worst-case scenario, it's possible you'll not obtain any medicine at all regardless of paying for it. Therefore, it is very important ensure that the online pharmacy is licensed and based mostly within the United States and if not that it is accredited and dispenses medication authorised by its government. <br/><br/>Since rogue pharmacies are likely to want to be invisible and unreachable besides in our on-line world, it is very important obtain up-to-date contact data within the type of a bodily address and telephone number. With that information you can try and obtain a Better Enterprise Bureau report.  If a Higher Business Bureau report shouldn't be available you'll be able to then do an advanced Dun & Bradavenue search to make sure that the enterprise does the truth is exist. Keep away from doing  Farmacia italiana business with operations that solely offer you an e-mail address as a type of contact. In addition to possibly precluding you from obtaining credentials and details about business practices, the provision of just an e-mail address could be an indicator of the quality of customer service you possibly can count on or not expect. Additionally acquire the license number and any accreditation credentials from the pharmacy then confirm the data via the state pharmacy board of the state by which the pharmacy is based, an all important step because a number of the alleged Internet pharmacies are usually not really reputable licensed operations. In addition to verifying license standing and the fact that the pharmacy is located in the United States and meets quality standards, state boards of pharmacy or the Nationwide Affiliation of Boards of Pharmacy (NABP) also can let you already know if an internet pharmacy is accredited by Verified Internet Pharmacy Follow Sites (VIPPS) or other recognized accreditation programs. b'<br/>  Sommaire  1 Description 2 Exemples 3 Performances 4 Planification 5 Code 6 Wikipedia   Description Le LinkBot parcoure les articles de Wikipast et recherche pour chacun d\'entre eux un article correspondant sur Wikipedia en fran\xc3\xa7ais. Pour chaque correspondance trouv\xc3\xa9e, il ajoute \xc3\xa0 la fin de l\'article Wikipast une section Wikipedia contenant le lien vers la page Wikipedia, uniquement si celle-ci n\'est pas encore pr\xc3\xa9sente dans la page. Les articles Wikipast parcourus sont ceux cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9s par les utilisateurs agr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9s. La recherche sur Wikipedia d\'une correspondance est faite par un algorithme de l\'API de Wikipedia. Celui-ci retourne g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ralement un unique article. Si plusieurs articles sont retourn\xc3\xa9s, la section Wikipedia n\'est pas ajout\xc3\xa9e. Exemples Section Wikipedia ajout\xc3\xa9e sur la page Munich Section Wikipedia ajout\xc3\xa9e sur la page Wolfgang Pauli Performances La section "Wikipedia" a pu \xc3\xaatre ajout\xc3\xa9e sur tous les articles de datafication biographique de la page Biographies.  Planification Le bot doit \xc3\xaatre activ\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 chaque nouvel article d\'un utilisateur agr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9, ou \xc3\xa0 chaque modification du nom d\'un article d\'un utilisateur agr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9. Si cela n\'est pas possible, il peut \xc3\xaatre activ\xc3\xa9 chaque semaine, ce qui semble \xc3\xaatre une fr\xc3\xa9quence adapt\xc3\xa9e au Bot.  Code  # -*- coding: utf-8 -*-     import lxml import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import wikipedia import re import sys  # login, settings and format data user=\'TotallyNotBot\' passw=XXX baseurl=\'http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/\' summary=\'LinkBot update\' wikipediaHeader = \'==Wikipedia==\' # Used for regex search in removeWikipediaContent wikipedia.set_lang("fr")  # Constants  pageNotFound = -1 wikipediaLinkNotFound = -2  # - - - - - - -    # Returns all the pages modified and added by the users of the course. def getPageList():     protected_logins=["Frederickaplan","Maud","Vbuntinx","Testbot","SparqlBot","IB","SourceBot","PageUpdaterBot","Orthobot","BioPathBot","ChronoBOT","Amonbaro","AntoineL","AntoniasBanderos","Arnau","Arnaudpannatier","Aureliver","Brunowicht","Burgerpop","Cedricviaccoz","Christophe","Claudioloureiro","Ghislain","Gregoire3245","Hirtg","Houssm","Icebaker","JenniCin","JiggyQ","JulienB","Kl","Kperrard","Leandro Kieliger","Marcus","Martin","MatteoGiorla","Mireille","Mj2905","Musluoglucem","Nacho","Nameless","Nawel","O\'showa","PA","Qantik","QuentinB","Raphael.barman","Roblan11","Romain Fournier","Sbaaa","Snus","Sonia","Tboyer","Thierry","Titi","Vlaedr","Wanda"]          liste_pages=[]     for user in protected_logins:         result=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&list=usercontribs&ucuser=\'+user+\'&format=xml\')         soup=BeautifulSoup(result.content,\'lxml\')         for primitive in soup.usercontribs.findAll(\'item\'):             liste_pages.append(primitive[\'title\'])          liste_pages=list(set(liste_pages))      return liste_pages   # get wikipedia link from page # return format should be a string (e.g. page=\'Cern\' returns \'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CERN\') # if it cannot find the link, it should return the empty string \'\'. def getWikipediaLink(page):     try:         page_wiki = wikipedia.page(page)         return page_wiki.url      except:         return \'\'  # Get content returns the current content of a wiki page. Returns # pageNotFound if either the page could not be found, or if the content # is empty. def getContent(page):     try:         result=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+page+\'&export&exportnowrap\')          soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text,\'lxml\')         data=\'\'          for primitive in soup.findAll("text"):             # Check if the article is empty, if it is empty, return the empty string             try:                 data+=primitive.string             except:                 return data                  return data      except:         return pageNotFound   # Adds a new content (newContent) to the page def addContent(page, newContent):     # Login request     payload={\'action\':\'query\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'meta\':\'tokens\',\'type\':\'login\'}     r1=requests.post(baseurl + \'api.php\', data=payload)      #login confirm     login_token=r1.json()[\'query\'][\'tokens\'][\'logintoken\']     payload={\'action\':\'login\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'lgname\':user,\'lgpassword\':passw,\'lgtoken\':login_token}     r2=requests.post(baseurl + \'api.php\', data=payload, cookies=r1.cookies)      #get edit token2     params3=\'?format=json&action=query&meta=tokens&continue=\'     r3=requests.get(baseurl + \'api.php\' + params3, cookies=r2.cookies)     edit_token=r3.json()[\'query\'][\'tokens\'][\'csrftoken\']      edit_cookie=r2.cookies.copy()     edit_cookie.update(r3.cookies)      payload={\'action\':\'edit\',\'assert\':\'user\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'text\':newContent,\'summary\':summary,\'title\':page,\'token\':edit_token}     r4=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php\',data=payload,cookies=edit_cookie)   # Add wikipedia content adds the old content with the wikipediaContent appeneded at the end of the page. def addWikipediaContent(page, oldContent, wikipediaLink):      wikipediaContent = wikipediaHeader + \'\\n\' + wikipediaLink     newContent = oldContent + \'\\n\' + wikipediaContent     addContent(page, newContent)   # Removes the wikipedia content from a page by using regex patterns. def removeWikipediaContent(page):          oldContent = getContent(page)      if (oldContent == pageNotFound):         return      if re.search(wikipediaHeader, oldContent) is not None:          stringArray = oldContent.split(\'\\n\')          newContent = \'\'         headerFound = False         for line in stringArray:             if not headerFound:                  if line == wikipediaHeader:                     headerFound = True                 else:                     newContent += (line + \'\\n\')             else:                 headerFound = False          addContent(page, newContent)   # Main program which for every page in getPages(), (i.e. the biographies) if the page has no wikipedia content, # then it will add the corresponding wikpedia link. def main():           print(\'LinkBot starting...\')      # load pages ]o add Wikipedia links     page_list = getPageList()     # lists for data (which links could not be found, which have been added already?)     page_list_without_wikipedia_link = []     page_list_already_with_link = []     page_list_new_wiki = []      for page in page_list:          ## This also verifies if the page can be accessed. If it cannot, oldContent will be         ## equal to pageNotFound and hence nothing is added         oldContent = getContent(page)          wikipediaLink = getWikipediaLink(page)          # If there is a non verified wikipedia link, delete it         if wikipediaHeader in oldContent and wikipediaLink == \'\':             removeWikipediaContent(page)          # Check if a Wikipedia link has already been added.         if oldContent != pageNotFound and wikipediaHeader not in oldContent:                          # If wikipediaLink is the null string then no appropriate link has been found.             if (wikipediaLink != \'\'):                 addWikipediaContent(page, oldContent, wikipediaLink)                 page_list_new_wiki.append(page)              else:                 page_list_without_wikipedia_link.append(page)          else:             page_list_already_with_link.append(page)       # output data     linksAdded = len(page_list) - len(page_list_without_wikipedia_link) - len(page_list_already_with_link)     print(str(linksAdded) + \' links added to \' + str(len(page_list)) + \' pages.\\n\')  if __name__ == "__main__": main()   Wikipedia https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lintot     \t0'

b'Sommaire  1 Description 2 M\xc3\xa9thode de traduction 3 Probl\xc3\xa8mes rencontr\xc3\xa9s 4 Exemples de R\xc3\xa9sultats 5 \xc3\x89valuation du Bot 6 Programmation 7 Code 8 Conclusion et Remerciements   Description TranslatorBot a pour but de traduire les pages en plusieurs langues au moyen de la librairie Python: googletrans qui exploite les services de traduction de Google.  M\xc3\xa9thode de traduction On traduit par bloc d\'environ 5000 caract\xc3\xa8res, en adaptant la taille du bloc selon la ponctuation (afin d\'\xc3\xaatre certain de traduire une phrase compl\xc3\xa8te et non une partie de la phrase). Afin d\'avoir une meilleure synergie avec d\'autres bots, TranslatorBot prendra en param\xc3\xa8tre la liste des pages \xc3\xa0 traduire ainsi que la langue choisie. Cela permet de garder le contr\xc3\xb4le du bot et d\'\xc3\xa9viter qu\'il traduise \xc3\xa0 la cha\xc3\xaene chaque nouvelle page qu\'il trouve. TranslatorBot est enti\xc3\xa8rement modulable gr\xc3\xa2ce \xc3\xa0 un syst\xc3\xa8me de v\xc3\xa9rification du vocabulaire distinguant les noms propres des noms communs.  TranslatorBot cr\xc3\xa9e la page traduite dans un r\xc3\xa9pertoire correspondant \xc3\xa0 la langue choisie.  Probl\xc3\xa8mes rencontr\xc3\xa9s Un des premiers probl\xc3\xa8mes consid\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9s, au vu des pages d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 existantes sur wikipast, a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 la traduction des pages g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9es ou modifi\xc3\xa9es par des bots. Celles-ci \xc3\xa9tant parfois victimes d\'actions ind\xc3\xa9sirables d\'autres bots, leur contenu n\'a aucun sens et, par cons\xc3\xa9quent, devient impossible \xc3\xa0 traduire.  \xe2\x86\x92 Le probl\xc3\xa8me s\'est r\xc3\xa9gl\xc3\xa9 de lui-m\xc3\xaame: la m\xc3\xa9thode appel\xc3\xa9e par TranslatorBot garde la partie probl\xc3\xa9matique du texte non modifi\xc3\xa9e. Il s\'agit d\'un soucis \xc3\xa0 consid\xc3\xa9rer par le ManagerBot.  Si on ne traduit pas les hyperlinks, comment faire la diff\xc3\xa9rence entre un hyperlink d\'un nom propre qui va vers une page en fran\xc3\xa7ais et celui qui m\xc3\xa8ne en anglais? \xe2\x86\x92 Ce probl\xc3\xa8me est r\xc3\xa9gl\xc3\xa9 avec la solution pour les noms propres par biais d\'un nouveau bot qui classe les pages des personnalit\xc3\xa9s.  Un autre probl\xc3\xa8me important consiste en traduction des noms propres. A premi\xc3\xa8re vue, les noms propres tels que les noms g\xc3\xa9ographiques doivent \xc3\xaatre traduits; cependant, les noms des personnes ne sont pas \xc3\xa0 traduire. Un autre probl\xc3\xa8me se pose ici: comment distinguer un nom de famille d\'origine g\xc3\xa9ographique d\'un nom g\xc3\xa9ographique? \xe2\x86\x92 La solution la plus \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9gante serait de laisser \xc3\xa0 la prochaine vol\xc3\xa9e d\'\xc3\xa9tudiants la cr\xc3\xa9ation d\'un nouveau bot qui classerait les pages existantes selon leur genre. Ceci permettrait de facilement distinguer les pages de personnalit\xc3\xa9s des autres.  Une question pertinente est la s\xc3\xa9paration des blocs \xc3\xa0 traduire.  \xe2\x86\x92 On boucle sur le texte: on part du 5000-\xc3\xa8me caract\xc3\xa8re et on it\xc3\xa8re sur les caract\xc3\xa8res pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9dents pour trouver l\'indice d\'une ponctuation de fin de phrases. On traduit le bloc de texte jusqu\'\xc3\xa0 cet indice, et puis on r\xc3\xa9it\xc3\xa8re l\'op\xc3\xa9ration.   Comment g\xc3\xa9rer les pages traduites: r\xc3\xa9pertoire selon les langues  \xe2\x86\x92 (en cours de solution)  La mise en page est-elle conserv\xc3\xa9e par le bot\xc2\xa0?  \xe2\x86\x92 (en cours de solution)  Apr\xc3\xa8s la pr\xc3\xa9sentation:   rajout du tableau de langues de page -> modification de la page originale, v\xc3\xa9rification de l\'existence du tableau avant de l\'ajouter  le titre de la page est sous forme "(langue)___nom"  nouvelle id\xc3\xa9e: pour les pages qui n\'ont pas de traduction, ajouter un tableau de langues quand m\xc3\xaame, sauf que la deuxi\xc3\xa8me case serait un lien "Traduire la page" qui lance le TranslatorBot apr\xc3\xa8s le clic -> possibilit\xc3\xa9 de lancer le bot par un utilisateur simple (de fa\xc3\xa7on contr\xc3\xb4lable)  m\xc3\xaame chose pour les hyperliens: on traduit le texte du lien, du coup le lien sur la page traduite m\xc3\xa8ne vers une page inexistante; il faut alors appliquer le m\xc3\xaame syst\xc3\xa8me: si qqn clique sur le lien, au lieu de proposer de cr\xc3\xa9er une nouvelle page, il va lancer le bot qui va la cr\xc3\xa9er et traduire  Exemples de R\xc3\xa9sultats Original fran\xc3\xa7ais (cliquer pour agrandir):  R\xc3\xa9sultat de traduction par TranslatorBot (cliquer pour agrandir):   \xc3\x89valuation du Bot Temps de traduction: (\xc3\xa0 compl\xc3\xa9ter une fois l\'impl\xc3\xa9mentation du bot est termin\xc3\xa9e) Qualit\xc3\xa9 de traduction: (\xc3\xa0 compl\xc3\xa9ter une fois l\'impl\xc3\xa9mentation du bot est termin\xc3\xa9e)  Programmation Le bot a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9 au cours d\'un travail de groupe. Le code a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 partag\xc3\xa9 via une repository priv\xc3\xa9e sur GitHub. L\'environnement utilis\xc3\xa9 est Anaconda et Jupyter Notebook. L\'impl\xc3\xa9mentation du bot a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9e par des recherches sur la cr\xc3\xa9ation des bots.   Code  import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup from googletrans import Translator  user=\'testbot\' passw=\'dhbot2017\' baseurl=\'http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/\' summary=\'Wikipastbot update\' names=[\'Henri Dunant\'] translator = Translator()  # login request payload={\'action\':\'query\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'meta\':\'tokens\',\'type\':\'login\'} r1=requests.post(baseurl + \'api.php\', data=payload)  # login confirm login_token=r1.json()[\'query\'][\'tokens\'][\'logintoken\'] payload={\'action\':\'login\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'lgname\':user,\'lgpassword\':passw,\'lgtoken\':login_token} r2=requests.post(baseurl + \'api.php\', data=payload, cookies=r1.cookies)  # get edit token2 params3=\'?format=json&action=query&meta=tokens&continue=\' r3=requests.get(baseurl + \'api.php\' + params3, cookies=r2.cookies) edit_token=r3.json()[\'query\'][\'tokens\'][\'csrftoken\']  edit_cookie=r2.cookies.copy() edit_cookie.update(r3.cookies)  # we fetch the text we want to translate for name in names:     result=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+name+\'&export&exportnowrap\')     soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text, "lxml")     code=\'\'     for primitive in soup.findAll("text"):         code += primitive.string      translated_text = translator.translate(code[:5000], src=\'fr\', dest=\'en\').text          #Create names with english prefix     en_name = \'en/\' + translator.translate(name, src=\'fr\', dest=\'en\').text   Conclusion et Remerciements Nous remercions le cours SHS Humanit\xc3\xa9s Digitales pour cette magnifique opportunit\xc3\xa9 de nous organiser pour travailler sur un projet nouveau.     \t0'

b"Medical insurance as a term normally always describes what's commonly referred to as a health insurance policy or even a health insurance plan. It is important to tell apart these wordings, as sometimes medical insurance could literally refer to some form of errors and omissions policy for a hospital/doctor or another healthcare provider. This type of insurance does exist widely but generally speaking when people refer to medical insurance they're discussing what's commonly referred to as medical insurance or medical care insurance. Medical insurance that's referring to medical insurance has many general principles that are essential to understanding. While this sort of insurance conforms to all the conventional principles of most kinds of domestic insurance, it is a lot more tightly regulated and specified regarding cost and benefit than other types of insurance. Additionally, an insurance company will have a much tighter control over the number of benefits and who may or might not provide them. The fundamental idea behind a medical insurance/health insurance plan is that the policyholder will probably pay an insurance premium to the insurance company who'll agree to supply a variety of financial benefits which are meant to pay the price of medical intervention, possibly a remain in a hospital and other associated costs.  In case you loved this information and you would want to receive more details regarding health insurance hospital cover i implore you to visit the web-page. Where the insurance company has a very tight control is on two underlying concepts that define the idea of health insurance.<br/><br/>The first is what the insurance companies make reference to as prior authorization. Which means that if the policyholder wants to have any medical intervention or diagnosis or treatment that could be covered underneath the terms of the insurance plan, then your Policyholder must get the agreement of the organization to go ahead with such treatment before it taking place. If the policyholder does not get prior authorization in this sense, then the insurance company will virtually automatically decline to pay for any claim. The other term that company use is that of the diagnosis or treatment being deemed to be'medically necessary'with the business themselves making that decision regarding whether the treatment is medically necessary or not. This in effect means that any kind of medical intervention or treatment that the policyholder wishes to pursue must certanly be agreed beforehand by the insurance company, and the insurance company makes the last decision as to whether such treatment is important or not, not the policyholder or their physician or another healthcare provider. So, be wise and choose private medical insurance plans or expatriate insurance travel move carefully.     \t1"

b"Le terme Datafication biographique d\xc3\xa9signe \xc3\xa0 la fois le processus de transformation des \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa8nements d'une biographie en donn\xc3\xa9e formalis\xc3\xa9e, facilement lisible par des algorithmes et les donn\xc3\xa9es r\xc3\xa9sultantes (aussi appel\xc3\xa9 databio). La datafication biographique se base sur une forme standardis\xc3\xa9e pour d\xc3\xa9crire les \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa8nements, en pr\xc3\xa9cisant notamment la mani\xc3\xa8re d'encoder les lieux, les p\xc3\xa9riodes et les entit\xc3\xa9s nomm\xc3\xa9es. Chaque \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ment d'une datafication biographique doit \xc3\xaatre associ\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 un syst\xc3\xa8me d'indetification non ambigu\xc3\xab, en utilisant par exemple des URIs associ\xc3\xa9s aux noms de personnes, de lieux et des syst\xc3\xa8mes de coordonn\xc3\xa9es standardadis\xc3\xa9s pour les p\xc3\xa9riodes temporelles. Le caract\xc3\xa8re standardis\xc3\xa9 d'une Datafication Biographique permet une lecture automatique des informations biographiques ainsi mod\xc3\xa9lis\xc3\xa9es, permettant leur utilisation pour effectuer des inf\xc3\xa9rences et des tests de contraintes. Le terme datafication est introduit dans\xc2\xa0:  Mayer-Sch\xc3\xb6nberger, Viktor, and Kenneth Cukier. 2013. Big Data: A Revolution That Will Transform How We Live, Work, and Think. Houghton Mifflin Harcourt.     \t0"

b'The recent real estate debacle has devastated many families not only right here in the US however worldwide. It is simple to understand what number of have soured on real estate. The final 5 years have seen residence prices have skilled declines of 25% or much more. Total, the nationwide median residence price is predicted to drop 11.3% by  \xd0\xb4\xd0\xbe\xd0\xbc +\xd0\xb8\xd0\xb7 \xd1\x81\xd0\xb8\xd0\xbf \xd0\xbf\xd0\xb0\xd0\xbd\xd0\xb5\xd0\xbb\xd0\xb5\xd0\xb9 \xd0\xbf\xd0\xbe\xd0\xb4 \xd0\xba\xd0\xbb\xd1\x8e\xd1\x87 June 30, 2010, based on Fiserv, a monetary information and evaluation firm. For 2011, it anticipates some stabilization with costs rising 3.6%.<br/><br/>Numbers aside, you need a spot to live. By renting, you might be paying someone else\'s mortgage. You stroll away out of your lease and also you stroll away owning nothing. There is a long standing anecdote that claims "You may by no means get rich owning nothing".<br/><br/>This being mentioned, owing a home shouldn\'t be for everyone. According to Foreclosures.com, over 1 million folks lost their home to foreclosures last year. Whereas it can be argued there was rampant fraud by mortgage companies and appraisers, the speculative public can also be to be blamed. If there\'s a lesson to be discovered in this mess, it\'s that a house shouldn\'t be seen completely as an investment. It should be primarily seen as a place to rest your head on the end of an extended day.<br/><br/>Listed here are some points you should consider before purchasing a home:<br/><br/>How\'s your finances? <br/>Seize a sheet of paper and draw a line down the middle. On the left write down your AFTER tax income. In case you are a commissioned salesperson, stay extraordinarily conservative when predicting your monthly income. Subsequent write down all of your monthly expenses. Ideally you will wish to write down every part you spend for 60 days. This could offer you a good idea what you monthly revenue and outflow of money is. As a normal rule, your mortgage shouldn\'t exceed 28% of your take home income.<br/><br/>Your career scenario: <br/>How stable is your organization? How stable is your profession? Do you typically job hop or have you been on the identical agency for years. Unemployment is at 10% nationally. Some would argue the federal government is skewing the numbers down and that unemployment is definitely at 12-15%. Presently unemployment benefits max out at round $500 per week. There\'s a "bye" week, which means you aren\'t getting paid as well as a 6-8 week waiting period earlier than you receive your first unemployment check. In a worst case state of affairs, what would you do in the event you discovered your self unemployed? May you get by on $2,000 per month for 6 months or more?<br/><br/>Do you have got an emergency fund? <br/>Are you adequately prepared for an emergency? Typically it\'s best to have 6 months or more saved up. You\'ve already figured your price range (see above). If you\'re self employed, it\'s best to have eight-12 months of expenses saved. Till you\'ve your emergency fund absolutely funded, purchasing a house ought to be out of the question.<br/><br/>How\'s your car running? <br/>Whereas it is inconceivable to predict automotive repairs, it is potential to be prepared for them. Do you personal a automobile that is 10 years old with150,000 miles? When was the last time you changed your tires or breaks? You would possibly consider having a good mechanic check your car for anything which may break the bank earlier than you purchase your house. If you\'ll purchase a new house, you don\'t need any additional stress or monetary surprises.<br/><br/>I discovered a house I can afford, can I buy it now? <br/>Not fairly yet. Earlier than committing your hard earned cash, you\'ll want to have a mortgage company in place. You\'re going to know what your closing prices are going to be and have this money readily available. In case you are not prepared to live in your house for five years, do not even consider shopping for a house. Closing prices are expensive. If you\'re incorrect about your market, you could take giant loss when you must sell.<br/><br/>You\'ll additionally must understand how a lot your property taxes are going to cost. In addition, you\'ll want to fact in the price of homeowner\'s insurance. Insurance coverage prices can add several hundred dollars per thirty days in added expenses. You will want fire in addition to house proprietor\'s insurance. In sure cases, you may need flood, hurricane, volcano and earthquake insurance. Please seek the advice of with a superb insurance coverage agent. Don\'t forget to factor in shifting expenses as well as household gadgets such furniture.     \t1'

M\xc3\xa9thode de traduction On traduit par bloc d'environ 4500 caract\xc3\xa8res, en adaptant la taille du bloc selon la ponctuation (afin d'\xc3\xaatre certain de traduire une phrase compl\xc3\xa8te et non une partie de la phrase).     \t0"

b"<br/> Le panarabisme est un mouvement politique, culturel, et id\xc3\xa9ologique fortement s\xc3\xa9culier qui vise \xc3\xa0 r\xc3\xa9unir et \xc3\xa0 unifier les peuples arabes ou arabis\xc3\xa9s (correction(s): arabis\xc3\xa9 ). b'Sommaire  1 R\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9 des fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s 2 Description technique 3 Performances 4 Exemples de r\xc3\xa9sultats 5 Code   R\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9 des fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s Lutte activement contre les nombreux SPAMBot qui assi\xc3\xa8gent Wikipast.  Description technique Le but ce bot est d\'identifier les pages qui sont susceptibles d\'avoir \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es par des bot "malveillant". Nous avons d\xc3\xa9cid\xc3\xa9 de r\xc3\xa9soudre ce probl\xc3\xa8me en utilisant le machine learning, plus pr\xc3\xa9cis\xc3\xa9ment le deep learning, en utilisant un r\xc3\xa9seau de neurone r\xc3\xa9current, car il pr\xc3\xa9sente plusieurs aspects int\xc3\xa9ressants:   contrairement \xc3\xa0 un bot se basant sur des r\xc3\xa8gles pr\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9finies, notre bot sera capable de s\'adapter au nouveau type de bot vandal qui pourraient appara\xc3\xaetre sur le wikipast (nouvelles langues, nouvelles syntaxes, ...)  au fur et \xc3\xa0 mesure de l\'\xc3\xa9volution du wikipast, le r\xc3\xa9seau pourra \xc3\xaatre de nouveau entrain\xc3\xa9 afin de mieux d\xc3\xa9tecter les pages d\'origine v\xc3\xa9rifi\xc3\xa9es (pages cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es par le professeur, les \xc3\xa9tudiants, ou par les futures bots d\xc3\xa9velopp\xc3\xa9s dans le cadre du cours). Nous avons d\xc3\xa9cider d\'utiliser un r\xc3\xa9seau neuronal r\xc3\xa9current car il est l\'un des plus populaires, et probablement un des plus performants pour faire du text classification. Nous avons choisi d\'utiliser comme loss function le f-score au lieu du traditionel binary crossentropy, afin de minimiser le nombre de faux positifs et de maximiser le nombre de vrai n\xc3\xa9gatifs (le plus importants \xc3\xa9tant avant tout de ne pas enlever de pages v\xc3\xa9rifi\xc3\xa9es, en enlevant le plus de pages non-v\xc3\xa9rifi\xc3\xa9es possible). Lorsque le bot identifie une page susceptible d\'avoir \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9e par un bot, ce dernier la signalera en y ajoutant le flag ci dessous, et se sera alors au mod\xc3\xa9rateur de d\xc3\xa9cider de l\xe2\x80\x99avenir de la page.  FLAG  L\'algorithme g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ral est expliqu\xc3\xa9 ci-dessous:   nous avons d\xe2\x80\x99abord r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9 dans une liste tous les usernames des utilisateurs certifi\xc3\xa9s (\xc3\xa0 savoir les \xc3\xa9tudiants, les mod\xc3\xa9rateurs et leurs bots), et les pages qui leurs sont associ\xc3\xa9es. On a fait de m\xc3\xaame avec des utilisateurs et pages malveillants, en g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rant des pages al\xc3\xa9atoirement, et en v\xc3\xa9rifiant qu\xe2\x80\x99elles n\xe2\x80\x99appartiennent pas \xc3\xa0 la liste pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9dente.  \xc3\xa0 chaque page nous avons assign\xc3\xa9 un boolean, (true = bot, false = utilisateur certifi\xc3\xa9) afin d\xe2\x80\x99avoir une base de donn\xc3\xa9e sur laquelle le r\xc3\xa9seau neuronal peut s\xe2\x80\x99entra\xc3\xaener.  le r\xc3\xa9seau neuronal est ensuite entra\xc3\xaen\xc3\xa9 avec l\'ensemble  des pages r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9es.  une fois le r\xc3\xa9seau entra\xc3\xaen\xc3\xa9, il nous suffit de passer le contenu d\'une page \xc3\xa0 notre r\xc3\xa9seau qui d\xc3\xa9terminera si oui ou non cette page a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9e par un bot malveillant.   les pages d\xc3\xa9tect\xc3\xa9 comme \xc3\xa9tant du spam sont ensuite marqu\xc3\xa9es avec le flag d\xc3\xa9finit pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9demment et ajout\xc3\xa9es \xc3\xa0 une page contenant la liste de tous les spams ([[]]). Performances Exemples de r\xc3\xa9sultats Code Le code source est disponible sur Github     \t0'

b' Snoopy is a loyal, innocent, imaginative and good-natured beagle who is prone to imagining fantasy lives, including being an author, a college student known as "Joe Cool" and a World War I Royal Flying Corps ace. He is perhaps best known in this last alternate persona, wearing an aviator\'s helmet and goggles and a scarf while carrying a swagger stick. Snoopy can be selfish and/or lazy at times, and had his share of moments where he is mocking his owner, Charlie Brown, but through it all, he has shown great love, care, and loyalty for his owner (even though he can\'t even remember his name and always refers to him as "The Round-Headed Kid"). All of his fantasies have a similar formula: Snoopy pretends to be something, usually "world famous", and fails. His short "novels" are never published, and his Sopwith Camel is consistently shot down by his imaginary enemy, the Red Baron. Schulz said of Snoopy\'s character in a 1997 interview: "He has to retreat into his fanciful world in order to survive. Otherwise, he leads kind of a dull, miserable life. I don\'t envy dogs the lives they have to live."[3] Snoopy imagines himself to speak, but never actually does; much like with real life animals, the human characters are unaware of his musings. Though very rarely, he talks, but usually to himself. His (very articulate) thoughts are shown in thought balloons. In the animated Peanuts films and television specials, Snoopy\'s thoughts are not verbalized; his moods are instead conveyed through growls, sobs, laughter, and monosyllabic utterances such as "bleah" or "hey" as well as through pantomime. The only exceptions are in the animated adaptions of the musicals You\'re a Good Man, Charlie Brown and Snoopy!!! The Musical in which Snoopy\'s thoughts are verbalized by Robert Towers and Cameron Clarke respectively. (His dialogue, however, is not "heard" by the other characters except Woodstock and other non-human characters.) Snoopy\'s doghouse defies physics and is shown to be bigger on the inside than the outside. It is also his "airplane" in his fantasies. In the 90s comic strips, he is obsessed with cookies. b"Sommaire  1 Description 2 Scrapping d'informations 3 Test d'importance 1 4 Test d'importance 2 5 Interface   Description EntryMakerBot se base sur des archives de texte afin de d\xc3\xa9terminer quelles informations pourraient \xc3\xaatre ajout\xc3\xa9es \xc3\xa0 la page wikipast associ\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 la recherche. En t\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9chargeant le texte brut depuis les archives, il est possible de d\xc3\xa9terminer quelles lignes correspondent au personnage recherch\xc3\xa9, la date de publication du journal, puis d'effectuer un simple triage en fonction de leur pertinence. L'important r\xc3\xa9side dans le but fix\xc3\xa9 d'\xc3\xaatre capable de savoir quel objet s\xc3\xa9mantique est le plus important. Le fonctionnement du bot se divise en 3 \xc3\xa9tapes: Premi\xc3\xa8rement, un scrapping d'informations sur le site de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence (wikip\xc3\xa9dia) est effectu\xc3\xa9. L'algorithme d\xc3\xa9termine, gr\xc3\xa2ce aux locations du nom de la personne recherch\xc3\xa9e, les phrases du texte importantes pour la recherche d'informations. Deuxi\xc3\xa8mement, les phrases passent par un premier test d'importance puis les dix plus importantes sont s\xc3\xa9lectionn\xc3\xa9es afin de passer par la troisi\xc3\xa8me \xc3\xa9tape: Une s\xc3\xa9lection bas\xc3\xa9e sur le lexique382.  Scrapping d'informations En utilisant un crawler, il est possible de trouver un nombre d\xc3\xa9fini d'articles li\xc3\xa9 au personnage mais ne contenant pas son nom dans le titre (afin d'obtenir des informations diff\xc3\xa9rentes de ce que l'on pourrait trouver simplement en lisant son article wikip\xc3\xa9dia) et de les placer dans un dossier sp\xc3\xa9cifique. Dans chacun de ces fichier, une it\xc3\xa9ration sur chaque mot est effectu\xc3\xa9e afin de trouver les locations du nom du personnage recherch\xc3\xa9. En interpolant sur ces locations, il est ensuite possible de reconna\xc3\xaetre l'emplacement de l'article concernant la cible. Si le texte contient du bruit, il est ensuite nettoy\xc3\xa9, c'est \xc3\xa0 dire que les phrases illisibles sont supprim\xc3\xa9es, ainsi que les objets purement typographiques, afin de rendre le texte plus facile \xc3\xa0 analyser pour un ordinateur.   Test d'importance 1 Le premier test d'importance se fait en utilisant simplement les phrases analys\xc3\xa9es. Durant ce test, le nombre d'occurrences (le nombre de fois qu'il apparait dans le texte)  de chaque mot est compt\xc3\xa9 et avec cela on d\xc3\xa9termine leur fr\xc3\xa9quence dans le texte. Si la phrase contient le nom du personnage, on lui attribuera des points (ce qui va la faire monter dans le classement) puis les phrases avant et apr\xc3\xa8s celles-ci gagnent des points elles aussi sous forme d'une fonction en inverse d'exponentielle. Gr\xc3\xa2ce \xc3\xa0 ces informations, il est possible de classer les phrases et de d\xc3\xa9terminer celles ayant le plus de chances d'avoir des informations importantes.   Test d'importance 2 Le deuxi\xc3\xa8me test prend en input les dix premi\xc3\xa8res phrases dans le classement du premier puis refait un test d'occurence, mais cette fois-ci en utilisant la fr\xc3\xa9quence report\xc3\xa9e sur la table du lexique382. Gr\xc3\xa2ce \xc3\xa0 cela il est possible d'effectuer un nouveau classement et d'obtenir le r\xc3\xa9sultat final.  Interface Le bot poss\xc3\xa8de une interface utilisant la librairie tkinter. Some others buy them because a football shirt can be a very cool and practical thing to wear.<br/><br/>There is a wide array of shops that sell football shirts today. b"<br/>  Sommaire  1 Description 2 M\xc3\xa9thodes de correction 3 Exemples de R\xc3\xa9sultats 4 Remarques 5 \xc3\x89valuation du Bot 6 Code   Description OrthoBot d\xc3\xa9tecte les fautes d'orthographe. Il parcourt l'ensemble des mots d'une page, les compare \xc3\xa0 une liste de mots fran\xc3\xa7ais(dictionnaire), et propose une correction si un mot n'appartient pas \xc3\xa0 cette liste. Lorsque le bot d\xc3\xa9tecte une faute, il modifie la page en colorant le mot, et propose une correction de la forme:  faute(correction: 'correction1','correction2',...) . OrthoBot ne corrige pas les hypermots \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9e qu'il s'agit souvent de noms propres et qu'ils sont normalement correctement orthographi\xc3\xa9s.  M\xc3\xa9thodes de correction Lorsqu'une faute est trouv\xc3\xa9e, OrthoBot va chercher une correction possible en modifiant le mot pour trouver un correctif dans son dictionnaire. Pour se faire, il va appliquer successivement diff\xc3\xa9rentes m\xc3\xa9thodes pour pouvoir trouver le maximum de corrections possibles: -Cas 1: 1 lettre est fausse. Il modifie une \xc3\xa0 une chaque lettre du mot et teste s'il existe une correspondance dans le dictionnaire. Si oui, il proposera cette correction. -Cas 2: Il manque une lettre. Il teste l'ajout d'une lettre \xc3\xa0 chaque emplacement possible(au d\xc3\xa9but du mot, entre la 1e et la 2e lettre, etc.), cherche une correspondance dans le dictionnaire, propose une correction si elle existe. -Cas 3: Il y a une lettre en trop. Il essaye d'effacer chaque lettre une \xc3\xa0 une et contr\xc3\xb4le s'il existe une correspondance dans le dictionnaire et propose une \xc3\xa9ventuelle proposition. -Cas 4: Cas particuliers. Modifie la lettre 'f' par 'ph' et cherche une correction dans le dictionnaire. <br/>  Exemples de R\xc3\xa9sultats Si notre bot rencontre une page contenant le texte suivant: Ceci est une p\xc3\xa2ge test pour OrthoBot. Elle contien des fautes d'orthografe. Il va modifier la page comme ci-dessous: Ceci est une p\xc3\xa2ge (correction(s): page, p\xc3\xa2me, \xc3\xa2ge, pige, p\xc3\xa2te, p\xc3\xa2le) test pour OrthoBot. Elle contien (correction(s): contiens, contient) des fautes d'orthografe (correction(s): orthographe). Cet exemple est tir\xc3\xa9 de la page cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9e pour tester notre bot: testOrthobot  Remarques -Le dictionnaire ne comprenant pas de nom propres, OrthoBot les signale comme des fautes, notamment les lieux ou pays. Il semble donc important que ces mots soient des hypermots. -Possibilit\xc3\xa9 d'\xc3\xa9tendre le dictionnaire au noms propres en ajoutant \xc3\xa0 celui-ci des listes de mots (par exemple une liste de pays). -OrthoBot ne d\xc3\xa9tecte ni les fautes d'accords, ni celles de conjugaison, car ce ne sont pas des fautes d'orthographe \xc3\xa0 proprement parler. -La partie 'Cas particuliers' de la correction peut \xc3\xaatre \xc3\xa9tendue \xc3\xa0 de nombreuses fautes. -Une fois qu' OrthoBot trouve une faute sur une page, il la garde en m\xc3\xa9moire pour ne pas avoir \xc3\xa0 corriger ce mot plusieurs fois. -Si OrthoBot rencontre du texte color\xc3\xa9 soit en vert soit en rouge il ne le prend pas en compte. Si un mot est vert c'est qu'il est une proposition de correction donc il est correct, et si il est rouge, ce mot est orthographi\xc3\xa9 faux et a d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 signal\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 son auteur. Il est donc inutile dans ces deux cas de contr\xc3\xb4ler l'orthographe. -OrthoBot ne corrige pas le mot, il ne fait que proposer une solution, tout en modifiant la page. Il revient donc aux utilisateurs de corriger cette derni\xc3\xa8re apr\xc3\xa8s le passage du bot. -Le dictionnaire est, pour le moment, un dictionnaire de mots en fran\xc3\xa7ais uniquement. -Le bot ignore les parties des pages contenant du code, ainsi que les tableaux.  \xc3\x89valuation du Bot - Lorsqu'un mot est mal orthographi\xc3\xa9, il est syst\xc3\xa9matiquement d\xc3\xa9couvert. Mais un mot correctement orthographi\xc3\xa9 peut \xc3\xaatre \xc3\xa9valu\xc3\xa9 comme faux. Nous avons trouv\xc3\xa9 un total de 571 fautes diff\xc3\xa9rentes sur toutes les pages du wiki. Parmi ces fautes, 32% sont des mots provenant d'autres langues, principalement de l'anglais, 24% sont des noms propres (lieu, personnes), 21% sont des fautes diverses comme des abr\xc3\xa9viations ou des noms de m\xc3\xa9thodes de python. Enfin, 18% sont des vraies fautes: des mots r\xc3\xa9ellement mal \xc3\xa9crits qui doivent \xc3\xaatre corrig\xc3\xa9s. Et 5% des mots faux trouv\xc3\xa9s sont des mots correctement orthographi\xc3\xa9s qui ne sont malheureusement pas dans le dictionnaire que nous avons utilis\xc3\xa9. Une solution pour augmenter le pourcentage des vraies fautes serait de joindre \xc3\xa0 notre dictionnaire fran\xc3\xa7ais un dictionnaire anglais ainsi qu'un dictionnaire des noms propres. Cela r\xc3\xa9duirait d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 passablement le nombre de fautes trouv\xc3\xa9es et am\xc3\xa9liorerait l'efficacit\xc3\xa9 de notre bot. Il faudrait aussi si possible trouver un dictionnaire le plus r\xc3\xa9cent possible qui contient tous les n\xc3\xa9ologismes de ces derni\xc3\xa8res ann\xc3\xa9es. Le dictionnaire que nous utilisons n'est aussi pas complet au niveau des conjugaisons et cela peut amener notre bot \xc3\xa0 trouver une fausse erreur. - Le bot trouve toutes les corrections, selon les crit\xc3\xa8res d\xc3\xa9crits ci-dessus, d'un mot en un temps moyen d'environ 1 seconde pour un mot de 6 \xc3\xa0 8 caract\xc3\xa8res. Ce qui est raisonnable puisqu'une page contenant 60 fautes est \xc3\xa9valu\xc3\xa9e en 1 minute environ tandis qu'il faudrait beaucoup plus de temps pour le faire \xc3\xa0 la main suivant la taille de la page. -Notre Bot serait pr\xc3\xaat \xc3\xa0 \xc3\xaatre mis sur un serveur et ex\xc3\xa9cut\xc3\xa9 p\xc3\xa9riodiquement toutes les 24h. b'<br/> Chronobot est un bot programm\xc3\xa9 en langage Python et qui agit sur des pages Wikipast. Il permet de regrouper tous les \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements qui se sont pass\xc3\xa9s en une ann\xc3\xa9e dans une m\xc3\xaame page  Sommaire  1 Fonctionnement  1.1 G\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ralit\xc3\xa9s 1.2 Liste des fonctions  1.2.1 Fonctions principales 1.2.2 Fonctions secondaires     2 Exemples de pages cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es 3 Critiques et faiblesses du bot 4 Scheduling 5 Code source  5.1 main_one_page.py et main.py  5.1.1 main_one_page.py 5.1.2 main.py   5.2 select_pages.py  5.2.1 Code source 5.2.2 Whitelist   5.3 recherchedates2.py 5.4 modify_links.py 5.5 create_site.py 5.6 order.py et order_all.py  5.6.1 order.py 5.6.2 order_all.py   5.7 place_evenement.py 5.8 event_not_in_page.py 5.9 retrieve_content.py 5.10 split_date.py 5.11 smaller_than.py     Fonctionnement Chronobot va d\'abord effectuer un scan sur l\'ensemble des pages biographiques cr\xc3\xa9es par les \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa8ves du cours "Humanit\xc3\xa9s Digitales" (2017). Il effectue ensuite un scan sur tous les \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements relev\xc3\xa9s dans chaque page et en stocke la date (sous forme AAAA.MM.JJ) et la description dans une liste. Une fois cette liste en main, il cr\xc3\xa9e une page pour chaque jour diff\xc3\xa9rent. Pour des raisons pratiques, il est plus logique de n\'avoir qu\'une seule page par ann\xc3\xa9e avec tous les \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements relev\xc3\xa9s durant cette ann\xc3\xa9e class\xc3\xa9s chronologiquement. Pour ce faire, au lieu d\'agir directement sur l\'url de la page, Chronobot redirige chaque lien d\'un jour vers l\'url de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e correspondante. Enfin, il y \xc3\xa9crit l\'\xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nement en bas de la page de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e correspondante. Quand il finit le scan, il ordonne tous les \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements des pages ann\xc3\xa9es qui ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 modifi\xc3\xa9es. La gestion des doublons est r\xc3\xa9solue ult\xc3\xa9rieurement.  G\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ralit\xc3\xa9s  Concepteurs\xc2\xa0: Arnau Alb\xc3\xa0 Jacas, Sonia Bouchiba, Jonathan Charri\xc3\xa8re, S\xc3\xa9bastien Morel, Aur\xc3\xa9lien Verdier.  UserName\xc2\xa0: ChronoBOT Liste des fonctions Fonctions principales  select_page.py parcourt les diff\xc3\xa9rentes pages sur une s\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ection pr\xc3\xa9cise de Users (ceux du cours SHS) et en retourne les pages cr\xc3\xa9es sous formes de cha\xc3\xaenes brutes (String). Les images (.png) sont \xc3\xb4t\xc3\xa9es ainsi que  recherchedates.py prend en argument une page donn\xc3\xa9e (string) et en sort une liste ann\xc3\xa9e/\xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nement  modify_links.py modifie toutes les pages des dates pour qu\'elles soient redirig\xc3\xa9es vers la page de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e.   create_new_site.py cr\xc3\xa9e une page Wikipast avec le contenu donn\xc3\xa9  order.py ordonne une page dans l\'ordre chronologique et order_all.py effectue order.py sur toutes les pages une fois qu\'elles sont toutes \xc3\xa9crites.  place_evenement.py \xc3\xa9crit un \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nement dans une page.  event_not_in_page.py g\xc3\xa8re les doublons en comparant deux strings-\xc3\xa9venements caract\xc3\xa8re par caract\xc3\xa8re. Il consid\xc3\xa8re ainsi deux \xc3\xa9venements identiques s\'ils contiennent les m\xc3\xaames suites de caract\xc3\xa8res. Il ne tient pas compte des virgules (,), points (.) et espaces ( ) s\'ils sont diff\xc3\xa9rents dans les deux strings.   Fonctions secondaires  retrieve_content.py prend en input le nom d\'une page et retourne tout le texte contenu en syntaxe wiki.  split_date.py prend en input une date \'aaaa.mm.jj\' et retourne une array [ann\xc3\xa9e, mois, jour]. Exemples de pages cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es  1990.02.23 -> redirection vers 1990  1990.06 -> redirection vers 1990  1990 Critiques et faiblesses du bot  Optimisation du code (plusieurs minutes pour s\'ex\xc3\xa9ctuer sur toutes les pages.)   Si une ann\xc3\xa9e a d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9e avant notre bot et une phrase a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 ajout\xc3\xa9e, par exemeple "Grande ann\xc3\xa9e" redigirig\xc3\xa9e vers "1995" comportait une phrase comman\xc3\xa7ant par "Grande ann\xc3\xa9e". Pour r\xc3\xa9soudre ce probl\xc3\xa8me, deux solutions sont enbisageables\xc2\xa0: la premi\xc3\xa8re, assez radicale, est d\'effacer la ligne en question dans la page Wikpast. La seconde (celle choisie, plus douce) est   Gestion des doublons\xc2\xa0: pourrait \xc3\xaatre am\xc3\xa9lior\xc3\xa9 dans la comparaison de deux \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements similaires. Actuellement, seules deux \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements \xc3\xa9crits exactement pareils ne sont pas d\xc3\xa9doubl\xc3\xa9s (par la fonction event_not_in_page.py), mais on pourrait imaginer qu\'un \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nement du type Mariage qui serait \xc3\xa9crit comme "A se marie avec B" dans la page de A et "B se marie avec A" dans la page de B, et qui serait donc relev\xc3\xa9 deux fois.   Normalisation des dates sur les pages de la database (car par exemple une inversion mois-jour pas prise en compte actuellement)  Classement chronologique des \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements dans les pages de la database  Section "Mois" dans les pages ann\xc3\xa9es Scheduling Tant que le nombre d\'utilisateurs reste en accord avec le nombre d\'\xc3\xa9tudiants dans le cours "Humanit\xc3\xa9s Digitales" de l\'EPFL, le bot va tourner une fois par semaine. Si wikiapst devient un site ouvert au public, il faudra \xc3\xa9ventuellement le lancer plus fr\xc3\xa9quemment. recherchedates2(page_name):      x=str(retrieve_content(page_name))      x=x.split("\\n")     dates=[]     for i in x:         d_start=i.find("[[")         if (d_start!=-1) and text      #check for repeated lines     provisional=[]     for line in newtext:         if line not in provisional:             provisional.append(line)        newtext=provisional          ok=0 Si cet evenement est d\xc3\xa9ja dans la page de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e il renvoie 0 Si il n\'est pas encore dans la page de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e il renvoie 1 \'\'\'  from retrieve_content import retrieve_content  def event_not_in_page(date,evenement):     text=retrieve_content(str(date)).replace(\' \',\'\')     text=text.replace(\',\',\'\')     text=text.replace(\'.\',\'\')     pos=evenement.find(\']]\')     evenement=evenement[pos+2:].replace(\' \',\'\')     evenement=evenement.replace(\',\',\'\')     evenement=evenement.replace(\'.\',\'\')     if evenement in text:         return 0     else:         return 1   retrieve_content.py  \'\'\' cette fonction prend en input le nom d\'une page et retourne tout le text qu\'il y a dedans, en code wiki \'\'\' import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup  def retrieve_content(name):     baseurl=\'http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/\'     result=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+name+\'&export&exportnowrap\')     soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text, "html.parser")     code=\'\'     if soup.findAll("text")[0][\'bytes\']==\'0\':         return code     for primitive in soup.findAll("text"):         code+=primitive.string     return code   split_date.py  def split_date(date): #format date: \'aaaa.mm.jj\'  /!\\ la date doit \xc3\xaatre au format string     date=str(date); #on est jamais trop s\xc3\xbbr     annee=\'\';     mois=\'\';     jour=\'\';     for i in range(len(date)):         if(i<4): annee=annee+date[i];         if(i>4 and i<7): mois=mois+date[i];         if(i>7 and i<10): jour=jour+date[i];     return [annee, mois, jour];   smaller_than.py  def smaller_than(date1,date2):#need to be format aaaa.mm.dd                                 #a year of format aaaa is always smaller     #case aaaa     if(len(date1)==4):         return 1     if(len(date2)==4):         return 0     #case     m1=date1[5:7]     d1=date1[8:]     m2=date2[5:7]     d2=date2[8:]      if(m1<m2):         return 1     elif(m1>m2):         return 0     elif(m1==m2):         if(d1<=d2):             return 1         else:             return 0      \t0'

[2]La R\xc3\xa9publique Arabe Unie (RAU) (\xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xac\xd9\x85\xd9\x87\xd9\x88\xd8\xb1\xd9\x8a\xd8\xa9 \xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xb9\xd8\xb1\xd8\xa8\xd9\x8a\xd8\xa9 \xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd9\x85\xd8\xaa\xd8\xad\xd8\xaf\xd8\xa9 al (correction(s): val, alu, ml, cal, ail, aa, an, l, mal, a\xc3\xaf, bal, dal, a, ah, ale, il, au, gal, pal, ai, as ) jumh\xc5\xabr\xc4\xabya al (correction(s): val, alu, ml, cal, ail, aa, an, l, mal, a\xc3\xaf, bal, dal, a, ah, ale, il, au, gal, pal, ai, as )-arab\xc4\xabya al (correction(s): val, alu, ml, cal, ail, aa, an, l, mal, a\xc3\xaf, bal, dal, a, ah, ale, il, au, gal, pal, ai, as )-mutta\xc4\xa5ida) est un \xc3\x89tat cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9 en 1958 par l'union de l'\xc3\x89gypte et de la Syrie, puis, pendant une courte p\xc3\xa9riode, du [[Y\xc3\xa9men. Il a disparu en 1961 mais l'\xc3\x89gypte continua \xc3\xa0 \xc3\xaatre appel\xc3\xa9e sous ce nom officiel jusqu'en 1971. Cette tentative d'union rel\xc3\xa8ve du panarabisme nass\xc3\xa9rien.  1965.02.19 / Le Caire\xc2\xa0: Arriv\xc3\xa9e d'Ernesto Rafael Guevara en voyage au Caire, afin de d\xc3\xa9velopper les relations \xc3\xa9conomiques entre la R\xc3\xa9publique Arabe Unie (RAU) et Cuba. b'BERLIN (AP) - Millions of Europeans who arrived late to work or school Wednesday had a good excuse - an unprecedented lag in the continent\'s electricity grid that\'s slowing down some clocks.<br/><br/>The problem is caused by a political dispute between Serbia and Kosovo that\'s sapping a small amount of energy from the local grid, causing a domino effect across the 25-nation network spanning the continent from Portugal to Poland and Greece to Germany.<br/><br/>"Since the European system is interconnected ... when there is an imbalance somewhere the frequency slightly drops," said Claire Camus, a spokeswoman for the European Network of Transmission System Operators for Electricity.<br/><br/>FILE - In this Nov. 1, 2017 file photo high power cables hang from a pole on a field in Hattersheim, Germany. Millions of Europeans who arrived late to work or school Wednesday March 7, 2018 have a good excuse: an unprecedented slowing of the frequency of the continent\'s electricity grid. The Brussels-based European Network of Transmission System Operators for Electricity, or ENTSO-E, says the problem began mid-January and affects 25 countries, from Portugal to Poland and Greece and Germany. (AP Photo/Michael Probst,file)<br/><br/>The Brussels-based organization, known as ENTSO-E, said in a separate statement that "this average frequency deviation, that has never happened in any similar way in the Continental European power system, must cease."<br/><br/>The deviation from Europe\'s standard 50 Hz frequency has been enough to cause electric clocks that keep time by the power system\'s frequency, rather than built-in quartz crystals, to fall behind by about six minutes since mid-January. The problem mostly affects radio alarms, oven clocks or clocks used to program heating systems.<br/><br/>ENTSO-E said it\'s working on a technical solution that could bring the system back to normal within "a few weeks," but urged European authorities and national governments to address the political problem at the heart of the issue.<br/><br/>"This is beyond the technical world. Now there needs to be an agreement between Serbia and Kosovo about this lack of energy in the Kosovo system. You need to solve it politically and then technically," Camus told The Associated Press.<br/><br/>The friction between Serbia and Kosovo is part of a broader  Agen Judi Bole dispute that goes back almost 20 years. Since the war in Kosovo ended in 1999, the Serb-dominated north of Kosovo that remains loyal to Belgrade, haven\'t paid the Kosovo government for the energy they consume.<br/><br/>A 2015 agreement was meant to resolve the dispute, but Serbia has blocked its implementation.<br/><br/>Serbia\'s power grid company EMS blamed the problem on Kosovo, claiming that in January and February the country "was uninterruptedly withdrawing, in an unauthorized manner, uncontracted electric energy from the Continental Europe synchronous area."<br/><br/>Kadri Kadriu, deputy manager of Kosovo\'s grid operator KOSTT, acknowledged that electricity from elsewhere was diverted to the Serb minority in the north, but said consumers there hadn\'t paid for their electricity, causing considerable financial burden to the company.<br/><br/>ENTSO-E warned that "if no solution can be found at political level, a deviation risk could remain."<br/><br/>So far the only consequence seems to be the effect on clocks.<br/><br/>"The system is built in such a way that all your basic needs are really secured by the distribution and the transmission system operators," Camus said. "Frankly, there is no risk other than those clocks running behind."<br/><br/>___<br/><br/>Dusan Stojanovic and Jovana Gec in Belgrade, Serbia, Llazar Semini in Tirana, Albania, and Sylvain Plazy in Brussels, contributed to this report.<br/><br/>Advertisement     \t1'

b'  Langue  Fran\xc3\xa7ais  English  d\xc3\xa9finition Un n-gramme est une sous-s\xc3\xa9quence de n \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ments construite \xc3\xa0 partir d\'une s\xc3\xa9quence donn\xc3\xa9e. [1]  applications Cette notion s\'utilise g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ralement avec des s\xc3\xa9quences de caract\xc3\xa8res ou de mots:  n-gramme de caract\xc3\xa8res\xc2\xa0: suite cons\xc3\xa9cutive et ordonn\xc3\xa9e de n caract\xc3\xa8res. exemple\xc2\xa0: Si la s\xc3\xa9quence est "le chat court." la liste des 3-grammes de caract\xc3\xa8re est "le_", "e_c", "_ch", "cha", "hat", "at_", "t_c", "_co", "cou", "our" et "urt".  n-gramme de mots\xc2\xa0: suite cons\xc3\xa9cutive et ordonn\xc3\xa9e de n mots. exemple\xc2\xa0: Si la s\xc3\xa9quence est "le chat noir court vite." la liste des 3-grammes de mots est "le chat noir", "chat noir court" et "noir court vite".  n-gram viewer Le n-gram viewer est l\'outil qui permet d\'afficher le graphique de la fr\xc3\xa9quence normalis\xc3\xa9e (g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ralement par ann\xc3\xa9e) des n-grammes de mots par rapport au temps (g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ralement les ann\xc3\xa9es). Il permet de visualiser le profil temporel des mots, c.a.d. l\'\xc3\xa9volution de la fr\xc3\xa9quence d\'utilisation des mots, dans un corpus donn\xc3\xa9e.     \t0'

b"Once you work your whole life somewhere on the way, you begin considering retirement. Things you wish to do, places to go and other things that would not require being in a certain place from 9 to 5 every day. One method to assure this type of retirements is to think ahead with a pension annuity. Individuals who decide, while they're working, they wish to include this income with their retirement arrange to have monthly deductions from their paycheck directly deposited into the annuity account. Like this, you may not feel any hardship but, rather, it is much like having Social Security or various other automatic payment. You will be amazed at how quickly contributions to the plan add up to a sizable amount, which will be earning interest entirely along. There is a wide range of annuities which are available, so it's essential that you carefully examine each one of these to find something that will fit your requirements. A number of the annuities charge fees, which are periodically deducted, and the interest earnings on some rely on the stock market. Finding one that matches your particular needs is simple and can really pay off when retirement time comes around. When seated by having an Annuity agent, he or she'll look over all your personal information such as current age, expected retirement, how much cash is likely to be needed at that time, other income and so forth.  If you have almost any questions relating to wherever in addition to tips on how to work with investment adviser, you can e-mail us at our web page. With this particular information at hand, they will have a way to assist you in calculating which annuity best fits your needs to meet up the needed retirement income.<br/><br/>An annuity is an agreement in that you simply agree to pay a quantity of money in return for receiving an income either for your entire lifetime or for a set period. It should be considered an investment in your future. This is the reason it is so important to decide on one that may participate in your retirement lifestyle. Most annuities add a guaranteed death benefit which allows the total amount remaining in the annuity to be handed down to your beneficiary. This usually avoids going through probate in many states. Also, all interest earned on the policy is tax-deferred until withdrawn. The forms of annuities are Fixed Annuity, Indexed Annuity, Deferred Annuity, and Immediate Annuity. A few of these also provide sub-types. Each offer different options. Fixed Annuity, for instance, guarantees a fixed interest rate, Indexed Annuity's interest rate depends upon the performance of the stock market but will never fall below zero. Deferred Annuity identifies putting off when payments will become, and Immediate Annuity involves creating a lump sum deposit and starting to gather the premium payment and interest right away. A pension annuity may have charges attached, and others are an investment that may gain or lose money. As mentioned, if you should be considering adding an annuity to your retirement package it is important that you sit back with a financial advisor and review every one of the terms of each kind of annuity.     \t1"

b'<br/>  Sommaire  1 Description 2 Exemples 3 Performances 4 Code  4.1 IMAGEBOT_v2_categorysearch 4.2 IMAGEBOT_v2_namesearch     Description ImageBot scan toutes les pages de biographies, certaines de lieu du wiki et les illustre en y ins\xc3\xa9rant une image en Creative Commons issu de la biblioth\xc3\xa8que d\xe2\x80\x99image Yahoo. Lorsque le bot scan une page, il v\xc3\xa9rifie d\xe2\x80\x99abord si cette page poss\xc3\xa8de une image et s\'il n\xe2\x80\x99y a pas d\xe2\x80\x99image il ajoute une image ad\xc3\xa9quate en haut \xc3\xa0 droite de la page en question. Si une image est d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 pr\xc3\xa9sente sur la page mais qu\xe2\x80\x99elle n\xe2\x80\x99est pas au tout d\xc3\xa9but, alors elle sera d\xc3\xa9plac\xc3\xa9e au tout d\xc3\xa9but mais une nouvelle image ne sera pas ajout\xc3\xa9e. Pour ajouter une image aux pages biographiques, le bot scan la page Biographies et pour chaque personne il y ajoute une image selon les r\xc3\xa8gles pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9dentes.  Pour les lieux, pour le moment, le bot scan les lieux de la page Naissance et pour chaque entr\xc3\xa9e y ajoute aussi une image. Pour recevoir une liste de titres de pages on peut facilement ins\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9r une condition dans la recherche des titres afin d\'extraire des nouveaux param\xc3\xaatres de recherche. Nous avons test\xc3\xa9 sur une centaine d\'entr\xc3\xa9es et tant que le layout de la page Biographies/Naissance n\'est pas modifi\xc3\xa9 par un autre bot il n\'y a aucun conflit avec les autres bots. Une p\xc3\xa9riode optimale pour le lancement du bot est tout les trois jours.  Exemples     Cette page       et cette page       donnent toutes les deux cette page     Performances Ce bot \xc3\xa9tant g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ral, il ne pr\xc3\xa9cise pas la cat\xc3\xa9gorie du mot que l\'on recherche, ainsi pour certains lieux l\xe2\x80\x99ajout d\xe2\x80\x99image n\xe2\x80\x99est pas ad\xc3\xa9quat. En effet un lieu ayant un nom de personne ou d\xe2\x80\x99autres choses plus populaires aboutira \xc3\xa0 cette recherche et non celle voulue. Une solution possible pour des recherches manuelles est pr\xc3\xa9sent\xc3\xa9e avec le code IMAGEBOT_v2_namesearch. L\'implementation du bot Listepagesbot permettrait d\'obtenir la liste de toutes les pages du wiki, afin d\xe2\x80\x99ajouter une image \xc3\xa0 cette liste enti\xc3\xa8re et pas seulement les lieux de naissance et les biographies. Cependant, en r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence au point pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9dent, il faudrait impl\xc3\xa9menter une pr\xc3\xa9cision de la cat\xc3\xa9gorie du mot recherch\xc3\xa9. Nous ne l\'avons pas fait afin de garder le c\xc3\xb4t\xc3\xa9 g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ral du bot, mais aussi car ceci est difficilement r\xc3\xa9alisable. En effet, il faudrait rechercher des sch\xc3\xa9mas qui permettent d\'identifier le type d\'entr\xc3\xa9e (comme par exemple majuscules aux deux mots pour une personne ou une pr\xc3\xa9position au milieu des trois mots pour un lieu, et l\xc3\xa0 il y aura encore des probl\xc3\xa8mes avec les noms de nobles, ex: "Lancelot du Lac"). D\'autres options ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 pr\xc3\xa9sent\xc3\xa9es lors du cours 8 de Maud Ehrmann. Cependant, le code permets de rajouter une cat\xc3\xa9gorie en sp\xc3\xa9cifiant une page de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence, de laquelle ont aimerait aussi consid\xc3\xa9rer les entr\xc3\xa9es dans l\'extraction du bot, de la m\xc3\xaame facon que pour les pages de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rences Naissance et Biographies d\'o\xc3\xb9 le bot extrait la liste des pages a traiter. En effet, la liste fourni par Listepagesbot ne pr\xc3\xa9cise pas la cat\xc3\xa9gorie de chaque titre et donc il faudrait un autre bot qui s\'occuperait de cette fonction.  Probl\xc3\xa8me si quelqu\'un a d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 ajout\xc3\xa9 manuellement une image auparavant mais qui n\'est pas une image de la personne ou du lieu de la page: La premi\xc3\xa8re telle image sera alors d\xc3\xa9plac\xc3\xa9e au d\xc3\xa9but de la page, comme si c\'\xc3\xa9tait une image qui illustrait la page mais qui \xc3\xa9tait mal plac\xc3\xa9e. Les images suivantes ne seraient pas touch\xc3\xa9s. Le bot n\'acc\xc3\xa8pte donc pas un placement individuel de la premi\xc3\xa8re image. Le bot ne fonctionne pas si la page \xc3\xa0 modifier existe, mais est vide. (il v\xc3\xa9rifie si une image est pr\xc3\xa9sente dans un caract\xc3\xa8re vide et donc affiche une erreur). Cependant, il fonctionne si la page est inexistante et donc, dans ce cas, il va la cr\xc3\xa9er et placer l\'image (il ne v\xc3\xa9rifie pas la pr\xc3\xa9sence ou non d\'image car la page n\'existait pas et donc le bot fonctionne). Ce probl\xc3\xa8me de page vide peut \xc3\xaatre r\xc3\xa9gl\xc3\xa9 avec un contr\xc3\xb4le de page vide et une action \xc3\xa0 r\xc3\xa9aliser dans ce cas. Ou avec un Bot s\xc3\xa9par\xc3\xa9 qui s\'occupe de supprimer les pages cr\xc3\xa9es mais vides. Code IMAGEBOT_v2_categorysearch Code automatis\xc3\xa9 pour la recherche des bibliographies et des endroits a partir des Pages Biographies et Naissance. Des autres Pages de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence peuvent \xc3\xaatre ajout\xc3\xa9es. Attention: Une fois lanc\xc3\xa9 ce bot modifie beaucoup de pages, c\'est pourquoi une confirmation des Titres extraits dans les pages est necessaire. Celle-ci peut aussi \xc3\xaatre enlev\xc3\xa9e.   abcd= contient tous les pages sources pour \xc3\xa9xtraire les titres des pages  apr\xc3\xa8s la boucle for sur abcd il y a un names=[] qui peut \xc3\xaatre d\xc3\xa9comment\xc3\xa9 et utilis\xc3\xa9 pour tester le bot sur une seule ou plusieures pages test.     import re import urllib2 import requests import os from bs4 import BeautifulSoup # b'  Language  Fran\xc3\xa7ais  English  definition An n-gram is a subsequence of n elements constructed from a given sequence. [1]  applications This notion is generally used with sequences of characters or words:  n-gram of characters\xc2\xa0: consecutive and ordered sequence of n characters. example: If the sequence is "the cat runs." the list of 3-gram of character is "the", "he_", "e_c", "_ca", "cat", "at_", "t_r", "_ru", "run" and "uns".  n-gram of words\xc2\xa0: consecutive and ordered sequence of n words. example: If the sequence is "the black cat runs fast." the list of 3-gram of words is "the black cat", "black cat runs" et "cat runs fast".  n-gram viewer The n-gram viewer is the tool used to display the graph of the normalized frequency (usually per year) of n-grams of words over time (usually years). It allows to visualize the temporal profile of the words, ie the evolution of the frequency of use of the words, in a given corpus.     \t0'

Individuals who decide, while they're working, they wish to incorporate this income with their retirement arrange to have monthly deductions from their paycheck directly deposited into the annuity account. Using this method, you don't feel any hardship but, rather, it is like having Social Security or some other automatic payment. You is likely to be amazed at how fast contributions to the program add up to sizable amount, which will be earning interest entirely along. There's a wide variety of annuities which are available, therefore it is important that you carefully examine every one to locate something which will fit your requirements. A number of the annuities charge fees, which are periodically deducted, and the interest earnings on some depend on the stock market. Finding one that matches your particular needs is straightforward and really can pay off when retirement time comes around. When seated with an Annuity agent, he or she'll check out all your individual information such as for instance current age, expected retirement age, how much money will soon be needed in those days, other income and so forth. It is highly recommended an investment in your future. This is the reason it's so important to decide on one that'll fit in with your retirement lifestyle. Most annuities include a guaranteed death benefit which allows the balance remaining in the annuity to be offered to your beneficiary. This usually avoids going right through probate in many states. Also, all interest earned on the policy is tax-deferred until withdrawn. The forms of annuities are Fixed Annuity, Indexed Annuity, Deferred Annuity, and Immediate Annuity. Some of these also provide sub-types. Each offer different options. Fixed Annuity, for instance, guarantees a fixed interest rate, Indexed Annuity's interest rate is dependent upon the performance of the stock market but won't fall below zero. Deferred Annuity describes postponing when payments begins, and Immediate Annuity involves creating a lump sum deposit and starting to collect the premium payment and interest right away. A pension annuity may have charges attached, and others are an investment that may gain or lose money. As previously mentioned, if you should be considering adding an annuity to your retirement package it's essential that you sit down with an economic advisor and review every one of the terms of each type of annuity.     \t1"
b'Overview<br/>Retrocalcaneal Bursitis. This bursa is located at the back of the heel. Bursitis in this area is often associated with conditions such as ankylosing spondylitis or rheumatoid arthritis. It can occur in healthy individuals who wear improperly fitted shoes. Symptoms include painful swelling that develops at the back of the heel. Calcaneal Bursitis. This bursa is located at the sole or bottom of the heel. Inflammation usually produces pain in the heel when standing. Causes include heel spurs, excess weight, injury, and wearing improperly fitted shoes.<br/><br/>Causes<br/>Overtraining in a runner (eg, excessive increases in miles or intensity). Tight or poorly fitting shoes that, because of a restrictive heel counter, exert excessive pressure on the posterior heel and ankle<br/>Haglund deformity, causing impingement between the increased posterior superior calcaneal prominence and the Achilles tendon during dorsiflexion. More recent research suggests that a misaligned subtalar joint axis (measured in terms of joint inclination and deviation) in relation to the Achilles tendon can result in an asymmetrical force load on the tendon, disrupting normal biomechanics. This altered joint axis is associated with an increased risk for Achilles pathologies, including bursitis.<br/><br/>Symptoms<br/>Your heel may feel more sensitive to the cold and ache in cold and damp weather due to impaired circulation. These symptoms are often the result of failure to treat the injury properly from the outset and overicing.<br/><br/>Diagnosis<br/>Plain radiographs of the calcaneus may reveal a Haglund deformity (increased prominence of the posterosuperior aspect of the calcaneus). However, on weight-bearing lateral radiographs, the retrocalcaneal recess often appears normal even in patients with retrocalcaneal bursitis, limiting its usefulness in making this diagnosis.Radiographs may be used as a diagnostic measure to support a clinician?s diagnosis of retrocalcaneal bursitis. Individuals with retrocalcaneal bursitis may have an absence of the normal radiolucency (ie, blunting) that is seen in the posteroinferior corner of the Kager fat pad, known as the retrocalcaneal recess or bursal wedge. This may occur with or without an associated erosion of the calcaneus.<br/><br/>Non Surgical Treatment<br/>So what can you do to alleviate this type of pain in the foot? If the bursitis pain is occurring on the toes, bunion or back of the heel area the smart money would be on eliminating the shoes that seem to aggravate the condition. Eliminating these shoes may not in itself clear up the problem but you can be sure that if you continue to wear the offending shoes nothing you or your doctor do will permanently\xc2\xa0?fix? the problem. A recurring theme that I use throughout this site that if you put an abnormally shaped foot in a dressy shoe it is literally the same as trying to put a square peg in a round hole, it will not fit. OK, so you threw away those dressy shoes and the foot still hurts, now what? Depending on the severity of the pain, over the counter anti-inflammatory medication may do the trick. The key here is to take the medication on an ongoing basis, according to the directions on the package to build up therapeutic blood levels. Assuming you can tolerate this type of medication, along with alternative treatments you can try). take the medication for 10-14 days. Stop if the symptoms have not dramatically improved. Icing the area during this period may also help reduce the symptoms.<br/><br/>Surgical Treatment<br/>Surgery. Though rare, particularly challenging cases of retrocalcaneal bursitis might warrant a bursectomy, in which the troublesome bursa is removed from the back of the ankle. Surgery can be effective, but operating on this boney area can cause complications, such as trouble with skin healing at the incision site. In addition to removing the bursa, a doctor may use the surgery to treat another condition associated with the retrocalcaneal bursitis. For example, a surgeon may remove a sliver of bone from the back of the heel to alter foot mechanics and reduce future friction. Any bone spurs located where the Achilles attaches to the heel may also be removed. Regardless of the conservative treatment that is provided, it is important to wait until all pain and swelling around the back of the heel is gone before resuming activities. This may take several weeks. Once symptoms are gone, a patient may make a gradual return to his or her activity level before their bursitis symptoms began. Returning to activities that cause friction or stress on the bursa before it is healed will likely cause bursitis symptoms to flare up again.     \t1'
