b'Le code pour le bot est disponible sur https://github.com/mj2905/InferenceBot. Il suffit de lancer le fichier python main.py, puis de taper autorun lorsqu\'une entr\xc3\xa9e utilisateur est demand\xc3\xa9e. La d\xc3\xa9duction est un principe en intelligence artificielle qui permet d\xe2\x80\x99obtenir de nouvelles informations en se basant sur des faits, et des r\xc3\xa8gles d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9tablies.  Pour la r\xc3\xa9alisation de ce projet, nous avons divis\xc3\xa9 le travail \xc3\xa0 accomplir en trois parties, chacune pouvant \xc3\xaatre modul\xc3\xa9e, afin de pouvoir \xc3\xaatre \xc3\xa9tendue par la suite\xc2\xa0:   Le \xe2\x80\x9cwiki scraping\xe2\x80\x9d (r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9ration des informations), qui nous permet de lire directement r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9rer des informations en provenance du wiki. En l\'occurrence, pour notre bot, ces informations correspondent aux diff\xc3\xa9rents faits qui seront utilis\xc3\xa9s pour d\xc3\xa9duire d\xe2\x80\x99autres faits.  Le moteur d\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence, qui va inf\xc3\xa9rer des informations \xc3\xa0 partir de ce qui lui est fourni en entr\xc3\xa9e.  Le \xe2\x80\x9cwiki writing\xe2\x80\x9d (\xc3\xa9criture des informations sur le wiki) qui va \xc3\xa9crire les faits d\xc3\xa9duits, consid\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9s comme utiles, dans le wiki.<br/><br/> Sommaire  1 Le wiki scraping 2 Le moteur d\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence 3 La g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ration de Graphe de parent\xc3\xa9 4 Le wiki writer 5 Exemple d\xe2\x80\x99Output 6 Autonomie 7 \xc3\x89valuation des performances   Le wiki scraping Les objectifs fix\xc3\xa9s pour la r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9ration des donn\xc3\xa9es sur le wiki \xc3\xa9taient les suivants:   Modularit\xc3\xa9: \xc3\xa9tendre le code du programme pour r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9rer davantage de faits doit \xc3\xaatre facile.  Flexibilit\xc3\xa9: de petits \xc3\xa9carts dans le format d\'une ligne ne doivent pas faire \xc3\xa9chouer l\'extraction des faits.  Abstraction: la r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9ration des donn\xc3\xa9es ne doit pas pr\xc3\xa9senter de couplage avec le reste du programme. Pour r\xc3\xa9aliser les objectifs ci-dessus, nous avons impl\xc3\xa9ment\xc3\xa9 le bot de la fa\xc3\xa7on suivante. Tout d\xe2\x80\x99abord, il r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa8re la liste des URLs r\xc3\xa9cemment modifi\xc3\xa9es par des utilisateurs agr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9s. Il regroupe ensuite les adresses en paquet de dix et ouvre un nombre \xc3\xa9quivalent de connexions HTTP pour r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9rer les donn\xc3\xa9es relatives aux pages. Pour ouvrir des connexions en parall\xc3\xa8le nous cr\xc3\xa9ons plusieurs "threads" qui s\'ex\xc3\xa9cutent de mani\xc3\xa8re concurrente. La raison qui nous a pouss\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 choisir cette approche parall\xc3\xa9lis\xc3\xa9e est que l\'obtention des donn\xc3\xa9es demande un temps beaucoup plus \xc3\xa9lev\xc3\xa9 que leur traitement. Il est donc judicieux de chercher \xc3\xa0 en minimiser l\'impact.  Une fois les donn\xc3\xa9es HTML acquises, le bot les analyse s\xc3\xa9quentiellement dans le but d\'y trouver de potentiels concepts int\xc3\xa9ressants. Comme mentionn\xc3\xa9 pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9demment, le temps requis par ce traitement s\xc3\xa9quentiel des donn\xc3\xa9es est n\xc3\xa9gligeable par rapport au temps n\xc3\xa9cessaire pour les obtenir. L\'analyse des donn\xc3\xa9es consiste \xc3\xa0 trouver des correspondances entre des "regular expressions" (abr\xc3\xa9g\xc3\xa9es en \'regex\') python et des sous parties du texte. L\'utilisation des regex nous permet d\'obtenir une certaine marge de tol\xc3\xa9rance vis-\xc3\xa0-vis des entr\xc3\xa9es mal format\xc3\xa9es par les utilisateurs. En effet, il est possible d\'obtenir des correspondances m\xc3\xaame lorsque des caract\xc3\xa8res de formatages tels que ceux utilis\xc3\xa9s pour les dates: (.-/) sont manquants ou mal plac\xc3\xa9s.  Il est important de noter qu\'\xc3\xa0 ce stade il n\'existe pas de lien trivial entre les cha\xc3\xaenes de caract\xc3\xa8res extraites du wiki et les objets utilis\xc3\xa9s par le moteur d\'inf\xc3\xa9rence. Afin de d\xc3\xa9coupler le r\xc3\xa9sultat du scraping du fonctionnement du reste du programme, le scraper instancie des objets (au sens de la programmation orient\xc3\xa9e-objet) correspondants au concepts recherch\xc3\xa9s. Ces objets servent d\'abstraction pour le moteur d\'inf\xc3\xa9rence qui peut alors traiter les donn\xc3\xa9es sans se soucier de leur format sous-jacent. Lorsque l\'algorithme de scraping prend fin, nous obtenons un objet, appel\xc3\xa9 WikiPage, regroupant l\'ensemble des concepts extraits pour une page donn\xc3\xa9e. Une s\xc3\xa9rie de WikiPages sont ensuite li\xc3\xa9s par une nouvelle structure, appel\xc3\xa9e WikiData, qui repr\xc3\xa9sente l\'ensemble de tous les concepts extraits de toutes les pages visit\xc3\xa9es. Finalement, puisque le moteur d\'inf\xc3\xa9rence n\'est pas directement d\xc3\xa9pendant du processus d\'obtention des donn\xc3\xa9es, il est facile d\'\xc3\xa9tendre l\'ensemble des concepts \xc3\xa0 extraire. Cela se fait en d\xc3\xa9finissant de nouvelles regex ainsi que des structures de donn\xc3\xa9es ad\xc3\xa9quates pour accueillir les informations obtenues du wiki. Nous remplissons ainsi les objectifs fix\xc3\xa9s pour la r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9ration des donn\xc3\xa9es.  Le moteur d\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence Ici, il s\xe2\x80\x99agit d\xe2\x80\x99obtenir des faits \xc3\xa0 partir d\xe2\x80\x99autres faits et r\xc3\xa8gles. Nous avons utilis\xc3\xa9 un algorithme d\xe2\x80\x99intelligence artificielle appel\xc3\xa9 \xe2\x80\x9ccha\xc3\xaenage avant\xe2\x80\x9d, qui nous permet d\xe2\x80\x99effectuer ces d\xc3\xa9ductions. L\xe2\x80\x99algorithme a la forme suivante\xc2\xa0:         Q = faits existants       Solutions = liste vide       R\xc3\xa8gles = r\xc3\xa8gles existantes        tant que Q n\xe2\x80\x99est pas vide:             fait = premier \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ment de Q              si fait n\xe2\x80\x99est pas dans Solutions:                 ajouter fait \xc3\xa0 Solutions                  # V\xc3\xa9rifie si des r\xc3\xa8gles sont d\xc3\xa9clench\xc3\xa9es par le nouveau fait.                 pour chaque r\xc3\xa8gle dans R\xc3\xa8gles:                     si le fait satisfait une des conditions de r\xc3\xa8gle,                      et que l\xe2\x80\x99ensemble des faits d\xc3\xa9duits (Solutions)                      peut satisfaire l\xe2\x80\x99ensemble des autres conditions de cette m\xc3\xaame r\xc3\xa8gle:                         ajouter la conclusion de la r\xc3\xa8gle \xc3\xa0 Q      renvoyer Solutions  Cet algorithme utilise plusieurs \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ments de base\xc2\xa0: Les faits, qui sont des \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ments basique dans notre algorithme, et qui peuvent contenir des variables. Des exemple de faits seraient\xc2\xa0: p\xc3\xa8re(Paul, Pierre) ou oncle(?A, Jean) avec\xc2\xa0?A une variable. Les r\xc3\xa8gles, qui suivent la logique des pr\xc3\xa9dicats, et doivent appartenir \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99ensemble des clauses de Horn. Cet ensemble correspond \xc3\xa0 tout pr\xc3\xa9dicat sous la forme d\xe2\x80\x99une disjonction de litt\xc3\xa9raux qui sont tous n\xc3\xa9gatifs, sauf au plus un des litt\xc3\xa9raux qui peut \xc3\xaatre positifs. Cela nous permet d\xe2\x80\x99avoir des r\xc3\xa8gles de la forme not(A) or not(B) or \xe2\x80\xa6 or Z, ce qui peut \xc3\xaatre r\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9crit sous la forme (A et B et \xe2\x80\xa6) => Z. Nous commen\xc3\xa7ons donc \xc3\xa0 comprendre comment et pourquoi nous pouvons ajouter la conclusion de la r\xc3\xa8gle (notre Z) \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99ensemble des faits d\xc3\xa9duits, si l\xe2\x80\x99ensemble des conditions de cette r\xc3\xa8gle (A, B, \xe2\x80\xa6) sont satisfaites. De plus, comme des variables sont impliqu\xc3\xa9es dans nos r\xc3\xa8gles (en effet, nous ne savons pas \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99avance pour qui/quoi ces r\xc3\xa8gles s\xe2\x80\x99appliqueront), nous devons utiliser un algorithme d\xe2\x80\x99unification, qui va pouvoir mettre ensemble deux faits qui peuvent \xc3\xaatre unifi\xc3\xa9s, \xc3\xa0 la mani\xc3\xa8re d\xe2\x80\x99une reconnaissance de motif (pattern matching), et renvoyer l\xe2\x80\x99association des variables identifi\xc3\xa9es comme d\xc3\xa9finies.  La g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ration de Graphe de parent\xc3\xa9 La g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ration des graphes de parent\xc3\xa9 se fait avec 2 types de pr\xc3\xa9dicats:   Les Mariages ( Mariage de X et Y)  Les Parents ( La m\xc3\xa8re de Secundinus Aurelianus est Laelia Eumenius) Ainsi on peut g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rer des arbres g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9alogiques qui seront inscrits dans les discussions de chaque personne concern\xc3\xa9e. On peut constater qu\xe2\x80\x99un moteur d\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence n\xe2\x80\x99est pas n\xc3\xa9cessaire pour g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rer les graphes.  Les graphes sont g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9s \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99aide d\xe2\x80\x99une biblioth\xc3\xa8que GraphViz et d\xe2\x80\x99un standard de repr\xc3\xa9sentation des graphes, le langage DOT.  Le wiki writer Cette \xc3\xa9tape nous permet de directement \xc3\xa9crire sur le wiki les informations utiles obtenues. Etant donn\xc3\xa9 qu\xe2\x80\x99un grand nombre de faits sont d\xc3\xa9duits, m\xc3\xaame des faits interm\xc3\xa9diaires sans doutes inutiles, il faut pouvoir trier ce qui est obtenu. Ainsi, nous disons que par d\xc3\xa9faut, aucun fait n\xe2\x80\x99est \xc3\xa9crit, sauf certains sp\xc3\xa9cifi\xc3\xa9s. C\xe2\x80\x99est pour cette raison que nous ne retrouvons en sortie que les faits Erreur de date, Erreur de recontre, Erreur d\xe2\x80\x99\xc3\xa9lection\xe2\x80\xa6 Par la suite, \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9 que nous obtenons des informations utiles, mais pas tr\xc3\xa8s lisibles, il faut passer par une \xc3\xa9tape de transcription de l\xe2\x80\x99erreur brute vers une erreur plus compr\xc3\xa9hensible pour la personne/le bot qui se chargera de modifier la page par la suite. Nous avions choisi d\xe2\x80\x99\xc3\xa9crire directement dans la page InferenceBot - Output. Cependant, apr\xc3\xa8s la discussion du mardi 2 mai, utiliser la page discussions nous a sembl\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xaatre une bonne id\xc3\xa9e, \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9 que notre bot serait plus utile si il avertissait directement les personnes concern\xc3\xa9es, plut\xc3\xb4t que de les obliger \xc3\xa0 venir voir la page contenant toutes les erreurs du wiki, afin de voir s\'ils ont des probl\xc3\xa8mes dans leurs pages. C\'est pour cette raison que nous \xc3\xa9crivons dans cette page, en suivant le format suivant\xc2\xa0:   == InferenceBot == * fait 1 * fait 2 ... * fait N ----  Tout ce qui pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa8de et tout ce qui suit cette section est conserv\xc3\xa9. De plus, si la section n\'existe pas dans la page de discussion, le bot va la cr\xc3\xa9er (en conservant encore le reste du contenu) \xc3\xa0 la page discussion. De plus, \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9 que nous cr\xc3\xa9ons les arbres g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9alogiques de personnes du wiki, il nous faut \xc3\xa9crire ces images sur le wiki. De m\xc3\xaame que pour les faits inf\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9s, nous \xc3\xa9crivons dans une section sp\xc3\xa9ciale de la page discussion de la personne. Cette section s\'appelle InferenceBotPicture, et contient toutes les images d\'arbres g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9alogiques contenus dans la page (par exemple, pour la page mariage, il peut y en avoir plusieurs).  Afin de faire cette \xc3\xa9criture, il nous faut importer premi\xc3\xa8rement l\'image dans le wiki sous le nom Fichier:*nom_de_l\'image*, puis mettre un lien de la forme [[Fichier:*nom_de_l\'image*]] dans chacune des pages l\'utilisant. Pour g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rer le nom de l\'image, nous utilisons une m\xc3\xa9thode de hash des noms des personnes contenues dans cet arbre g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9alogique. Ceci fonctionne bien, mais a la f\xc3\xa2cheuse tendance d\'\xc3\xa9crire beaucoup d\'images diff\xc3\xa9rentes sur le site (ralentissant le bot), et de r\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9crire plusieurs fois les m\xc3\xaames images entre les diff\xc3\xa9rents lancements du bot. De plus, comme nous n\'avons pas de pouvoir de suppression d\'images, il ne nous est pas possible de supprimer les nombreuses pages cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es quand les images ne sont plus utilis\xc3\xa9es. Exemple d\xe2\x80\x99Output Nous avons cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9 plusieurs pages de test afin de v\xc3\xa9rifier le comportement de notre bot. Les pages sont Secundinus_Aurelianus, Pompilius_Iuvenalis et Laurentinus_Porcius. <br/> Nous avons directement pu obtenir les informations suivantes sur les pages Discussion:Secundinus_Aurelianus, Discussion:Pompilius_Iuvenalis et Discussion:Laurentinus_Porcius. <br/>   <br/> Ainsi, comme nous pouvons le voir sur cet exemple provenant de la page Discussion:Secundinus_Aurelianus, le bot d\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence a pu d\xc3\xa9duire plusieurs erreurs, comme une erreur de naissance (qui devrait se d\xc3\xa9rouler avant la mort, pas comme ici); une erreur de rencontre, o\xc3\xb9 deux personnes se sont rencontr\xc3\xa9es en m\xc3\xaame temps \xc3\xa0 deux endroits diff\xc3\xa9rents; ainsi que plusieurs dates de mort.  Autonomie Pour rendre le programme autonome nous avons impl\xc3\xa9ment\xc3\xa9 une interface en ligne de commande simpliste. Cette interface permet \xc3\xa0 l\'utilisateur de contr\xc3\xb4ler l\'ex\xc3\xa9cution du bot et d\'obtenir un feedback pr\xc3\xa9cieux sur les t\xc3\xa2ches en cours d\'ex\xc3\xa9cution. Les commandes \xc3\xa0 disposition sont les suivantes:   autorun: programme le bot pour ex\xc3\xa9cuter une passe de scraping, d\'inf\xc3\xa9rence et d\'\xc3\xa9criture toutes les heures. \xc3\x89quivalent \xc3\xa0 l\'ex\xc3\xa9cution successive des commandes scrape / infer / clean.   scrape: lance une passe de scraping.   infer: lance le moteur d\'inf\xc3\xa9rence. Doit \xc3\xaatre ex\xc3\xa9cut\xc3\xa9 apr\xc3\xa8s la commande scrape. Cette commande se charge \xc3\xa9galement d\'\xc3\xa9crire les r\xc3\xa9sultats obtenus sur le wiki.  clean: supprime les donn\xc3\xa9es obtenues du wiki. Utile pour lancer une nouvelle passe de scraping.  stop: suspend l\'ex\xc3\xa9cution du bot apr\xc3\xa8s qu\'il ait termin\xc3\xa9 la t\xc3\xa2che en cours.  shutdown: arr\xc3\xaate l\'ex\xc3\xa9cution du bot et termine le programme. Les commandes autorun et scrape peuvent prendre un argument num\xc3\xa9rique qui doit \xc3\xaatre pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9 du code \'--days\' permettant de sp\xc3\xa9cifier le nombre de jours \xc3\xa0 consid\xc3\xa9rer durant le scraping. La sortie de la console durant le traitement des donn\xc3\xa9es est illustr\xc3\xa9e ci-dessous: <br/>  <br/>  \xc3\x89valuation des performances Actuellement, les r\xc3\xa8gles du bot d\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence se focalisent principalement sur des erreurs de contenu (incoh\xc3\xa9rences dans les dates ou des lieux p.ex.). Sachant que les pages pertinentes du wikipast (donc pas celles cr\xc3\xa9es par des attaques de bots) ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es m\xc3\xa9ticuleusement par un \xc3\xa9tudiant, il est rare qu\xe2\x80\x99elle contiennent de telles erreurs. C\xe2\x80\x99est pourquoi le bot ne g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa8re pas beaucoup d\xe2\x80\x99erreurs autres que celles provoqu\xc3\xa9es par les pages de test. Cependant, nous pensons qu\xe2\x80\x99il est utile d\xe2\x80\x99avoir un tel bot lorsque le nombre de pages augmente et lorsque des utilisateurs et bots commencent \xc3\xa0 modifier les pages des autres utilisateurs. En effet, il est beaucoup plus facile de faire des erreurs en modifiant les pages d\xe2\x80\x99autres utilisateurs. Le nombre de faits et d\'erreurs inf\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9s d\xc3\xa9pend aussi du nombre de r\xc3\xa8gles impl\xc3\xa9ment\xc3\xa9es. Comme indiqu\xc3\xa9 dans la description du bot, il est facile d\xe2\x80\x99ajouter des r\xc3\xa8gles gr\xc3\xa2ce \xc3\xa0 la modularit\xc3\xa9 de son impl\xc3\xa9mentation. Une des limites de notre bot est le nombre de r\xc3\xa8gles que le responsable du bot doit cr\xc3\xa9er si il veut obtenir des conclusions int\xc3\xa9ressantes. Cette structure bas\xc3\xa9e sur les r\xc3\xa8gles est aussi un point faible. En effet, le bot construit des pr\xc3\xa9dicats seulement lorsque l\'entr\xc3\xa9e du wiki correspond \xc3\xa0 un format particulier (ordre des mots par exemple). Le manque de structure de certains types d\'entr\xc3\xa9es rend parfois impossible la cr\xc3\xa9ation de r\xc3\xa8gle d\'inf\xc3\xa9rence. Concernant le temps n\xc3\xa9cessaire \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence des faits/erreurs par le bot, il faut savoir que la puissance et le nombre de connexions de l\xe2\x80\x99ordinateur/serveur utilis\xc3\xa9 sont des facteurs importants. Le bot, lorsqu\xe2\x80\x99il est ex\xc3\xa9cut\xc3\xa9 sur un ordinateur portable, prend actuellement quelques minutes pour scraper tout le Wikipast et inf\xc3\xa9rer les faits/erreurs. Nous avons impl\xc3\xa9ment\xc3\xa9 l\xe2\x80\x99utilisation de multiples connexions (r\xc3\xa9glable simplement) pour scraper plus rapidement, car il s\xe2\x80\x99agit d\'une partie prenant une grosse partie du temps total d\xe2\x80\x99ex\xc3\xa9cution (autour de 100 secondes en conditions r\xc3\xa9elles). L\xe2\x80\x99inf\xc3\xa9rence des faits/erreurs \xc3\xa9tait peu co\xc3\xbbteuse lorsque nous avions peu de r\xc3\xa8gles et de faits, cependant \xc3\xa0 force d\'ajouter un grand nombre de faits, par exemple pour d\xc3\xa9tecter que deux lieux ou deux dates sont diff\xc3\xa9rentes, \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9 que le temps d\xe2\x80\x99ex\xc3\xa9cution est polynomial selon le nombre d\'entr\xc3\xa9es, nous avons remarqu\xc3\xa9 un certain ralentissement lors des derniers tests, \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9 le grand nombre de faits \xc3\xa0 traiter et les nouvelles r\xc3\xa8gles ajout\xc3\xa9es au projet. Le temps d\'\xc3\xa9criture est aussi non n\xc3\xa9gligeable \xc3\xa0 l\'heure actuelle, puisqu\'il n\'a pas \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 parall\xc3\xa9lis\xc3\xa9, et ne profite pas (encore) d\'optimisations afin d\'\xc3\xa9viter une lecture co\xc3\xbbteuse de la page. R\xc3\xa9cemment, nous nous sommes heurt\xc3\xa9 au probl\xc3\xa8me suivant\xc2\xa0: maintenant que nous g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rons des arbres g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9alogiques et que nous avons des erreurs qui peuvent impliquer plus d\'une page, et que nous r\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9crivons sur ce qui avait \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa9crit auparavant dans la section discussions, il nous faut scraper toutes les pages. Si ce n\'\xc3\xa9tait pas le cas, il pourrait y avoir des faits existants qui ne seraient pas visibles \xc3\xa9tant donn\xc3\xa9 que nous ne prendrions que les faits provenant de pages r\xc3\xa9cemment modifi\xc3\xa9es. Ainsi, les images et les faits ne seraient pas tout \xc3\xa0 fait justes, ce qui n\'est pas acceptable. Nous avons trouv\xc3\xa9 que notre bot avait des conflits, surtout avec le bot TangoBot. Les pages de test de notre bot ont des entr\xc3\xa9es qui se ressemblent \xc3\xa0 la date ou au lieu pr\xc3\xa8s, car nous testons diff\xc3\xa9rentes r\xc3\xa8gles qui se concentrent sur les dates, lieux et personnes. TangoBot supprime ce qu\'il consid\xc3\xa8re \xc3\xaatre trop ressemblant et r\xc3\xa9duit consid\xc3\xa9rablement nos pages de test. InferenceBot BioPathBot     \t0'

b'Being in the self-defense trade, I\'m always all for what does and would not work with regards to you and me defending ourselves in opposition to crime. Today we\'re going to speak about personal alarms; what they\'re, what they do, and are they really an efficient form of defense against crime.<br/><br/>First, what they are. Personal alarms are usually small, battery-operated gadgets that make a variety of noise. Their small dimension makes them straightforward to carry in your individual, hence the name "Personal Alarm". I do know, I do know, that sounds pretty apparent to most of us, however I had to start with a fundamental description just in case anybody out there may be model new to this sort of thing.<br/><br/>Subsequent, what they do. Nicely, like I stated, personal alarms make numerous noise. That\'s exactly what they\'re speculated to do and so long as they\'re working correctly, that is exactly what they do. The typical personal alarm has a noise ranking of wherever between 100 decibels and one hundred thirty decibels. To put that into perspective consider this,<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 A house vacuum cleaner is around 65 to 70 decibels loud<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 An average alarm clock is around eighty decibels loud<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 A chainsaw is around one hundred decibels loud<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 A jackhammer is around a hundred thirty decibels loud<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 And a gun or an air raid siren is someplace round one hundred forty decibels loud<br/><br/>Sounds louder than ninety decibels are considered doubtlessly harmful to someone\'s hearing. Both the quantity of noise and the length of publicity decide the quantity of damage.<br/><br/>Most personal alarms are activated by both a push button, an on-off switch, or a pull-out pin that activates the alarm when the pin is faraway from the device.<br/><br/>I personally choose those with the pull-out pin, because if the alarm is dropped throughout a wrestle, it won\'t unintentionally flip off. In actual fact, the one solution to shut it off (in need of smashing it to items) is to  alarma para piso interchange the activation pin or remove the batteries.<br/><br/>Finally, are they effective? Yes they\'re effective but it surely all is dependent upon what you count on them to do for you. Personal alarms work because they emit a loud, high-pitched frequency, which is much more irritating to the ears than a low pitch frequency of the same volume.<br/><br/>The screeching or sometimes siren like sounds that these alarms give off can quickly disorient an attacker for a number of seconds, and they also can cause some pain to the eardrum, even if the particular person is not usually sensitive to loud noises.<br/><br/>However, probably the most useful use of those personal alarms, as I see it, is their capability to attract attention to your situation. Most criminals don\'t desire an audience after they assault somebody, and a a hundred thirty-decibel alarm can be heard from as far-off as two or three metropolis blocks, even with the sound of shifting site visitors on the street. To allow them to simply draw the eye of anyone close by while you\'re strolling by a car parking zone or down the road, or even jogging via the park. This alone can typically ship your attacker running off within the different direction seeking less noisy prey.<br/><br/>Personal alarms solely value a couple of dollars, which makes them very straightforward to own. Also they are not weapons so they are authorized to hold everywhere. But please remember, that like all self-defense tool, a personal alarm just isn\'t magic. Regardless of how loud your alarm is, it doesn\'t put up some form of magical power subject that may shield you from all bad individuals in the world. They\'ll nonetheless, catch most individuals by surprise and disorient them lengthy sufficient to present you a chance to get away. And they will additionally entice attention to your state of affairs even should you aren\'t able to scream for help.     \t1'

Steve Gray, a University of Michigan law professor who leads a law clinic aimed at helping folks navigate unemployment law. MiDAS processed about 1.4 million claims since 2013; it has established 46,638 fraud cases since then, unemployment agency spokesman Ken Silfven wrote in an e-mail. Of those, Silfven said, 60% of the fraud determinations were "at least partially affirmed." This, the state seems to view as positive. b'Overview<br/>Arch pain (usually Plantar Fasciitis) is pain that is usually felt first thing in the morning or after rising up from a prolonged resting position and pain increases after more use of feet. The causes of arch pain include: weight, a foot injury, overuse, abnormal biomechanics of the foot (e.g. flat feet or abnormal pronation), footwear, certain activities, inappropriate training, and medical conditions (eg. rheumatoid arthritis). Treatment of arch pain include weight reduction, rest, ice, activity modification, anti-inflammatory products, sports massage, stretching, strengthening, acupuncture, strapping, steroid injection, ultrasound and orthotics.<br/><br/><br/>Causes<br/>In most cases, plantar fasciitis develops without a specific, identifiable reason. There are, however, many factors that can make you more prone to the condition. Tighter calf muscles that make it difficult to flex your foot and bring your toes up toward your shin. Obesity. Very high arch. Repetitive impact activity (running/sports). New or increased activity.Although many people with plantar fasciitis have heel spurs, spurs are not the cause of plantar fasciitis pain. One out of 10 people has heel spurs, but only 1 out of 20 people (5%) with heel spurs has foot pain. Because the spur is not the cause of plantar fasciitis, the pain can be treated without removing the spur.<br/><br/>Symptoms<br/>Intense heel pain, especially first thing in the morning and after a long day. Difficulty walking or standing for long periods without pain. Generally, the sharp pain associated with plantar fasciitis is localized to the heel, but it can spread forward along the arch of the foot and back into the Achilles tendon. While severe cases can result in chronic pain that lasts all day, the most common flare ups occur first thing in the morning, making those first steps out of bed a form of torture, and in the evening after having spent a day on your feet. Overpronation (a foot that naturally turns too far inward), high arches, and flat feet (fallen arches) can all cause similar arch pain. In these cases, however, the pain is more likely to continue throughout the day rather than being worst in the morning.<br/><br/>Diagnosis<br/>The adult acquired flatfoot, secondary to posterior tibial tendon dysfunction, is diagnosed in a number of ways with no single test proven to be totally reliable. The most accurate diagnosis is made by a skilled clinician utilizing observation and hands on evaluation of the foot and ankle. Observation of the foot in a walking examination is most reliable. The affected foot appears more pronated and deformed compared to the unaffected foot. Muscle testing will show a strength deficit. An easy test to perform in the office is the single foot raise.<br/><br/>Non Surgical Treatment<br/>Tight arches, overpronation and flat feet as well as tight calves all lead to inflammation of the connective tissue that forms this arch of your foot. This condition, plantar fasciitis, can be very painful, from your first step in the morning. Fortunately, treatment is easier than most. No operations, no fancy pulsed waves, no night splints necessary. Good arch supports? full length flexible (not hard) orthotics are key. Stretches of the calf relieve arch tightness as the heel bone acts like a fulcrum pulling back the arch tissues if too tight. Regularly perform the gastroc and soleus stretches that you learned at the gym. If lazy, buy "Pro-Stretch" on line which helps you stretch your calves easily. Use it often. You can\'t stretch too often, only too little. Finally, the magic cure is to roll a golf ball under the arch for half-hour once a day. (I know; a half-hour is a long time to perform one exercise, but that\'s what it takes. Once you master this exercise, it is easy to do while you work at your desk or are watching a half hour TV program.) This may hurt the first week. Keep going because by week two, after you go over the pain hump, the pain will be gone.<br/><br/><br/>Surgical Treatment<br/>As with most surgeries, patients and physicians should consider the surgery only after other, less invasive treatments have proven unproductive. Indications for surgery include Pain. Inability to function. Failure to improve after a six-month course of specific, directed physical therapy. Failure to improve after using arch supports, orthotics, or ankle and foot bracing. Once patients are at that point, the good news is that the procedure has considerably better outcomes than more traditional flat foot surgery. In the past, surgeons would realign and fuse the three hind joints, which would cause patients to lose motion, leaving them with a significantly stiff hind foot, With these newer procedures, if the foot is still flexible, surgeons can realign it and usually restore a close-to-normal or functional range of motion in the joints.<br/><br/><br/>Prevention<br/>There are several things you can do to prevent pain on the bottom of the foot. Here are some tips to help you avoid this condition. Do simple stretches each day (See Plantar Fasciitis Exercises for a list of all exercises). Wear good shoes that fit properly and are appropriate for the activity you are participating in. Lose excess weight if possible. Build your stamina slowly, especially with new exercises. Rest and elevate your feet, whenever possible, keeping them at least twelve inches above your heart. Always follow your doctor?s instructions for treatment. Each day do a different activity. For example: one day ride your bike, and swim the next day.     \t1'

La notation de d\xc3\xa9part s'effectue sur une note de 6.0, \xc3\xa0 laquelle on retire des malus. La pr\xc3\xa9sentation et la syntaxe Wiki ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 respect\xc3\xa9e (0.5) Le bot v\xc3\xa9rifie les aspects de syntaxe wiki suivants\xc2\xa0:    La pr\xc3\xa9sence d'une ast\xc3\xa9risque en d\xc3\xa9but de ligne   La pr\xc3\xa9sence d'une (ou plusieurs) date(s)  Une syntaxe avec  \xe2\x80\x9c/\xe2\x80\x9d apr\xc3\xa8s la date et \xe2\x80\x9c.\xe2\x80\x9d avant la description.   La note de z\xc3\xa9ro (0.5 de malus)  est attribu\xc3\xa9e si au moins deux crit\xc3\xa8re non respect\xc3\xa9s, un malus de 0.25 est donn\xc3\xa9 par crit\xc3\xa8re manquant.   Toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es sont sourc\xc3\xa9es avec au moins un article (0.5)  Le bot regarde toutes les lignes, s\xe2\x80\x99il manque une source \xc3\xa0 au moins une ligne, le bot attribue un malus de 0.5  Le codage utilisant des hypermots est satisfaisant (0.5) Le but v\xc3\xa9rifie la syntaxe des hypermots , et se les hypermots sont pr\xc3\xa9sents de fa\xc3\xa7on suffisante ( Plus que 10)  Le malus est de 0 ou 0.5.   Au moins cinq pages li\xc3\xa9es ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es ou mises \xc3\xa0 jour (0.5) Le bot recherche de la ligne sur les pages li\xc3\xa9es en scanant  toutes les entr\xc3\xa9s, et v\xc3\xa9rifie que le nombre de pages li\xc3\xa9es est suffisant.  Le malus est de 0 ou 0.5.  <br/>  Performances Les performance de ce bot sont correctes, il distribue un feedback constructif sur la page. b"Despite having totally different origins, many people at this time consider talismans and amulets to be synonymous to 1 another. The most common differentiation is that amulets are said to ward off undesirable influences, while talismans are stated to attract specifically energies. This distinction will not be in any formal definition, but nonetheless routinely recognized. For the sake of simplicity, the terms amulets and talismans will probably be used interchangeably throughout this article.<br/><br/>Amulets and talismans have been part of the historical past of people, for as long as there have been stories and tales. From historical Egyptians to Romans to Medieval occasions, symbolic trinkets have been utilized by the commonest of folk to the highest monarchy. Kings and queens would have trusted confidants create small tokens they may preserve in the secret folds of their robes and peasants would see the village witch and purchase bundled herbs or woven twigs to hold above their door or to put below their pillows. Indeed, the historical past of amulets is rich and varied.<br/><br/>Nowadays many people still put on amulets and talismans, although they might not realize the thought behind their jewelry. Consider the religious Christian who wears a cross around their neck - this could imply many things, symbolizing the life and demise of their saviour, eternal life after death, or it might probably even serve as a reminder of the golden rule, do unto others as thou would have carried out unto you. It is important to understand that while some symbols have common meanings, many symbols may also carry a private, personal reminder. The energy in the that means of an amulet or talisman relies on the faith of the particular person utilizing it.<br/><br/>When making an attempt to determine the that means behind an amulet or talisman, consider all of its factors. What shape is it? What colour is it? Is there a treasured gemstone or crystal in it? Are there herbs or pure components encased in it? By combining several factors, akin to color, material and form, it's possible to customize the meaning behind a talisman. Amulets will be bought in nearly any jewellery store, nonetheless they can be made and customised just as easily. Though on no account an entire listing, consider the parts beneath in case you are trying to find an amulet or talisman that is proper for you.<br/><br/>Colours<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Red: Red symbolises passion, courage, energy, good health and powerful emotions. This color can be utilized when making an attempt to overcome the concern you could have of a state of affairs or person. It additionally promotes the ability to be robust and confident in your convictions and encourages therapeutic for good health.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Pink: This colour universally stands for love, but additionally represents friendship and beauty. When attempting to improve a relationship, whether or not it is romantic or not, pink is the appropriate colour to choose.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Orange: Orange is used to increase personal energy or to attract energy from the world round you. It's stimulating and is claimed to assist enhance the ability to concentrate and think clearly.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Yellow: This color represents mind, communication, and clear thinking. It's generally used to help with persuasion or public speaking. Yellow can also be a color of pleasure and happiness, and is subsequently used to ward off depression and anxiety.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Green: Green is mostly related to prosperity and wealth. It isn't limited to monetary prosperity, nonetheless, because it also promotes healing and fertility. Girls who're having bother conceiving will usually flip to this colour.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Blue: Blue has  sides, light and dark. Just like water can be calm and still or violent and aggressive, so can this colour. In lighter shades it represents therapeutic, peace, calmness,  taweez and happiness. In darker shades blue focuses more on impulsive action, moving forward, and change.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Purple: Once considered a royal colour, purple now most strongly represents spirituality and psychic ability. If you are having hassle focusing and calming your thoughts, purple aids in meditation and is used to strengthen your will power.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 White: White is a pure color, symbolising safety, sincerity, truth, and optimism. White is considered to be essentially the most highly effective selection in any state of affairs, because it represents and incorporates all colors and subsequently can tackle all elements and characteristics.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Black: Black has been promoted as an evil color throughout the media, but that might not be more faraway from the truth. Instead, this color is said to banish negativity and to encourage change.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Brown: Brown is a natural color, and is associated with being grounded, discovering your roots, animals, and order in your life.<br/><br/>Gems<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Amethyst: Recognized for it's protecting powers, amethyst is likely one of the mostly used gemstones. It's stated to focus not only on safety, but to help with meditation, serenity, and peace.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Citrine: Citrine is used when an individual requires balance in their life and is in want of energy and creativity.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Garnet: Considered to be energising, garnets can help with health, love, and devotion.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Jade: A soothing stone, jade is used for turning into more balanced and grounded.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Quartz: Quartz is usually related to energy, protection, and meditation and non secular progression.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Tiger's Eye: This is a very talked-about option for the trendy day individual, as tiger's eye is said to assist organize a cluttered, scattered mind, helping an individual to think more clearly, focus, and stay calm.<br/><br/>Symbols<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Ankh: A preferred Egyptian symbol, the ankh represents life and immortality.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Circle: Having no clear ending or starting, the circle represents eternity. It's also used for the pure cycle of life, femininity, and as a logo of the Goddess.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 4 leaf clover: If you're acquainted with any image, it's probably the 4 leaf clover. Representing good luck and fortune, the four leaf clover is a popular jewelry charm.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Hand of Fatima: A Muslim symbol, the hand of Fatima is claimed to ward towards the evil eye and negative energy in general. This symbol is depicted as a hand with an eye on its palm.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Moon: Mystical and magical, the Moon typically represents femininity, knowledge and intuition.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Pentacle: A five pointed star, the pentacle stands for the 4 elements plus the addition of God, Goddess, Spirit, or whatever higher Power its proprietor believes in. It's also typically used to banish negative energy and to ward off evil.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Sun: The Sun is alleged to be the bringer of prosperity, health, and hope. Additionally it is the male counterpart to the moon's feminine energy.<br/><br/>\xc2\xb7 Tao: Also called yin/yang, this ancient Chinese symbol depicts unity, equilibrium, and common harmony.     \t1"

b"Overview<br/>Achilles tendonitis is inflammation of the tendon, usually resulting from overuse associated with a change in playing surface, footwear or intensity of an activity. The Achilles tendon is surrounded by a connective tissue sheath (paratenon, or 'paratendon'), rather than a true synovial sheath. The paratenon stretches with movement, allowing maximum gliding action. Near the insertion of the tendon are two bursae - the subcutaneous calcaneal and the retrocalcaneal bursae.<br/><br/>Causes<br/>Unusual use or overuse of the lower leg muscles and Achilles tendon is usually the cause of Achilles tendinitis. Repetitive jumping, kicking, and sprinting can lead to Achilles tendinitis in both recreational and competitive athletes. Runners, dancers, and athletes over age 65 are especially at risk. Sudden increases in training or competition can also inflame your Achilles tendon. For example, adding hills, stair-climbing, or sprinting to your running workout puts extra stress on your Achilles tendon. Improper technique during training can also strain the tendon. Intense running or jumping without stretching and strengthening your lower leg muscles can put you at risk regardless of your age or fitness level. Running on tight, exhausted, or fatigued calf muscles can put added stress on your Achilles tendon, as your tendon may not be ready to quickly start a workout after a period of inactivity. Direct blows or other injuries to the ankle, foot, or lower leg may pull your Achilles tendon too far and stretch the tissue. A hard contraction of the calf muscles, such as can happen when you push for the final sprint in a race, can strain the tendon. People whose feet roll inward, a condition called overpronation, are particularly at risk. Sometimes, shoes with too much heel cushioning put extra strain on the Achilles tendon.<br/><br/>Symptoms<br/>People with Achilles tendinitis may experience pain during and after exercising. Running and jumping activities become painful and difficult. Symptoms include stiffness and pain in the back of the ankle when pushing off the ball of the foot. For patients with chronic tendinitis (longer than six weeks), x-rays may reveal calcification (hardening of the tissue) in the tendon. Chronic tendinitis can result in a breakdown of the tendon, or tendinosis, which weakens the tendon and may cause a rupture.<br/><br/>Diagnosis<br/>A podiatrist can usually make the diagnosis by clinical history and physical examination alone. Pain with touching or stretching the tendon is typical. There may also be a visible swelling to the tendon. The patient frequently has difficulty plantarflexing (pushing down the ball of the foot and toes, like one would press on a gas pedal), particularly against resistance. In most cases X-rays don't show much, as they tend to show bone more than soft tissues. But X-rays may show associated degeneration of the heel bone that is common with Achilles Tendon problems. For example, heel spurs, calcification within the tendon, avulsion fractures, periostitis (a bruising of the outer covering of the bone) may all be seen on X-ray. In cases where we are uncertain as to the extent of the damage to the tendon, though, an MRI scan may be necessary, which images the soft tissues better than X-rays. When the tendon is simply inflamed and not severely damaged, the problem may or may not be visible on MRI. It depends upon the severity of the condition.<br/><br/>Nonsurgical Treatment<br/>The main treatments for Achilles tendinitis do not involve surgery. It is important to remember that it may take at least 2 to 3 months for the pain to go away. Try putting ice over the Achilles tendon for 15 to 20 minutes, two to three times per day. Remove the ice if the area gets numb. Changes in activity may help manage the symptoms. Decrease or stop any activity that causes you pain. Run or walk on smoother and softer surfaces. Switch to biking, swimming, or other activities that put less stress on the Achilles tendon. Your health care provider or physical therapist can show you stretching exercises for the Achilles tendon. They may also suggest the following changes in your footwear, a brace or boot or cast to keep the heel and tendon still and allow the swelling to go down, heel lifts placed in the shoe under the heel, shoes that are softer in the areas over and under the heel cushion. Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) such as aspirin and ibuprofen can help with pain or swelling. Talk with your health care provider. If these treatments do not improve symptoms, you may need surgery to remove inflamed tissue and abnormal areas of the tendon. Surgery also can be used to remove the bone spur that is irritating the tendon. Extracorporeal shock wave therapy (ESWT) may be an alternative to surgery for people who have not responded to other treatments. This treatment uses low-dose sound waves.<br/><br/><br/><br/>Surgical Treatment<br/>Surgery should be considered to relieve Achilles tendinitis only if the pain does not improve after 6 months of nonsurgical treatment. The specific type of surgery depends on the location of the tendinitis and the amount of damage to the tendon. Gastrocnemius recession. This is a surgical lengthening of the calf (gastrocnemius) muscles. Because tight calf muscles place increased stress on the Achilles tendon, this procedure is useful for patients who still have difficulty flexing their feet, despite consistent stretching. In gastrocnemius recession, one of the two muscles that make up the calf is lengthened to increase the motion of the ankle. The procedure can be performed with a traditional, open incision or with a smaller incision and an endoscope-an instrument that contains a small camera. Your doctor will discuss the procedure that best meets your needs. Complication rates for gastrocnemius recession are low, but can include nerve damage. Gastrocnemius recession can be performed with or without d?bridement, which is removal of damaged tissue. D?bridement and repair (tendon has less than 50% damage). The goal of this operation is to remove the damaged part of the Achilles tendon. Once the unhealthy portion of the tendon has been removed, the remaining tendon is repaired with sutures, or stitches to complete the repair. In insertional tendinitis, the bone spur is also removed. Repair of the tendon in these instances may require the use of metal or plastic anchors to help hold the Achilles tendon to the heel bone, where it attaches. After d?bridement and repair, most patients are allowed to walk in a removable boot or cast within 2 weeks, although this period depends upon the amount of damage to the tendon. D?bridement with tendon transfer (tendon has greater than 50% damage). In cases where more than 50% of the Achilles tendon is not healthy and requires removal, the remaining portion of the tendon is not strong enough to function alone. To prevent the remaining tendon from rupturing with activity, an Achilles tendon transfer is performed. The tendon that helps the big toe point down is moved to the heel bone to add strength to the damaged tendon. Although this sounds severe, the big toe will still be able to move, and most patients will not notice a change in the way they walk or run. Depending on the extent of damage to the tendon, some patients may not be able to return to competitive sports or running. Recovery. Most patients have good results from surgery. The main factor in surgical recovery is the amount of damage to the tendon. The greater the amount of tendon involved, the longer the recovery period, and the less likely a patient will be able to return to sports activity. Physical therapy is an important part of recovery. Many patients require 12 months of rehabilitation before they are pain-free.<br/><br/>Prevention<br/>The following measures can significantly reduce the risk of developing Achilles tendonitis. Adequately stretch and warm up prior to exercise. Warm down and stretch after exercise. Choose footwear carefully and use footwear appropriate to the sport being undertaken. Use orthotic devices in footwear to correctly support the foot. Exercise within fitness levels and follow a sensible exercise programme. Develop strong, flexible calf muscles.     \t1"

b"1919.01.09 / ??: Trotsky accuse L\xc3\xa9nine d'\xc3\xaatre trop mod\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9, et le fait arr\xc3\xaater [1]. 1920.06.04 / Moscou: Une contre-r\xc3\xa9volution \xc3\xa9clate \xc3\xa0 Moscou, mettant L\xc3\xa9nine et Trotsky en fuite [2]. 1920.06.04 / Moscou: Une contre-r\xc3\xa9volution \xc3\xa9clate \xc3\xa0 Moscou, mettant L\xc3\xa9nine et Trotsky en fuite [3]. 1920.06.04 / Moscou: Une contre-r\xc3\xa9volution \xc3\xa9clate \xc3\xa0 Moscou, mettant L\xc3\xa9nine et Trotsky en fuite [4]. 1925.12 / [...] Trotsky \xc3\xa9cart\xc3\xa9 du gouvernement de l'URSS. [5] 1929.07.09 / [...]. Joseph Staline n\xc3\xa9gocie avec Trotsky. [6] 1929.07.18/ [...]. Trotsky publie une lettre contre Joseph Staline. b'Overview<br/>Painful progressive flatfoot, otherwise known as Tibialis Posterior Tendinitis, is caused by inflammation of the tendon of the tibialis posterior. The tendon then becomes inflamed, stretched or suffers a partial or total tear. If left untreated, this condition may lead to severe disability and chronic pain. Some people are predisposed to this condition if they have flatfeet or an abnormal attachment of the tendon to the bones in the midfoot. Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory medications, ice, physical therapy, supportive taping and bracing, or orthotic devices are the common ways of treating painful progressive flatfoot. Contact your physician before taking any medication. In some cases, a surgical operation may need to be performed to repair the torn or damaged tendon and restore normal function. To prevent reinjury, orthotic devices may be recommended. In severe cases, surgery on the midfoot bones may be necessary to treat the associated flatfoot condition.<br/><br/><br/>Causes<br/>In most cases, plantar fasciitis develops without a specific, identifiable reason. There are, however, many factors that can make you more prone to the condition. Tighter calf muscles that make it difficult to flex your foot and bring your toes up toward your shin. Obesity. Very high arch. Repetitive impact activity (running/sports). New or increased activity.Although many people with plantar fasciitis have heel spurs, spurs are not the cause of plantar fasciitis pain. One out of 10 people has heel spurs, but only 1 out of 20 people (5%) with heel spurs has foot pain. Because the spur is not the cause of plantar fasciitis, the pain can be treated without removing the spur.<br/><br/>Symptoms<br/>The groups of muscles that support the arch can be divided into two groups. The muscles on the top of the arch start on the front lower leg and help to lift the arch, and the muscles that help pull the arch on the bottom of the foot are located the on back of the lower leg. Muscle injury may be indicated when pain is felt when the foot is fully extended, flexed, or turned in or out. Pain may also be felt when working the foot against resistance. Bruises are the result of a direct-force injury to the body. A bruise can occur to the foot by a variety of causes, such as having your foot stepped on or by stepping on a rock. The tissues that compose the arch do not provide that area of the body much protection. Blows to the foot that result in pain, discoloration, swelling, and changes in how you walk may indicate more serious damage.<br/><br/>Diagnosis<br/>The doctor will examine your feet for foot flexibility and range of motion and feel for any tenderness or bony abnormalities. Depending on the results of this physical examination, foot X-rays may be recommended. X-rays are always performed in a young child with rigid flatfeet and in an adult with acquired flatfeet due to trauma.<br/><br/>Non Surgical Treatment<br/>Treatment for a high arch foot or Charcot Marie Tooth disorder depends on the extent of deformity and the amount of disability experienced by the patient. Depending upon the symptoms, treatment may include. Changing the shoes. Special orthotic supports (devices that support, adjust, or accommodate the foot deformity). Cushioning pads. Foot and ankle braces or surgery.<br/><br/><br/>Surgical Treatment<br/>Tendon transfers: Too much pull of certain muscles and tendons is often the cause of the deformity related with a cavus foot. Moving one of these muscles or tendons may help the foot work better. In addition, patients with a cavus foot may have weakness in moving the foot up, which is sometimes called a foot drop. In these cases, a tendon from the back of the ankle may be moved to the top of the foot to help improve strength. Correcting the deformity of the foot may not be possible with soft tissue procedures alone. In these instances, one or more bone cuts (osteotomies) may be needed. Instead of a bone cut, a fusion (arthrodesis) procedure may be used. A fusion removes the joint between two bones so they grow together over time. During a fusion the bones may be held in place with plates or screws. Calcaneal osteotomy: This procedure is performed to bring the heel bone back under the leg. This is needed if correction of the deformity in the front of the foot does not also correct the back of the foot or ankle. A calcaneal osteotomy can be performed several ways and is often held in place with one or more screws. Sometimes patients have a deformity that has caused damage to the joints. In these cases, soft tissue procedures or bone cuts may not be enough, and it may be necessary to eliminate the joint. Clawed toes are a common problem with cavus foot deformity. This can be treated with tendon surgery, fusion or removal of part of the toe bones. Following surgery the toes are often temporarily held in place with pins.<br/><br/><br/>Prevention<br/>So how do you prevent plantar fasciitis? Factors which can be controlled include training progression, environmental factors, shoes, and strength and flexibility exercises. A useful guideline for a safe training progression is\xc2\xa0?the 10% rule.? Limit increases in distance or intensity to 10% a week. For example, if a person is running 60 minutes at a session, 4 times a week, or 240 minutes, she or he can probably increase the running time to 264 minutes (240 + 10%), the following week if all else remains the same. Terrain is also an important factor in training. Running 30 minutes on hills is very different from running 30 minutes on flat surfaces in terms of the forces on the legs and feet. Work up gradually to increase your running time on hills. Also lean forward when running downhill. If you run on a banked or crowned surface, vary the direction you run in so you alternate which leg is higher and which leg is lower on the bank. If you know concrete or asphalt is causing you discomfort, try running on a cinder or composite track. If you are going on vacation and are not used to running on sand or grass, don?t spend your whole vacation doing it.<br/><br/>Stretching Exercises<br/>Point your toes. To ease foot pain and aching in your feet, lift one foot and roll it downward until the toes are pointed toward the ground. Then flex your foot. Repeat using the other foot. This exercise will help stretch out all the small muscles that are on the bottom of your feet, which can help relieve aching and improve blood circulation. Raise your heels. This exercise is good for relieving toe cramps caused by standing for hours in constricting shoes, says Kurtz. Bonus: It can also strengthen calf muscles and make them look more defined. Stand up and lift your heels so that you are standing on the balls of your feet. Hold for 10 seconds. Repeat 10 times. Squeeze your toes. To strengthen the toes and help alleviate foot pain from hammertoes (when a toe resembles a claw), separate your toes using corks or foam toe separators and then squeeze your toes together for five seconds. Repeat 10 times. Roll a ball. Want to create an instant massage for the bottom of your feet? Roll a golf ball or tennis ball under the ball of your foot. Apply light pressure for about two minutes. This exercise can be helpful for arch pain, cramps, and heel pain from plantar fasciitis. Stretch standing up. A weight-bearing, runners-type stretch can be helpful for foot pain in the arch. Stand up and place your toes against a wall; lean forward a little until you feel your arch stretch. Repeat using the other foot. Stretch sitting down. Sit barefoot and cross your left leg so that your ankle rests on your right thigh. Then hold your toes and bend them back toward your shin, stretching the band of tissue connecting the bottom of the heel to the ball. A University of Rochester study found that people living with plantar fasciitis had a 75 percent chance of having no pain within three to six months of performing this stretch three times daily. Give yourself a foot massage. Nothing spells pain relief like a good foot rub. Use the following technique recommended by Rhonda Crockett, a licensed massage therapist at Ohio State University?s Center for Integrative Medicine in Columbus. Start with your toes, using your thumb to massage them in circular motions. Then move to the arch under your foot and gradually work your way down to the heel, applying pressure with your fingers and palm of your hand. Use lotion to allow your hand to move smoothly over your foot. Relax in a warm bath with Epsom salts. The combination of warm water and Epsom salts will give you a double dose of pain relief and relaxation. Magnesium sulfate, the key compound in Epsom salts, has been found to relax muscles, reduce pain, and sedate the nervous system. Plus, warm water helps improve circulation in the feet and relieve muscle pain. Crockett recommends adding two cups of Epsom salts to a warm bath and soaking for 20 minutes.     \t1'

b'RefBot est un bot programm\xc3\xa9 en langage Python et qui agit sur des pages Wikipast.  Sommaire  1 Description 2 Restrictions 3 Exemples 4 Code 5 Cr\xc3\xa9ateurs   Description C\'est un bot agr\xc3\xa9able!... ou pas. Ce vous qui d\xc3\xa9cide, mais nous pensons qu\xe2\x80\x99il est mignon\xc2\xa0:-) Le bot est consist\xc3\xa9 de trois parties principales.  La premi\xc3\xa8re partie est base sur le SourceBot, qui contr\xc3\xb4le tous les pages de Datafication Biographique et signale s\'il y a des erreurs ou manques de datafication. Maintenant notre bot utiles les donn\xc3\xa9es du SourceBot. \xc3\x80 partir de ces donn\xc3\xa9es il va cr\xc3\xa9er et mise \xc3\xa0 jour \xc3\xa0 la fin de chaque page de Biographie une section "R\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence", qui respecte la r\xc3\xa8gle de citation. La deuxi\xc3\xa8me partie est base sur le LinkBot, qui parcoure les articles de Wikipast et recherche pour chacun d\'entre eux un article correspondant sur Wikipedia en fran\xc3\xa7ais. Pour chaque correspondance trouv\xc3\xa9e, il ajoute \xc3\xa0 la fin de l\'article Wikipast une section "Wikipedia" contenant le lien vers la page Wikipedia. Maintenant RefBot va cr\xc3\xa9er une partie "Sites Externes", dans quelle en plus de Wikipedia, il y aura 5 liens vers site externes \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99aide de la recherche sur Google.  La troisi\xc3\xa8me partie. Bot va cr\xc3\xa9er une section "Cat\xc3\xa9gories" qui contient tous les hyper mots de page de Biographique, \xc3\xa0 l\xe2\x80\x99exception de la date et lieu en d\xc3\xa9but de chaque datafication. <br/> Renovation/New Idea Using the neural network made a Bot, which will create a summarising text (about 200 symbols) based on raw data of datafiction of course. We can notice that a lot of neural network working in English, so we use Translator of our classmates to use English version of datafiction.  Restrictions Il y a quelque restrictions applicable sur le bot:  - Le bot peut travailler seulement avec le source correct (respect le r\xc3\xa8gle de citation de cours). - Les sites externes, bot va ajouter plus de site s\xe2\x80\x99il d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 pr\xc3\xa9sente une section Wikiedia, pour afin d\xe2\x80\x99\xc3\xa9viter l\xe2\x80\x99ambigu\xc3\xaft\xc3\xa9.  - Le bot peut traiter seulement le hyper mot active (qui a une page cr\xc3\xa9e dans Wikipast).  Exemples Exemple \xe2\x84\x961     Exemple \xe2\x84\x962     Exemple \xe2\x84\x963     Code Code du RefBot   First round is to read all data from all pages of Bibliographie for made a text version of it, understandable by neural network.   Second step is let neural network working with the received data. And finally get the summarising of Bibliographie.    Third step is taking the final version of neural network\'s text and put it in the article of Bibliographie. b'<br/>  Sommaire  1 Description 2 Critique 3 Code 4 Groupe 5 Code   Description Depuis une databiographie (correction(s):  ) suivant le format utilis\xc3\xa9 sur le wiki (correction(s): kiki, tiki ) (ex (correction(s): exo, en, eu, eux, es, eh, et, x, e, rex, tex ): 1890.03.19 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve), le BioPathBot est capable d\'extraire les informations temporelles et spatiales. Ces deux donn\xc3\xa9es forment un tuple (correction(s): tuile, tulle ) et sont pars\xc3\xa9es (correction(s): par\xc3\xa9es, pans\xc3\xa9es, parl\xc3\xa9es, pass\xc3\xa9es ) de fa\xc3\xa7on suivante\xc2\xa0:   La date est form\xc3\xa9e d\'une ann\xc3\xa9e, d\'un mois et d\'un jour. Si des informations venaient \xc3\xa0 manquer, la date est compl\xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9e par d\xc3\xa9faut avec le mois de janvier et le premier du mois.  Le lieu est transform\xc3\xa9 en coordonn\xc3\xa9es g\xc3\xa9ographiques (utilisant la librairie python [https (correction(s):  )://pypi.python.org (correction(s): orge, ore, ors, or, ort, ord, erg )/pypi/geopy (correction(s):  ) geopy (correction(s):  )]) Ainsi transform\xc3\xa9es et tri\xc3\xa9es chronologiquement, ces donn\xc3\xa9es  permettent de g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rer une carte utilisant [http (correction(s):  )://matplotlib (correction(s):  ).org (correction(s): orge, ore, ors, or, ort, ord, erg )/basemap (correction(s):  )/index.html basemap (correction(s):  )], o\xc3\xb9 sont dessin\xc3\xa9s des points pour marquer les lieux, ainsi que des traits mettant en avant la trajectoire de la personne. Cette carte est ensuite import\xc3\xa9e sur wikipast (correction(s):  ) puis ins\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9e sur une page annexe. Par exemple la carte de Jean Tinguely se visualise comme:   Critique Peu importe le type de page (une page concernant une personne, un hypermot...), une carte est g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9e. Donc si une page ne relate pas la vie d\'une personne, la carte aura peu de sens. Avec l\'algorithme actuel, les dates et les lieux sont parfaitement extraits et plac\xc3\xa9 sur la carte. Cependant, si les donn\xc3\xa9es ne sont pas suffisamment pr\xc3\xa9cises, elles seront approxim\xc3\xa9es (correction(s):  ) (1980 devient 1980.01.01 tandis (correction(s): candis, tendis, taudis ) que le point g\xc3\xa9ographique correspondant \xc3\xa0 la Suisse sera son centre g\xc3\xa9ographique). Cela peut mener \xc3\xa0 des erreurs de trajectoire lors du tri chronologique ou simplement \xc3\xa0 une position diff\xc3\xa9rente de la r\xc3\xa9alit\xc3\xa9 sur la carte.  S\'il existe des \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements post-mortem (correction(s): mortel, mortes, morte ) mais que la mort de la personne n\'est pas mentionn\xc3\xa9e ou ne suit pas la convention de l\'hypermot D\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa8s, ces donn\xc3\xa9es seront aussi extraites et plac\xc3\xa9es sur la carte, alors m\xc3\xaame que la personne ne se d\xc3\xa9place pas.  Si des \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements sont spatialement trop proches, ils vont se superposer sur la carte et il deviendra difficile de retracer les \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements d\'une fa\xc3\xa7on visuellement claire. Par exemple, pour un trait entre Berne et Lausanne, il sera difficile de juger si une personne a fait plusieurs fois ce m\xc3\xaame d\xc3\xa9placement ou ne l\'a fait qu\'une seule fois au cours de sa vie. Parfois l\'outil qui transforme les lieux en coordonn\xc3\xa9es g\xc3\xa9ographiques cr\xc3\xa9e des erreurs. Par exemple "Rome" devient "Lom\xc3\xa9" qui se situe au Togo. Certains \xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9nements se passe sans que la personne soit physiquement pr\xc3\xa9sente, mais on ne peut pas le d\xc3\xa9tecter automatiquement. Les lieux apparaissent donc sur la carte. upload config def uploadMap(filename):      # read local file     upload_file = open(filename,"rb")     upload_contents = upload_file.read()     upload_file.close()      # setting parameters for upload     # in case of error print the response     # print(r4.text)  # add link to biopath in original page if not already existing def addLinkToOriginalPage(name):      result=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+name+\'&export&exportnowrap\')     soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text, "lxml")     #soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text)     code=\'\'     for primitive in soup.findAll("text"):         code+=primitive.string      exist = re.findall("(\\[\\["+name+" BioPathBot\\]\\])",code)     if(len(exist)==0):         title = name         content = "\\n\\n"+"[["+name+" BioPathBot]]"         requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+title+\'&export&exportnowrap\')         payload={\'action\':\'edit\',\'assert\':\'user\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'appendtext\':content,\'summary\':summary,\'title\':title,\'token\':edit_token}         r4=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php\',data=payload,cookies=edit_cookie)   def addToPage(name, images, legend):     title = name + " BioPathBot"     content = "[["+name+"]]<br>"+\'<div style="display:inline-block;">\'+legend+\'</div>\'     for img in images:         content += "[[Fichier: "+ img +"|left]]"      pageToChange = requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+title+\'&export&exportnowrap\')     payload={\'action\':\'edit\',\'assert\':\'user\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'text\':content,\'summary\':summary,\'title\':title,\'token\':edit_token}     r4=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php\',data=payload,cookies=edit_cookie)     print(r4.text)  # BioPathBot : add line of databiographie to the right page (time and space) def getDataFromPage(name):     data = []     dates = []     places = []     print("Page Created: " + name)     result=requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+name+\'&export&exportnowrap\')     soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text, "lxml")     #soup=BeautifulSoup(result.text)     code=\'\'     for primitive in soup.findAll("text"):         if primitive.string:             code+=primitive.string      # split on list (*)     lines = code.split("*")     for line in lines :          # add breaking lines (otherwise will be appened directly in one line)         line = "\\n\\n"+line          # get date if exist         date = re.findall("((?<=\\[\\[)\\d*(\\.*\\d*\\.*\\d*)*(?=\\]\\]))",line)         dateToAdd = ""          if len(date) != 0 :             dateToAdd = date[0][0]          # get place if exist         place = re.findall("(?<=\\/\\s\\[\\[)[A-z\xc3\x80-\xc3\xbf\\s\\-]*(?=\\]\\])",line)         if(len(place)==0):             place = re.findall("(?<=\\/\\[\\[)[A-z\xc3\x80-\xc3\xbf\\s\\-]*(?=\\]\\])",line)         placeToAdd = ""         if len(place) != 0:             placeToAdd = place[0]             if placeToAdd == "Rome":                 placeToAdd = "Roma"          # if both the date and the location are available, append in data array         if dateToAdd and placeToAdd:             location = ""             for retries in range(5):                 try:                     location = geolocator.geocode(placeToAdd)                 except GeocoderTimedOut:                     continue                 break              # geopy usage policy max 1 request/sec             # https://operations.osmfoundation.org/policies/nominatim/             time.sleep(2)              if location:                 print("Location: " + placeToAdd + " : " + str(location.longitude) + "," + str(location.latitude))                 dataToAdd = [location.longitude,location.latitude];                 dates.append(dateToAdd)                 places.append(placeToAdd)                 data.append(dataToAdd)          # stop getting data if find [[D\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa8s]]         foundDeces = re.findall("(\\[\\[D\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa8s*\\]\\] (de |d)\\[\\["+name+")",line)         if(len(foundDeces) != 0):             break      return [data, dates, places]  # finds the minimal and maximal longitude and latitude def findCorners(pts):     minlon = maxlon = pts[0][0]     minlat = maxlat = pts[0][1]     for p in pts:         currlon = p[0]         if currlon<minlon:             minlon = currlon         elif currlon>maxlon:             maxlon = currlon          currlat = p[1]         if currlat<minlat:             minlat = currlat         elif currlat>maxlat:             maxlat = currlat      return [minlon, maxlon, minlat, maxlat]   # draws the map, some points and the lines def drawmap_colors(pts, dates, places, filename, export=False):     n_pts = len(pts)     corners = findCorners(pts)     txt = ""     m = Basemap(llcrnrlon=corners[0]-1, llcrnrlat=corners[2]-1, urcrnrlon=corners[1]+1, urcrnrlat=corners[3]+1, resolution=\'i\')     m.drawmapboundary(fill_color=\'0.6\')     m.drawcountries(linewidth=1.0, color=\'0.6\')     m.fillcontinents(color=\'white\', lake_color=\'white\')     for i in range(n_pts-1): # draw lines         for j in range(SEGMENTS):             start = pts[i] + (pts[i+1]-pts[i])*(j/SEGMENTS)             end = pts[i] + (pts[i+1]-pts[i])*((j+1)/SEGMENTS)             m.plot([start[0], end[0]], [start[1], end[1]], color=hsv_to_rgb((i+j/SEGMENTS)/n_pts, 1, 1))     for i in range(n_pts): # draw points         curr_color = hsv_to_rgb(i/n_pts, 1, 1)         m.plot(pts[i][0], pts[i][1], marker=\'o\', color=curr_color, fillstyle=\'full\', markeredgewidth=0.0)         txt += "<br><span style=\'color:" + rgb2hex(curr_color) + "; font-weight:bold\'>" + dates[i] + " / " + places[i] + ". </span>"     if export:         plt.savefig(filename, bbox_inches=\'tight\')         plt.close()     # plt.show()     return txt  # inp: point inside the box # hs: half dimensions of the box # outp: another point # finds the intersection of the segment inp-outp and the box def line_box(inp, hs, outp):     dir = outp - inp     if dir[0] == 0: dir[0] = np.nextafter(0, 1)     if dir[1] == 0: dir[1] = np.nextafter(0, 1)     ref = np.array([np.copysign(hs[0],dir[0]), np.copysign(hs[1],dir[1])])     dir_x = np.array([(ref[1]/dir[1])*dir[0], ref[1]])     dir_y = np.array([ref[0], (ref[0]/dir[0])*dir[1]])     fdir = dir_x if np.linalg.norm(dir_x) < np.linalg.norm(dir_y) else dir_y     return inp+fdir  # computes the repulsion force if 2 boxes are overlapping def repulsion_force(pos1, pos2, bbox1, bbox2):     hs1 = np.array([bbox1.width,bbox1.height])/2     hs2 = np.array([bbox2.width,bbox2.height])/2     c1 = pos1 + hs1     c2 = pos2 + hs2      # if both same position, choose a random direction     if all(c1==c2):         return (np.random.rand(2)-np.array([0.5,0.5]))*hs1[1]      b1 = line_box(c1, hs1*1.5, c2)     b2 = line_box(c2, hs2*1.5, c1)      # if pointing in the opposite direction     if np.dot(b1-c1,b2-b1) < 0:         return b2-b1     return np.zeros(2)  # readjust text labels so there is no overlap def adjust_text(texts, text_width, text_height,num_iterations=20,eta=0.5):     text_pos = [np.array(text.get_position()) for text in texts]     indices = list(range(len(texts)))     colliding = [True for text in texts]      # get text bounding boxes     f = plt.gcf()     r = f.canvas.get_renderer()     ax = plt.gca()     bboxes = [text.get_window_extent(renderer=r).transformed(ax.transData.inverted()) for text in texts]      # center text pos on markers     for i in range(len(texts)):         text_pos[i][0] -= bboxes[i].width/2         text_pos[i][1] -= bboxes[i].height/2      # readjust text labels     for _ in range(num_iterations):         random.shuffle(indices)         for (i,j) in itertools.combinations(indices, 2):             if i == j:                 continue             # pdb.set_trace()             f = repulsion_force(text_pos[i], text_pos[j], bboxes[i], bboxes[j])             text_pos[i] += f*eta      # delete text objects and create annotations on the readjusted positions     for i in range(len(texts)):         a = plt.annotate(texts[i].get_text(), xy=texts[i].get_position(), xytext=text_pos[i],             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="-", color=\'k\', lw=0.5, alpha=0.6),bbox=dict(facecolor=\'b\', alpha=0.2))          # plt.plot(text_pos[i][0], text_pos[i][1], marker=\'o\',color=\'r\', fillstyle=\'full\', markeredgewidth=0.0,alpha=0.7)         # plt.plot(text_pos[i][0]+bboxes[i].width, text_pos[i][1], marker=\'o\',color=\'r\', fillstyle=\'full\', markeredgewidth=0.0,alpha=0.7)         # plt.plot(text_pos[i][0]+bboxes[i].width, text_pos[i][1]+bboxes[i].height, marker=\'o\',color=\'r\', fillstyle=\'full\', markeredgewidth=0.0,alpha=0.7)         # plt.plot(text_pos[i][0], text_pos[i][1]+bboxes[i].height, marker=\'o\',color=\'r\', fillstyle=\'full\', markeredgewidth=0.0,alpha=0.7)          a.draggable();         texts[i].remove()  # draws the map, some points and the lines def drawmap_date(pts, dates, places, filename, export=False):     n_pts = len(pts)     corners = findCorners(pts)     txt = ""      # ratio correction to 2:1     lon_width = min((corners[1]-corners[0]+10)*1.1, 360)     lat_width = min((corners[3]-corners[2]+10)*1.1, 180)     lon_center = (corners[1]+corners[0])/2     lat_center = (corners[3]+corners[2])/2     if lon_width > lat_width*2:         lat_width = lon_width/2     else:         lon_width = lat_width*2      corners[0] = lon_center-lon_width/2     corners[1] = lon_center+lon_width/2     corners[2] = lat_center-lat_width/2     corners[3] = lat_center+lat_width/2      if corners[0] < -180:         corners[1] -= corners[0]-(-180)         corners[0] = -180     elif corners[1] > 180:         corners[0] -= corners[1]-180         corners[1] = 180     if corners[2] < -90:         corners[3] -= corners[2]-(-90)         corners[2] = -90     elif corners[3] > 90:         corners[2] -= corners[3]-90         corners[3] = 90      # draw map background     m = Basemap(llcrnrlon=corners[0], llcrnrlat=corners[2], urcrnrlon=corners[1], urcrnrlat=corners[3], resolution=\'i\')     m.drawmapboundary(fill_color=\'0.6\')     m.drawcountries(linewidth=1.0, color=\'0.6\')     m.fillcontinents(color=\'white\', lake_color=\'white\')     texts = []     \'\'\'     for i in range(n_pts-1): # draw lines         for j in range(SEGMENTS):             start = pts[i] + (pts[i+1]-pts[i])*(j/SEGMENTS)             end = pts[i] + (pts[i+1]-pts[i])*((j+1)/SEGMENTS)             m.plot([start[0], end[0]], [start[1], end[1]], color=hsv_to_rgb((i+j/SEGMENTS)/n_pts, 1, 1))     \'\'\'     for i in range(n_pts): # draw points         curr_color = hsv_to_rgb(i/n_pts, 1, 1)         x,y = m(pts[i][0], pts[i][1])         m.plot(x, y, marker=\'o\', color=curr_color, fillstyle=\'full\', markeredgewidth=0.0,alpha=0.7)         texts.append(plt.text(x, y, dates[i]))         txt += "<span style=\'color:" + rgb2hex(curr_color) + "; font-weight:bold\'>" + dates[i] + " / " + places[i] + ". </span> <br>"     adjust_text(texts, 1, 0.4)     if export:         plt.savefig(filename, bbox_inches=\'tight\')         plt.close()     return txt  for name in names:     image_filename_colors = (name + "_colors_biopath.png").replace(" ","_")     image_filename_date = (name + "_date_biopath.png").replace(" ","_")     data = getDataFromPage(name)     if len(data[0]) != 0:         legend_colors = drawmap_colors(np.array(data[0]), data[1], data[2], image_filename_colors, True)         drawmap_date(np.array(data[0]), data[1], data[2], image_filename_date, True)         uploadMap(image_filename_date)         uploadMap(image_filename_colors)         addToPage(name, [image_filename_colors, image_filename_date], legend_colors)         addLinkToOriginalPage(name)         print("end")   Groupe    Nom et Pr\xc3\xa9nom   Pseudo    Christophe Badoux   Christophe    Julien Burkhard   JulienB    Kim Lan Phan Hoang   Kl    Robin Lang   Roblan11   Code    \t0'

b'Tea is drunk everywhere in the world, and is the second most popular drink after water. So why is it so well-liked?<br/><br/>1. Teas are available in different flavours and varieties. In the identical means that not all red or white wines style the identical, not all teas taste the same. Green Tea is made from solely the leaves of the tea plant. Black Tea is more oxidised and stronger than Green Tea. White Tea is fast dried whereas Green Tea is roasted. Oolong Tea is a Chinese tea that\'s in between Green and Black Tea. Herbal teas or fruit teas are strictly not teas, but infusions. Which means there are a lot of types to select from and so one thing for everyone.<br/><br/>2. Tea is refreshing and invigorating, but isn\'t overpowering or bitter like some coffees can be. Tea is also much more healthy than fizzy drinks, and may be drunk all day with out the well-known side results of fizzy drinks.<br/><br/>3. Tea comprises far less caffeine than coffee. Which means tea drinkers can take pleasure in more cups of tea as it\'s less stimulating than coffee. It is due to this fact the perfect drink for the night as it is much less more likely to cause sleep problems not like coffee.<br/><br/>4. Tea is straightforward to make and specialist tools isn\'t vital. A cup, kettle, water and tea bag are the bare minimum requirements for a cup of tea. Nevertheless, a lot of people choose to use a teapot to make the tea in, and can take milk and / or sugar in their tea. Connoisseurs often favor to use free tea and a tea strainer somewhat than tea Disposable filter bags for loose tea. That is the equivalent of using contemporary ingredients rather than having a microwave ready meal.<br/><br/>5. Completely different teas require different brewing times and water temperatures. Getting the time or temperature incorrect will mean that the tea will not style as it was intended. This studying process ensures that each cup of tea is more than definitely worth the effect.<br/><br/>6. Though traditionally grown in China, India, Japan, Kenya, and Sri Lanka, less apparent countries reminiscent of Iran, Brazil and Turkey also produce tea. Every nation\'s tea will style totally different because of the climate and the best way it\'s prepared.<br/><br/>7. Tea is nicely often known as a relaxing drink, and when sweetened, may help to reduce the results of shock. That is another reason why persons are usually offered it if they\'ve been involved in an accident.<br/><br/>8. Regardless of being grown in warm international locations, tea can be used as a warming drink when it\'s cold. Alternatively, and quite surprisingly, a pleasant cup of tea may be very refreshing when it\'s warm<br/><br/>9. Over current years the well being benefits of tea, particularly Green Tea, have become more apparent. From use as a weight reduction help to serving to to lessen the consequences of Alzheimers and Parkinson\'s disease, Green Tea might be called a "super drink".<br/><br/>10. The process of making and ingesting tea is steeped in tradition, and generally is a social occasion in itself, and a "cup of tea" isn\'t just that. Japanese tea ceremonies are very formal, and the ceremony is sort of a religious occasion as a lot as a social gathering. Afternoon tea can vary from a mug of something lukewarm and moist with a slice of dried out cake in a caf\xc3\xa9 in a department store, to a a lot more lavish affair involving many types of sandwiches, desserts and biscuits, and tea served within the best bone china in a fancy restaurant.     \t1'
