b'Hainan has not proven an international draw so far, attracting fewer than a million foreign visitors in 2016<br/><br/>China is encouraging its southern island of Hainan to develop horse racing and introduce a raft of reforms as Beijing pushes the tropical tourism destination as a beacon of openness.<br/><br/>The province will be urged to explore opening new types of lotteries connected to sports and international competitions, according to the guiding opinion jointly issued by the Communist Party Central Committee and State Council which was published Saturday by state news agency Xinhua.<br/><br/>It marks a change of tack for the Communist government which has long banned most forms of gambling in mainland China and comes against the backdrop of its massive campaign against corruption.<br/><br/>But those concerns appear to be taking a back seat as Beijing looks to ramp up consumption to fuel China\'s economy and rebalance away from the investment and exports that have led the way for four decades.<br/><br/>The plan aims to make Hainan, an island off China\'s southern coast, a "trial free trade zone" to try out the reforms Beijing has pledged to bring to the mainland for years with few tangible successes.<br/><br/>The outline comes days after President Xi Jinping pledged a "new phase of openness" for China at Hainan\'s annual Boao Forum for Asia, a Davos-like meeting of international leaders.<br/><br/>We will "build Hainan into an important open door for China onto the Pacific and Indian oceans", the plan says.<br/><br/>Sectors to open  agen judi bola up to further foreign investment include healthcare, education, sports, communications, internet, culture and finance.<br/><br/>Beijing also wants to to position Hainan as a "centre of international tourism consumption", a goal which has faced halting progress despite sandy beaches and massive spending on plush resorts.<br/><br/>The province has not proven an international draw so far, attracting fewer than a million foreign visitors in 2016 -- compared with over seven million in Thailand\'s Phuket, according to data compiled by Bloomberg News.<br/><br/>As part of making the b'Winning cash at blackjack is not all about basic strategy and counting cards. Consistently profitable big cash relies upon lots on the betting system you use. Anyone who has played blackjack at a real casino knows that one second you could be on prime of the world in chips but the subsequent you may be digging in your pockets for more funds.<br/><br/>The chip stacks in a traditional game of blackjack typically fluctuate erratically and therefor finding the perfect betting system when playing is crucial. This text discusses three standard gambling  black jack 21 betting programs used all through historical past (and present) and which ones are the most effective to use when taking part in blackjack. The three betting methods are the Labouchere, Paroli and Parlay systems.<br/><br/>1.) Labouchere Betting System<br/><br/>Description: The Labouchere system is a negative development betting system. It is also referred to as "Cancellation", "Crossout", "Labby" and "Break up Martingale". Utilizing the Labouchere betting system, you\'ll always make a profit after finishing the entire betting cycle. To finish the system you will need to win all bets.<br/><br/>How It Works: You must first write down a collection of numbers, similar to "1 2 3 four 5 6 7 eight", nevertheless the series might be any numbers and any length. It could possibly be "1 1 1 4 3 7" or three 1 5 6 1 1 8 four 2 1". The length and values of the numbers depend on the game you are enjoying and the rules.<br/><br/>Each number within the collection represents a value in items or chips. You start by adding up the first and last number in the series. The sum is the unit of chips you\'ll bet. If you happen to win, you cross out the first and last number, and add the subsequent first and final number in the collection (the ones not crossed out) and use this sum for your second bet. Should you lose at any time before completing the system, you start from the beginning. If you win all bets and full the system, then you start once more from the start (the unique sum from the primary and last number).<br/><br/>You should rigorously develop this method earlier than taking part in and strictly adright here to following it once taking part in to win money. Be sure you account for your bankroll.<br/><br/>2.) Paroli Betting System<br/><br/>Description: The Paroli system is a constructive progression betting system. This technique doesn\'t require a large bankroll and is considered more stable than different betting techniques when taking part in blackjack.<br/><br/>How It Works: You start your guess with one unit. For those who win the primary guess, then your second wager is the first bet plus your winnings. Should you win the second guess, then your third wager is the second guess plus the winnings from that. At any time that you simply lose, you start the subsequent wager at one unit.<br/><br/>For example, if you happen to begin with $100.00 and win $100.00, then your second guess could be $200.00. In the event you win the second bet, then your third guess would be $400.00... etc. You include all winnings in your subsequent bet, including additional winnings from doubling down, splitting or blackjack.<br/><br/>An essential part of this system is having a cease level, which you have to determine before you begin gambling. The stopping point could also be a unit or dollar amount. After you lose a guess or reach your stopping level, you need to wager one unit on the subsequent bet.<br/><br/>3.) Parlay Betting System<br/><br/>Description: The Parlay system is another constructive development betting system and might efficiently be used in the game of blackjack. It\'s derived from the system that banks use to compound interest and can also be referred to as the "Let It Ride" betting system.<br/><br/>This betting system includes less threat than similar methods and does not require a large bankroll to use.<br/><br/>How It Works: This technique is similar to the Paroli betting system. The one distinction with this technique is that you simply literally "let it trip" together with your bets. With each successive bet, you place your winnings on high of the unique bet. There is no such thing as a stopping point. Since you might be betting in a pyramid fashion, you can turn a small wager into exponentially massive winnings. Unfortunately with this system, if you lose you lose everything.<br/><br/>The Labouchere, Paroli and Parlay techniques are the very best betting systems for playing blackjack. There are different betting programs out there however they\'re higher used with different gambling games equivalent to craps and roulette. Which system you choose will rely on your own personal type and bankroll. These betting techniques are great for all blackjack games together with these at real and online casinos.     \t1'

b'SummarizingBot est un bot programm\xc3\xa9 en langage Python et qui agit sur des pages Wikipast.  Sommaire  1 Description  1.1 Expresion R\xc3\xa9guli\xc3\xa8re 1.2 Datum V\xc3\xa9rification   2 Points Critique des Performances 3 Exemple 4 Code 5 Cr\xc3\xa9ateurs   Description Le SummarizingBot cr\xc3\xa9e un r\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9, lisible, pour diff\xc3\xa9rents personnages sur la base des donn\xc3\xa9es saisies dans la partie Biographie de la page Wiki de chaque personnage (tous les personnages trait\xc3\xa9s se trouvent dans la page Wiki Biographies). Le volume approximatif du r\xc3\xa9sume est de 200 mots. La taille du r\xc3\xa9sume d\xc3\xa9pend fortement des qualit\xc3\xa9s des donn\xc3\xa9es d\'origine, acquises de la page du personnage. C\'est-\xc3\xa0-dire, leur volume (au moins 15 entr\xc3\xa9es) et l\'exactitude de l\'entr\xc3\xa9e (syntaxes du Wiki doivent \xc3\xaatre respect\xc3\xa9s). Le principe cl\xc3\xa9 du bot est l\'analyse des donn\xc3\xa9es (entr\xc3\xa9es) en utilisant le concept de Expression R\xc3\xa9guli\xc3\xa8re (Regular Expression ou RegExp) pour identifier les diff\xc3\xa9rentes parties d\xe2\x80\x99entr\xc3\xa9e (une ligne de donn\xc3\xa9e). Gr\xc3\xa2ce \xc3\xa0 cette analyse, on va obtenir des blocs d\'information \xc3\xa0 partir de laquelle chaque entr\xc3\xa9e est consist\xc3\xa9. Ces blocs sont les suivants\xc2\xa0: Le bloc du Data, Le bloc de la Ville et, finalement, Le bloc d\xe2\x80\x99information sur l\'\xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa8nement. Ensuite, on tire les informations suppl\xc3\xa9mentaires de chaque bloc et on les traite avec de diff\xc3\xa9rentes fonctions. En ce moment-l\xc3\xa0, on va comprendre quel type de donn\xc3\xa9es on a dans le bloc. Si le bloc est de bonne structure on va continuer \xc3\xa0 le traiter, sinon on va \xc3\xa9liminer ce bloc. On peut facilement appliquer les fonctions pour chaque cas particulier des donn\xc3\xa9es dans le bloc pour cr\xc3\xa9er une structure correcte applicable au r\xc3\xa9sume.   La performance du code est telle qu\'environ 92,8% de donn\xc3\xa9es du totale sont trait\xc3\xa9es et utilis\xc3\xa9es pour cr\xc3\xa9er le r\xc3\xa9sume. Ce pourcentage a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 calcul\xc3\xa9 comme le rapport entre le nombre total de lignes correctement lues par le code et le nombre total de lignes lues par le code de tous les pages de la Biographie.  Expresion R\xc3\xa9guli\xc3\xa8re  ^\\s?(\\d{4}\\.?\\d{0,2}\\.?\\d{0,2})(\\s?\\/\\s?)?(([\\w\\s\\-,]+))?\\.?\\s?(.+)$  Notre mod\xc3\xa8le de RegExp d\xc3\xa9finit trois blocs principaux par motifs (patterns) suivantes\xc2\xa0:   Date    ^\\s?(\\d{4}\\.?\\d{0,2}\\.?\\d{0,2})   Lieu (Ville)   (([\\w\\s\\-,]+))?   Information (\xc3\x89v\xc3\xa9nement)  s?(.+)  Datum V\xc3\xa9rification On veut fournir quelques exemples du traitement des lignes de donn\xc3\xa9es.    [1993.05.23][][] ---> "False\'\', car on a une ligne vide par rapport \xc3\xa0 l\'information.   [1993.05.23][Milan][Information][Bloc d\'information non attendent] ---> "False\'\', car on a trop de blocs de data.   [1993-1994][Milan][Information] ---> "False\'\', car on a une date qui ne respecte pas le RegExp pour la date (format pas bon).    [1993.05.23][Milan11][Information] ou [1993.05.23][Quelque  part][Information] ---> "False\'\', car on a un lieu qui n\'a pas un bon format (chiffres) ou il y a nombreux espaces dans le s\xc3\xa9rie.   Points Critique des Performances Les points critiques sont les suivants\xc2\xa0:  Erreurs dans la saisie des donn\xc3\xa9es dans la biographie. Non-respect de la syntaxe pos\xc3\xa9e pour l\'entr\xc3\xa9e dans la Biographie. Probl\xc3\xa8me de la langue utilis\xc3\xa9e. La langue fran\xc3\xa7aise est rarement utilis\xc3\xa9e dans les r\xc3\xa9seaux de neurones artificiels (artificial neural network) qui peuvent cr\xc3\xa9er du texte \xc3\xa0 partir de donn\xc3\xa9es qu\'on a.  La grammaire fran\xc3\xa7aise est assez compliqu\xc3\xa9e. Ceci impose un grand nombre de fonctions pour avoir un texte lisible et grammaticalement correct. \xc3\x89tude d\xc3\xa9taill\xc3\xa9 du type de donn\xc3\xa9es d\'entr\xc3\xa9e pour am\xc3\xa9liorer les motifs. Pour obtenir un pourcentage plus faible de donn\xc3\xa9es perdues et augmenter la quantit\xc3\xa9 d\'informations obtenues \xc3\xa0 partir d\xe2\x80\x99une entr\xc3\xa9e. Code Code du SummarizingBot   from urllib.request import urlopen import requests from urllib.parse import quote from bs4 import BeautifulSoup from collections import OrderedDict from geotext import GeoText import re   # Login information user=\'testbot\' passw=\'dhbot2017\' baseurl = \'http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/\' summary = \'Wikipastbot update\'  # Login request payload={\'action\':\'query\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'meta\':\'tokens\',\'type\':\'login\'} r1=requests.post(baseurl + \'api.php\', data=payload)  # Login confirm login_token=r1.json()[\'query\'][\'tokens\'][\'logintoken\'] payload={\'action\':\'login\',\'format\':\'json\',\'utf8\':\'\',\'lgname\':user,\'lgpassword\':passw,\'lgtoken\':login_token} r2=requests.post(baseurl + \'api.php\', data=payload, cookies=r1.cookies)  # Get edit token2 params3=\'?format=json&action=query&meta=tokens&continue=\' r3=requests.get(baseurl + \'api.php\' + params3, cookies=r2.cookies) edit_token=r3.json()[\'query\'][\'tokens\'][\'csrftoken\']  edit_cookie=r2.cookies.copy() edit_cookie.update(r3.cookies)  # Regexp for definet the type of datum with which we work content_reexp = re.compile("^\\s?(\\d{4}\\.?\\d{0,2}\\.?\\d{0,2})(\\s?\\/\\s?)?(([\\w\\s\\-,]+))?\\.?\\s?(.+)$") # Pattern for data reference_reexp = re.compile("\\s*\\[\\d+\\]\\s*") # Pattern for reference date_reexp = re.compile("^\\d{4}\\.?\\d{0,2}\\.?\\d{0,2}") # Pattern to date  # Function to get list of personages  def get_all_personages():     response = urlopen("http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/index.php/Biographies")     page_source = response.read()     soup = BeautifulSoup(page_source,\'html.parser\')     result = []     for primitive in soup.findAll("body"):         for tableTag in primitive.findAll("table"):              for trTag in tableTag.findAll("tr"):                 for tdTag in trTag.findAll("td"):                     for aTag in tdTag.findAll("a"):                         if aTag.string\xc2\xa0!= None:                             result.append(aTag.string)      for idx, _ in enumerate(result): # idx & _ are name of our values in table of results (1:Andre Breton)         result[idx] = str(result[idx].replace(\' \', \'_\')) # Reformatting the data to get correct link to get access to Biographie     return result  # Function for verification of personage data def is_valid_personage_line(datum): # Introduce initial values     date = datum[0].strip()     city = None     info = None      # Define the type of datum by their length     if len(datum) == 3: # We have date, city and info          city = datum[1].strip()         info = datum[2].strip()     elif len(datum) == 2: # We have date and info         info = datum[1].strip()     else:         return False      # Validate city & Validate date     if not date_reexp.match(date): # Date don\'t pass the verification of pattern         return False     if city:         places = GeoText(city)          if len(places.cities) == 0:             if city.count(\' \') > 2 or \'1\' in city: # Check if in place of city we add date or not correct name of city                 return False          return True  # Function for generate summarizing of Biographie def generate_text_for_personage(name, data):     result = \'\'     last_city = None      for datum in data: # Checking all datum in list of data         date = datum[0]           # Remove last dot from date         if date[-1] == \'.\': date = date[:-1]          city = datum[1].strip() if len(datum) == 3 else None         info = datum[-1]          # Remove incorrect information          if len(info) < 5: continue                  # Remove last dot from datum-info (sentence)         if info[-1] == \'.\': info = info[:-1]                  # Add some prefix to date, to make text more readably         date_prefix = \'En \' if len(date) == 4 else \'Le \'         # Removing city in case if city repat for two consecutive datum or put prefix         need_city = city\xc2\xa0!= last_city and city\xc2\xa0!= \'-\'          city_postfix = ((\' a \' + city) if city and need_city else \'\') + \'. \'          result += date_prefix + date + \' \' + info + city_postfix # Final info, more readable sentence           last_city = city     return result  personages = get_all_personages() # To get all personages for address to functioon "get_all_personnages"  data = {} # List of key:value for all data find correct_data_ratio = {} # List of key:value which keep ratio of lossing info for each personnage   # Inital values  total_number_of_content_lines = 0 total_number_of_correct_lines = 0  # Collecting all data from pages of Biograhpie for personage in personages:     site = ("http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/index.php/" + quote(personage))     response = urlopen(site)      page_source = response.read()     soup = BeautifulSoup(page_source,\'html.parser\')      content_div = soup.find(id="mw-content-text") # Defined the principle block of Biographie for each personage     content_lines = content_div.findAll("li") # Defined line of datum      data[personage] = [] # Relate data to personage     total_number_of_content_lines += len(content_lines) # Counting the total number of lines which we find          for content_line in content_lines: # Treatment each line in data we extrect for each personnage         content_text = content_line.get_text() # From datum extract text         content_match = content_reexp.match(content_text) # Checking our extracting text with pattern of text          if content_match: # If checking succeed             findings = content_reexp.findall(content_text)             findings_as_array = [x for xs in findings for x in xs] # Made the array of content and personage             findings_no_duplicates = list(OrderedDict.fromkeys(findings_as_array))              findings_no_duplicates.pop(1) # Removing duplicated datum              # Check if last is a reference             if reference_reexp.match(findings_no_duplicates[-1]): findings_no_duplicates.pop(-1)                      if is_valid_personage_line(findings_no_duplicates): data[personage].append(findings_no_duplicates)              if len(content_lines)\xc2\xa0!= 0: correct_data_ratio[personage] = len(data[personage]) / len(content_lines) # The ratio of correct data for personnage     else: correct_data_ratio[personage] = 1 # It\'s mean that we read zero lines in Biographie of personnage      total_number_of_correct_lines += len(data[personage]) # Counting total number of lines which we can process to use in summarizing      print(generate_text_for_personage(personage, data[personage])) # Checking of text which be used for summarizing   correct_data_ratio_overall = total_number_of_correct_lines / total_number_of_content_lines # Checking percentage of data losing after all iteration print(correct_data_ratio_overall)  Cr\xc3\xa9ateurs Cr\xc3\xa9e par Daniil Morzhakov (dmorzhakov) & Andrey Piskunov (Andrey P). _/\xef\xb9\x8b\\_<br/> (\xd2\x82`_\xc2\xb4)<br/> <,\xef\xb8\xbb\xe2\x95\xa6\xe2\x95\xa4\xe2\x94\x80 \xd2\x89 - - - - - - \xe2\x80\x94<br/> _/\xef\xb9\x8b\\_<br/>     \t0'

b'<br/>  Sommaire  1 R\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9 des fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s 2 Description technique 3 Exemples 4 Evaluation des performances  4.1 Scheduling   5 Le tango 6 Code 7 Sources   R\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9 des fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s Ce bot permet de supprimer les entr\xc3\xa9es redondantes sur une page.  Description technique Pour pouvoir \xc3\xa9liminer les entr\xc3\xa9es redondantes, il faut les comparer chacune les unes aux autres et estimer leur similarit\xc3\xa9. Avant de comparer les phrases il faut les "nettoyer".   Supprimer tout caract\xc3\xa8re sp\xc3\xa9cial ou signe de ponctuation. Mettre tous les caract\xc3\xa8res en minuscule. S\xc3\xa9parer les mots et en filtrer certains.  Les mots commen\xc3\xa7ant par "http" sont des sources et il est pr\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rable de les ignorer car ce ne sont pas des mots et n\'aide pas \xc3\xa0 comparer le sens de la phrase. Les "stopwords", ("Mot vide") (\'au\', \'ce\', \'du\', \'\xc3\xa9tais\', \'le\' \'la\', \'il\', \'je\', \'nous\',...) sont des mots tellement communs qu\'il est inutile de les prendre en compte, car il apparaissent avec une fr\xc3\xa9quence semblables dans n\'importe quel texte. Ils n\'aident pas \xc3\xa0 distinguer un texte par rapport \xc3\xa0 un autre et n\'apporterait que de l\'information inutile en plus. Par cons\xc3\xa9quent ils sont ignor\xc3\xa9s. Et les modifier pour en avoir plus en commun.  "Stemming", ("Racinisation") est un proc\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9 de transformation des flexions en leur radical ou racine. Ce qui permet de lier par exemple les mots continuait, continuerai et continuant qui ont comme racine commune continu. L\'algorithme de Porter est utilis\xc3\xa9e dans ce cas plut\xc3\xb4t qu\'un dictionnaire. On applique ensuite le TF-IDF (Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency) qui est une m\xc3\xa9thode qui permet de d\'\xc3\xa9valuer l\'importance d\'un mot dans un texte. L\'id\xc3\xa9e du "term frequency" est juste le nombre d\'occurrences dans un fichier sur le nombre d\'occurrences totals dans tous les fichiers tf(i,i) = n(i,i)/sum(n(k,i)) <br/> La fr\xc3\xa9quence inverse  vise \xc3\xa0 donner plus de poids au terme moins fr\xc3\xa9quent qui peuvent aider \xc3\xa0 mieux diff\xc3\xa9rencier un texte d\'un autre. idf(i) = log{(abs(D)/abs(dj tq ti appartient \xc3\xa0 dj)} ou D est le nombre total de documents dans le corpus et le d\xc3\xa9nominateur le nombre de document ou le terme ti appara\xc3\xaet Le poids s\'obtient en multipliant les deux mesures: tfidf(i,j) = tf(i,j) * idf(i) Le poids augmente proportionnellement au nombre d\'occurrences du terme dans le texte. On peut donc utiliser cette pond\xc3\xa9ration pour d\xc3\xa9crire les diff\xc3\xa9rents textes dans un mod\xc3\xa8le vectoriel ou chaque document est repr\xc3\xa9sent\xc3\xa9 par un vecteur. Sous forme vectoriel il est tr\xc3\xa8s facile de calculer la similarit\xc3\xa9 entre deux vecteurs (deux textes) par la similarit\xc3\xa9 cosinus. Le produit scalaire de deux vecteurs A et B donne:  ||A|| * ||B|| * cos(theta)  on peut donc d\xc3\xa9terminer l\'angle theta et comme cos(theta) est compris entre -1 et 1 on peut \xc3\xa9valuer le degr\xc3\xa9 de similarit\xc3\xa9.  De 1 (identique) \xc3\xa0 -1 totalement oppos\xc3\xa9es. Dans ce cas les vecteurs tf-idf sont toujours positif donc le degr\xc3\xa9 de similarit\xc3\xa9 est entre 0 (nulle) et 1. Le degr\xc3\xa9 de similarit\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 partir du quelle on consid\xc3\xa8re que deux entr\xc3\xa9es sont les m\xc3\xaames peut \xc3\xaatre estim\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 partir de la moyenne des "cosine similarities" ainsi que de la "standard deviation" mais dans ce cas de figure nous avons trouv\xc3\xa9 que le TangoBot donnait de meilleurs r\xc3\xa9sultats en consid\xc3\xa9rant les valeurs > 0.5 (seuil fixe) comme suffisantes pour consid\xc3\xa9rer l\'\xc3\xa9galit\xc3\xa9. Une fois que le degr\xc3\xa9 de similarit\xc3\xa9 entre chaque document est \xc3\xa9tablis le choix de quelle version des entr\xc3\xa9es dupliqu\xc3\xa9es il faut garder se fait sur le nombre d\'hyperliens dans l\'entr\xc3\xa9es. Les entr\xc3\xa9es les plus compl\xc3\xa8tes seront toujours gard\xc3\xa9es.  Exemples Pour une page de test ou les exemples ci-dessous ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 travers\xc3\xa9s par le TangoBot voir: TANGOBOT TEST PAGE <br/> 1) Si le TangoBot compare deux phrases identiques\xc2\xa0:  "1828.05.08 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Naissance de Henri Dunant. [1] | [2]." est pr\xc3\xa9sente deux fois dans la m\xc3\xaame page. Alors le TangoBot remarquera directement que les m\xc3\xaames phrases poss\xc3\xa8dent les m\xc3\xaames mots aux m\xc3\xaames endroits. Il d\xc3\xa9cidera donc d\'en supprimer une des deux. 2) Si le TangoBot compare deux phrases contenant les m\xc3\xaames mots-cl\xc3\xa9s mais pas identiques\xc2\xa0:  "1828.05.08 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Naissance de Henri Dunant. [3] | [4]." "1828.05.08 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Un m\xc3\xa9decin donne Naissance \xc3\xa0 Henri Dunant. [5] | [6]." Dans ce cas particulier, le TangoBot remarque que les mots cl\xc3\xa9s des 2 phrases sont identiques. Alors le TangoBot ne garde que la premi\xc3\xa8re des deux phrases.   3) Si le TangoBot compare deux phrases similaires\xc2\xa0:  "1828.05.08 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Naissance de Henri Dunant. [7] | [8]." "1828.05.08 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Henri Dunant est n\xc3\xa9. [9] | [10]." Ici, le TangoBot voit qu\'il y a Henri Dunant dans les 2 phrases et que le nom est associ\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 "Naissance" et "n\xc3\xa9". Il \xc3\xa9tablit donc un lien entre les 2 phrases et remarque qu\'elles sont fortement similaires. Il d\xc3\xa9cide donc de garder la premi\xc3\xa8re. Evaluation des performances Le TangoBot traite les erreurs dans le format des entr\xc3\xa9es en les ignorant, les consid\xc3\xa9rant comme du simple texte et respecte donc leur ordre dans le document. Le TangoBot est tol\xc3\xa9rant. Le TangoBot devient utile quand beaucoup de diff\xc3\xa9rents bots applique leurs t\xc3\xa2ches en s\'ignorant les uns les autres et par cons\xc3\xa9quent cr\xc3\xa9e des entr\xc3\xa9es dupliqu\xc3\xa9es. Le TangoBot r\xc3\xa9unit il ne divise pas. Le bot utilise des algorithmes qui calcule des similarit\xc3\xa9s en se basant presque que sur les entr\xc3\xa9es de base, cela permet de gagner en performance m\xc3\xaame si on perd en pr\xc3\xa9cision compar\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 des mesures de similarit\xc3\xa9 linguistique qui vont utiliser de grand dictionnaires. Le seuil utilis\xc3\xa9 pour consid\xc3\xa9rer une entr\xc3\xa9e comme \xc3\xa9gale \xc3\xa0 une autre est fixe (0.5) dans ce cas. Id\xc3\xa9alement il faudrait d\xc3\xa9terminer statistiquement quelle valeur est la meilleure ou encore en \xc3\xa9tudiant la distribution des scores de similarit\xc3\xa9. Dans certains cas une entr\xc3\xa9e dupliqu\xc3\xa9e est intentionnel, une option est d\xc3\xa9sormais possible pour l\'indiquer: <dup>. Ces faux positifs peuvent donc \xc3\xaatre \xc3\xa9vit\xc3\xa9s en ajoutant cette balise \xc3\xa0 la fin. Le bot pourrait \xc3\xaatre utilis\xc3\xa9 pour signaler les documents redondants sur Wikipast au lieu de juste les entr\xc3\xa9es. Temps d\'execution pour toutes les pages environ 3 minutes. (Le temps de 3 minutes est pour la premi\xc3\xa8re execution une fois les dupliqu\xc3\xa9s d\xc3\xa9tect\xc3\xa9s l\'algorithme ne va pas repasser dessus et va donc \xc3\xa9valuer seulement les changements, par cons\xc3\xa9quent le temps d\'execution ne d\xc3\xa9passera pas les 30 secondes apr\xc3\xa8s la premi\xc3\xa8re execution \xc3\xa0 moins d\'une cr\xc3\xa9ation massive de nouvelles entr\xc3\xa9es par un autre bot) La majorit\xc3\xa9 des entr\xc3\xa9es dupliqu\xc3\xa9es d\xc3\xa9tect\xc3\xa9es sont g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9es par d\'autres bots. (95%) Peu de cas d\'entr\xc3\xa9es s\xc3\xa9mantiquement identique. (<5%) Quelques cas de faux positifs. (<5%)  Scheduling Etant donn\xc3\xa9 que la majorit\xc3\xa9 des entr\xc3\xa9es dupliqu\xc3\xa9es sont cr\xc3\xa9es par des bots, il est logique de faire tourner le TangoBot apr\xc3\xa8s leur passage. Une fois par jour convient tr\xc3\xa8s bien par rapport aux autres scheduling des bots. b"What's meals storage and why do you need it, you ask? Properly there are a number of connotations that the word can be utilized in. This article will study a couple of of them. At its most basic, meals storage is a shelf, cabinet, or pantry the place you retailer food. While this is actually one clarification of the idea, it is hardly the summation of the concept.<br/><br/>For some, food storage is a cultural imperative. The LDS church, also referred to as the Mormon church; is a religion that recommends that its adherents have a six month provide of meals on hand. For the Mormons, it's a technique to be prepared for the top of the world. Through the end of the world, they imagine that Jesus will come and acquire the devoted; but that previous to this event they'll need to be able to outlive the breakdown of the current world order. Thus they need a supply of meals and water that is on hand to be prepared.<br/><br/>The very fact is nevertheless, that you do not need to ascribe to a sure religion to recognize the worth of being prepared for an emergency. In case you live in an space that could be a goal for natural disasters equivalent to hurricanes, earthquakes, tsunamis, or even volcanoes; it just is sensible to be prepared for a worst case scenario.<br/><br/>Of course in the event you plan to maintain a major supply of meals readily available, this makes the meals storage a bit more of an organizational problem than merely stocking your pantry. The only answer is to have room in the house dedicated to storing food and water, reminiscent of an unfinished basement room. These rooms operate best when they're full with shelving programs that support food rotation. Meals rotation is the follow of utilizing the oldest Legacy Premium Food Storage first, somewhat than purchasing and using new food. In shops, this prevents them from having to throw out old food and minimize into their profits.<br/><br/>Within the case of residence food storage nevertheless, rotation ensures that you do not find yourself with a stock of meals that is gone bad. The form of food that stores nicely has a standard characteristic, it will not spoil easily. Nevertheless, that doesn't mean that it's going to never spoil. Canned meals does go bad after a fashion of years. MREs (meals ready to eat) even have an expiration date. So if a household plans to make the most of meals storage, it makes sense to use the old food instead of letting it go bad. That is where product rotation can really help.     \t1"

Fondation de la R\xc3\xa9publique populaire chinoise par Mao Zedong Wikipedia https (correction(s):  )://fr (correction(s): for, fi, fa, far, fer, fra, or, fy, f ).wikipedia (correction(s):  ).org (correction(s): orge, ore, ors, or, ort, ord, erg )/wiki/Loi_sur_la_citoyennet (correction(s): citoyenne, citoyennet\xc3\xa9, citoyennes )%C3%A9_de_la_R%C3%A9publique_populaire_de_Chine     \t0'
b'Sommaire  1 R\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9 des fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s 2 Description technique 3 Discussion  3.1 Performances 3.2 Fr\xc3\xa9quence d\'utilisation / Scheduling du bot 3.3 Limites du bot   4 Exemples  4.1 Exemple 1 4.2 Exemple 2 4.3 Exemple 3 4.4 Groupe 4.5 Code     R\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9 des fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s PageUpdaterBot est un robot qui s\'occupe de compl\xc3\xa9ter les diff\xc3\xa9rentes pages sur Wikipast \xc3\xa0 partir d\'hyperliens. PageUpdaterBot v\xc3\xa9rifie que sur chaque page, tous les hyperliens (except\xc3\xa9 les dates) m\xc3\xa8nent vers une page existante et que les entr\xc3\xa9es correspondantes existent et soient plac\xc3\xa9es aux bons endroits.  Si la page associ\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 l\'hyperlien n\'existe pas, PageUpdaterBot cr\xc3\xa9e la page et place l\'entr\xc3\xa9e associ\xc3\xa9e dans cette page.  Description technique La principale fonction de PageUpdaterBot est de r\xc3\xa9percuter les modifications faites sur une page particuli\xc3\xa8re sur toutes les autres pages concern\xc3\xa9e par l\'entr\xc3\xa9e. PageUpdaterBot commence par analyser le contenu de chaque page entr\xc3\xa9e par entr\xc3\xa9e. Pour chacune d\'entre elles, le bot extrait les hyperliens qu\'elle contient,\xc3\xa0 l\'exception de la date et de celui de la page en cours d\'analyse.  PageUpdaterBot va ex\xc3\xa9cuter une action dans trois diff\xc3\xa9rents cas: si la page r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9e dans l\'hyperlien n\'existe pas, si l\'entr\xc3\xa9e en question n\'est pas pr\xc3\xa9sente dans la page r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9e ou si une entr\xc3\xa9e a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 modifi\xc3\xa9e dans l\'une des deux pages. Dans le premier cas, PageUpdaterBot cr\xc3\xa9e la page et y ajoute l\'entr\xc3\xa9e. Dans le deuxi\xc3\xa8me cas, il ajoute l\'entr\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 la liste pr\xc3\xa9sente dans la page r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9e puis trie toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es par ordre chronologique. Dans le dernier cas, l\'entr\xc3\xa9e la plus r\xc3\xa9cente remplace l\'entr\xc3\xa9e la plus ancienne.  Afin de faciliter le traitement, un commentaire est associ\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 chaque entr\xc3\xa9e. Le commentaire poss\xc3\xa8de la forme suivante\xc2\xa0:   <!-- PUB METAINFOS : entryID = &beginID&42&endID& entryHash = &beginHASH&6936b65604c6f91fab6552c2b2bdad9a&endHASH& --> . Il est plac\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 la suite de l\'entr\xc3\xa9e dans le code source de la page. Pour chaque entr\xc3\xa9e, PageUpdaterBot v\xc3\xa9rifie tout d\'abord qu\'elle poss\xc3\xa8de un id et un hash. Si tel n\'est pas le cas, il lui ajoute un nouvel id et un nouvel hash, qui n\'est rien d\'autre que le md5 du texte de l\'entr\xc3\xa9e. Le dernier id utilis\xc3\xa9 sur wikipast est \xc3\xa9crit dans le commentaire au somment de la pr\xc3\xa9sente page. Si l\'entr\xc3\xa9e poss\xc3\xa8de un commentaire, dans le cas o\xc3\xb9 PageUpdaterBot est d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 pass\xc3\xa9 une fois, PageUpdaterBot va aller sur les pages r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9es par les hyperliens, appel\xc3\xa9es pages filles par la suite. Plusieurs cas de figure sont consid\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9s. Si l\'entr\xc3\xa9e est absente de la page fille (l\'id ne s\'y trouve pas), c\'est qu\'elle a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 supprim\xc3\xa9e manuellement. L\'entr\xc3\xa9e est supprim\xc3\xa9e de la page m\xc3\xa8re. Si l\'entr\xc3\xa9e est encore pr\xc3\xa9sente sur la page fille (une entr\xc3\xa9e avec le m\xc3\xaame id s\'y trouve ou une entr\xc3\xa9e sans commentaire mais contenant les m\xc3\xaames hyperliens et r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rences), le bot compare l\'entr\xc3\xa9e sur les deux pages avec leur hash respectif. Si le hash de l\'entr\xc3\xa9e ne correspond plus au hash \xc3\xa9crit dans le commentaire, c\'est que l\'entr\xc3\xa9e a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 modifi\xc3\xa9e depuis le dernier passage de PageUpdaterBot. L\'entr\xc3\xa9e avec le hash diff\xc3\xa9rent est gard\xc3\xa9e sur les deux pages. Le hash est mis \xc3\xa0 jour.  PageUpdaterBot poss\xc3\xa8de aussi un mode de nettoyage, qui supprime les PUB_id dans toutes les pages de Wikipast. Pour cela il faut l\'appeler avec le param\xc3\xa8tre clean.  Discussion Performances L\'algorithme poss\xc3\xa8de une complexit\xc3\xa9 en O(n^2) par page. En effet, PageUpdaterBot compare toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es de la page m\xc3\xa8re avec toutes celles de la page fille. Le bot a des performances raisonnables compte tenu du faible nombre de pages contenu sur  WikiPast. Sur le Wikipast du 16.05.17, le script a tri\xc3\xa9 toute la base de donn\xc3\xa9e en 2 minutes 10 secondes. Comme le script s\'arr\xc3\xaate quand il y a du texte entre deux entr\xc3\xa9es, PageUpdaterBot n\'a consid\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9 que un quart des entr\xc3\xa9es au premier passage du script. Sur le Wikipast du 16.05.17, le script a nettoy\xc3\xa9 toute la base de donn\xc3\xa9e en 1 minute 1 seconde. Sur le Wikipast du 16.05.17, le script a tri\xc3\xa9 toute la base de donn\xc3\xa9e en 5 minutes 14 secondes.  Fr\xc3\xa9quence d\'utilisation / Scheduling du bot Ce bot devrait \xc3\xaatre appliqu\xc3\xa9 une fois par jour au wiki.  Limites du bot Le traitement peut \xc3\xaatre source d\'erreur si un utilisateur maladroit modifie accidentellement le PUB_id \xc3\xa0 la fin de chaque entr\xc3\xa9e, ce qui rend ce bot vuln\xc3\xa9rable au mauvais comportement des utilisateurs. Il serait envisageable d\'ajouter une sorte de "checksum" pour contr\xc3\xb4ler si le commentaire a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 affect\xc3\xa9 par un utilisateur et dans ce cas recommencer la construction des IDs \xc3\xa0 partir de z\xc3\xa9ro. De plus, dans le cas o\xc3\xb9 une section contiendrait des entr\xc3\xa9es sous forme de liste, puis quelques paragraphes de textes, et enfin \xc3\xa0 nouveau une liste d\'entr\xc3\xa9e, seul la premi\xc3\xa8re liste d\'entr\xc3\xa9e sera prise en charge. Dans le cas ou deux entr\xc3\xa9es ayant le m\xc3\xaame PUB_id ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 modifi\xc3\xa9es de fa\xc3\xa7on diff\xc3\xa9rente, la modification ne sera pas r\xc3\xa9percut\xc3\xa9es sur toutes les pages au premier passage du bot. Il faudra un nouveau passage pour unifier toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es. Si une entr\xc3\xa9e est mal con\xc3\xa7ue et ne contient pas l\'hyperlien de sa propre page, le bot ajoutera l\'entr\xc3\xa9e sur les pages r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9es mais une modification sur un de ces derni\xc3\xa8res n\'entrainera pas la modification sur la page de base. (Voir exemple 3)  Exemples Exemple 1 Un utilisateur met \xc3\xa0 jour la page Henri Dunant et entre l\'information suivante\xc2\xa0:  1864.08.22 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Cr\xc3\xa9ation par Henri Dunant de la Croix rouge. [1] En admettant que l\'entr\xc3\xa9e n\'est pas encore pr\xc3\xa9sente dans Gen\xc3\xa8ve, Cr\xc3\xa9ation et que la page Croix rouge n\'existe pas, le bot commence par associer un PUB_id \xc3\xa0 la nouvelle entr\xc3\xa9e et copie la ligne dans la page Gen\xc3\xa8ve ainsi que Cr\xc3\xa9ation. Le bot trie chronologiquement les entr\xc3\xa9es dans chacune des 2 pages. L\'entr\xc3\xa9e se retrouve donc \xc3\xa0 la bonne place. Comme la page Croix rouge n\'existe pas, le bot cr\xc3\xa9e la page et recopie la ligne dans cette nouvelle page. Finalement, les entr\xc3\xa9es de la page Henri Dunant sont ordonn\xc3\xa9es chronologiquement. De plus, un hash est associ\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 chacune des entr\xc3\xa9es afin de d\xc3\xa9tecter une quelconque modification et ainsi mettre \xc3\xa0 jour les pages qui y sont r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9es.  Exemple 2 Un utilisateur met \xc3\xa0 jour la page Cr\xc3\xa9ation et supprime l\'information suivante\xc2\xa0:  1864.08.22 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Cr\xc3\xa9ation par Henri Dunant de la Croix rouge. [2] Le bot supprime l\'entr\xc3\xa9e dans les pages Croix rouge, Henri Dunant et Gen\xc3\xa8ve en d\xc3\xa9tectant qu\'un id est associ\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 une entr\xc3\xa9e dans ces 3 pages mais pas dans la page Cr\xc3\xa9ation.  Exemple 3 Un utilisateur met \xc3\xa0 jour la page Henri Dunant et \xc3\xa9crit une entr\xc3\xa9e probl\xc3\xa9matique\xc2\xa0:  1864.08.22 / Gen\xc3\xa8ve. Il cr\xc3\xa9e la Croix rouge. [3] Le bot modifie l\'entr\xc3\xa9e sur la page Croix rouge. Puis un autre utilisateur supprime l\'entr\xc3\xa9e sur la page Croix rouge. Le bot ne supprimera pas l\'entr\xc3\xa9e sur la page Henri Dunant car aucun hyperlien la r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9ren\xc3\xa7ant n\'est pr\xc3\xa9sent.  Groupe    Nom et Pr\xc3\xa9nom    Fournier Romain    Giorla Matteo    Pannatier Arnaud    Viaccoz C\xc3\xa9dric   Code Le code est disponible sur le repository GitHub PageUpdaterBot BioPathBot     \t0'

b"1971.05.12 / Cannes. Distinction du titre de commandeur de l'Ordre national de la L\xc3\xa9gion d'honneur \xc3\xa0 Charlie Chaplin, \xc3\xa0 l'occasion du Festival de Cannes. [1]    \t0"
b'G\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa8re un document RDF \xc3\xa0 partir du contenu d\'une page biographique de Wikipast.  Sommaire  1 Description 2 Fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s 3 Probl\xc3\xa8mes rencontr\xc3\xa9s et \xc3\xa9ventuelles am\xc3\xa9liorations 4 Code 5 Exemples de r\xc3\xa9sultats   Description Le Triplificator est un bot qui va se charger d\'exprimer l\'information contenue dans les datafications biographiques de Wikipast \xc3\xa0 l\'aide de la structure RDF (Resource Description Framework). Celle-ci permet d\'organiser l\'information non structur\xc3\xa9e des pages Wikipast en la rendant interpr\xc3\xa9table par la majorit\xc3\xa9 des applications. Cette conversion a donc pour but d\'augmenter la port\xc3\xa9e des datafications biographiques en permettant le traitement automatique de leur contenu par des applications externes. Une page Wikipast structur\xc3\xa9e en RDF est compos\xc3\xa9e de triplets RDF. En effet, l\'information contenu dans une entr\xc3\xa9e est r\xc3\xa9sum\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 l\'aide de l\'association de 3 mots, le Sujet, le Pr\xc3\xa9dicat et l\'Objet, qui \xc3\xa9tablit le lien existant entre les \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ments contenus dans l\'information non structur\xc3\xa9e. Enfin, le Triplificator va mettre le contenu RDF sur une nouvelle page texte \xc3\xa0 laquelle on peut acc\xc3\xa9der depuis un lien mis \xc3\xa0 la fin de la biographie sur la page Wikipast.  Fonctionnalit\xc3\xa9s  Lecture de la page Wiki  Le contenu de la page Wikipast est extrait (Web scraping) afin de r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9rer les hypermots tels que la date, le lieu et les diff\xc3\xa9rentes actions dans chaque entr\xc3\xa9e de la datafication, que le bot va ensuite classer afin d\'y acc\xc3\xa9der facilement et de les utiliser pour cr\xc3\xa9er les triplets RDF.   Interpr\xc3\xa9tation du contenu et mise en forme sous format RDF  Pour interpr\xc3\xa9ter l\'information re\xc3\xa7ue et la convertir en triplets RDF, nous avons cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9 une librairie d\'\xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa8nements tels que "Naissance" ou "Mort" qui sont r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9s par rapport au moteur de d\xc3\xa9finitions Vocab.org. A partir de cette librairie, le Triplificator va associer une action venant de la datafication biographique avec son \xc3\xa9quivalent dans la librairie r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9e et va ensuite nous donner un triplet sur l\'action en question, qui est donc le pr\xc3\xa9dicat du triplet, le sujet \xc3\xa9tant toujours le nom du personnage de la biographie et l\'objet pouvant varier selon la cible du pr\xc3\xa9dicat. Il est important de noter que l\'on suppose que la syntaxe des biographies ait \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 respect\xc3\xa9e afin d\'assurer le bon fonctionnement du Triplificator.  Mise en ligne de la nouvelle page  Probl\xc3\xa8mes rencontr\xc3\xa9s et \xc3\xa9ventuelles am\xc3\xa9liorations  Librairie de pr\xc3\xa9dicats  Un des probl\xc3\xa8mes majeurs li\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 la conversion en format RDF est la retransmission des pr\xc3\xa9dicats. En effet, la liste des mots que nous avons r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9s \xc3\xa9tant cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9e en interne, nous poss\xc3\xa9dons un nombre limit\xc3\xa9 de ces mots. Ceci donne lieu \xc3\xa0 un fichier RDF qui ne contient pas la totalit\xc3\xa9 des entr\xc3\xa9es de chaque datafication biographique car le bot n\'y reconna\xc3\xaet simplement pas tous les pr\xc3\xa9dicats. Il est \xc3\xa9galement important de noter que notre liste a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 partir d\'une seule source de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence (Vocab.org). Une am\xc3\xa9lioration possible de notre bot serait donc d\'utiliser soit plusieurs sources, soit une plus grande librairie de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rences, ou encore de faire en sorte que le bot puisse acc\xc3\xa9der directement \xc3\xa0 la(aux) source(s) et qu\'il construise en amont et par lui-m\xc3\xaame un dictionnaire de pr\xc3\xa9dicats r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9renc\xc3\xa9s.  Syntaxe Wikipast  Comme mentionn\xc3\xa9 dans une section pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9dente, nous avons suppos\xc3\xa9 la que la syntaxe Wiki ait \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 parfaitement respect\xc3\xa9e, \xc3\xa0 savoir "DATE / LIEU. ACTION PERSONNAGE OBJET", afin que le Triplificator puisse agir correctement sur la page d\'une biographie. Bien que nous ayons l\xc3\xa9g\xc3\xa8rement am\xc3\xa9lior\xc3\xa9 le bon fonctionnement du bot pour une mauvaise syntaxe, par exemple en pr\xc3\xa9cisant que le lieu n\'a pas \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 indiqu\xc3\xa9 dans une ligne mais que le bot continue de la lire correctement pour en extraire les bonnes informations, nous nous concentrons sur la conversion RDF en elle-m\xc3\xaame et nous comptons sur le travail d\'un autre bot qui pourrait \xc3\xa9ventuellement corriger la syntaxe d\'une page biographique, o\xc3\xb9 notre bot pourrait alors effectuer son travail de "triplification".  Format XML  Afin que le document RDF puisse \xc3\xaatre lisible facilement par n\'importe quelle plateforme, l\'id\xc3\xa9al aurait \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 de convertir en format XML (Extensible Markup Language) qui est le format de r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence, tout d\'abord pour transporter de l\'information en g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ral, mais plus pr\xc3\xa9cis\xc3\xa9ment celui utilis\xc3\xa9 pour \xc3\xa9crire un fichier RDF la majorit\xc3\xa9 du temps. La conversion en un tel format \xc3\xa9tant un travail \xc3\xa0 part enti\xc3\xa8re et diff\xc3\xa9rent de notre objectif principal, nous avons \xc3\xa9galement choisi de la laisser en \xc3\xa9ventuelle am\xc3\xa9lioration qui est r\xc3\xa9alisable dans le futur. Predicate library from reference Web page   LibORG = ["bio", "bio", "bio", "bio", "bio", "bio", "bio","bio","bio","bio","bio","bio", "frbr/core",                   "participation","bio","bio","relationship", "bio"]   Types = [["bio:principal"], ["bio:principal"], ["bio:principal"], ["bio:principal"], ["bio:principal"],                  ["bio:principal"], ["bio:principal"], [], ["bio:principal", "bio:organization"],                  ["bio:principal", "bio:organization"], ["bio:principal", "bio:organization"], [],                  ["bio:event", "bio:principal"], ["bio:principal", "bio:nationality"], ["bio:work", "bio:principal"],                  ["bio:principal", "frbr/core:work"], ["bio:principal", "bio:participant"], ["bio:organization"],                  ["bio:principal"], [], ["bio:principal"], ["bio:partner"], ["bio:principal", "bio:partner"]]   baseurl = \'http://wikipast.epfl.ch/wikipast/\'   names = [\'Ferdinand_Hodler\']   for name in names:      Output = ""     fichier = open(\'Result_\' + name + \'.txt\', "rb+")     result = requests.post(baseurl+\'api.php?action=query&titles=\'+name+\'&export&exportnowrap\')     soup = BeautifulSoup(result.text, "lxml")      code=\'\'      for primitive in soup.findAll("text"):         code+=primitive.string      entrees = code.split("*")     entrees_avec_resultat = 0      nombre_total_entrees = len(entrees)      for entree in entrees:          lieu = []         date = []          #Trouve la date         date_lieu_action = entree.split("/")         date = date_lieu_action[0]         date = date.replace("[[", "")         date = date.replace("]]", "")         date = \'\'.join(date.split())  # supprimer tout les whitspaces (tab, retours \xc3\xa0 la ligne, espace...)         if not date[0].isdigit(): #Si le premier \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9ment n\'est pas un nombre, ce n\'est probablement pas une date             continue          #Trouve le lieu         if len(date_lieu_action) > 1: #s\'il y a plus qu\'une date              lieu_action = date_lieu_action[1]              if lieu_action.count(".") > 1: # Si la syntaxe "." apr\xc3\xa8s le lieu et "." final est respect\xc3\xa9e                 lieu_action = lieu_action.split(".")                 lieu = lieu_action[0]                 lieu = lieu.replace("[[", "")                 lieu = lieu.replace("]]", "")                 lieu = \'\'.join(lieu.split()) #supprimer tout les whitspaces (tab, retours \xc3\xa0 la ligne, espace...)             else:                 if lieu_action.count("-") == 0:                     lieu = "-. b' Lucky Luke is a humorous comics series created by Belgian cartoonist Morris in 1946. Various writers scripted the series starting in 1955, beginning with French writer Ren\xc3\xa9 Goscinny. French artist Achd\xc3\xa9 has continued the series as artist since Morris\'s death in 2001. The series takes place in the American Old West and features the titular Lucky Luke, a cowboy known as the "man who shoots faster than his shadow", accompanied by his horse Jolly Jumper and in many stories a dog named Rantanplan. Lucky Luke is charged with restoring justice to the Old West by chasing down bandits, the most famous of whom are the Dalton Brothers. The stories are filled with humorous elements parodying the Western genre. Lucky Luke is one of the best-known and best-selling comics series in Europe and has been translated into numerous languages. 68 albums have appeared in the series as of 2014, at first published by Dupuis, then from 1968 by Dargaud, and from 1999 by Lucky Comics. Each story was first serialized in a magazine:   in Spirou from 1946 to 1967, in Pilote from 1967 to 1973, in Lucky Luke in 1974\xe2\x80\x9375, in the French edition of Tintin in 1975\xe2\x80\x9376, and in various other magazines since. The series has been adapted to various other media, such as animated films and television series, live-action films, video games, toys, and board games. About half of the series\' adventures have been translated into English. Lucky Luke comics have been translated into 23 languages, including many European languages, some African and Asian languages.  Wikipedia https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucky_Luke     \t0'

b"We all have heard about them but sadly not many of us know what exactly these bath bombs are. Even those that use them regularly are unaware of what they are composed of. In the current years, numerous such merchandise have gained enormous reputation especially among females. Most of the females, who love soaking their our bodies in the tubs, are the ones preferring using these types of merchandise to make the experience even more revitalizing.<br/><br/>So, if you are someone who needs to know what these balls are made up of then read on...<br/><br/>What are they made of?<br/><br/>Some tub bombs are soft while most of them are hard to touch. They're made up of materials which dissolve and make bubbles as soon as they are in a tub crammed with water. Basically, as quickly as they arrive in contact with water they start dissolving and crackling. Not only this, the scented ones release the perfume while they're dissolving. A few of them even have essential oils, cleaning ingredients and minerals in them which are fairly beneficial to the human skin.<br/><br/>Citric acid, baking soda (sodium bicarbonate), magnesium sulfate, and com starch are additionally current in them. If any of those ingredients is missing, the product will lose its effects till it's changed with an equal ingredient. Due to this fact, all of those ingredients when combined together are capable of producing the fizzing effects for which these products are popular. Nevertheless, at instances a bath bomb can also include synthetic colours, fried flowers and glitter to add more effects to the bathing experience.<br/><br/>Tub bombs which have minerals, cleansing brokers and essential oils are useful to the individual in a therapeutic way. The truth is, within the current previous  zambia01 many individuals have established the idea that such products are nice to loosen up their our bodies and minds. Other merchandise like fizzers and bath salts are also widespread for the same purpose. At the moment, there are a number of flavors available. As an illustration, the mint taste is known for energizing the body in summer time whereas the rose taste and other similar candy ones are meant for relaxation. The almond oil ones are good for moisturizing the skin whereas those with avocado oil have quite a lot of therapeutic properties related to them.<br/><br/>Although medical science does not approve the fact that such products have any therapeutic advantages, many nonetheless use them and consider in it. The scent, the bubbles and the fizzy impact are enough to relax the body. As soon as your body is relaxed, your thoughts will be relaxed too. Due to this fact, utilizing tub salts and tub bombs is an effective way revitalizing your body in these aggravating days     \t1"
b"When many people consider African safaris they may think about trekking by the wilds of the Kruger Nationwide Park in South Africa or navigating by means of the plains of the Maasai Mara in Kenya. How many people can honestly say that they'd first consider Namibia as a wildlife haven? Effectively in fact Namibia safaris are becoming more and more well-liked as at this time a burgeoning vacationer trade sees travellers from across the globe arriving to appreciate the wondrous magnificence and rugged drama of this mercurial and magical landscape.<br/><br/>Namibia is located in the South West of Africa hugging the border with Botswana and South Africa. For many people, Namibia is portrayed as a land of huge ranging desert and desolation; a barren land with little to supply the traveller. The truth may in reality not be farther from this false impression; Namibia is a vibrant and rich land and though deserts do dominate large swathes of the coast and north jap regions; these areas supply a unique perspective and an experience quite not like any other.<br/><br/>For safari lovers searching for the enduring sights that entice so many individuals to Africa, the Etosha Nationwide Park gives over a hundred types of enormous mammal together with those archetypal lions, elephants, zebras and giraffes as well as both white and the endangered black rhino species. A vast group of vibrant pink flamingos are additionally attracted to the central salt pan during the summer season months when the area temporarily floods.<br/><br/>To the South East of the country the landscape is dominated by the Namib-Naukluft Park, part of the Namib Desert which trails alongside a lot of the country's coastline. Close to to this region is the spectacular Fish River Canyon, the second largest natural gorge on the earth, runner up only to the Grand Canyon. Arizona's biggest landmark is after all a house hold name, yet how many people can say that they have heard of Fish River Canyon? This instance appears to epitomise Namibia's international identity, a land with so much to offer, so misunderstood or underestimated by the broader global community.<br/><br/>The Namib Desert itself is a shocking and ever remodeling environment. Within the decrease reaches of the area from Luderitz to the Kuiseb Desert a sea of sand dunes stretches out as far as the eye can see featuring among the tallest within the world. The ore rich ore earth creates a kaleidoscope of colors starting from striking pink to vivid orange. Even right here a variety of species survive including desert elephants, gemsboks, antelopes, gazelles and ostriches. Additional up the coast the famous space of Sossusvlei and Deadvlei are amongst probably the most photographed places within the Africa. A surreal panorama of parched white earth, vibrant orange dunes and scorched black trees create visual contrasts that might not be misplaced in a Salvador Dali dreamscape.<br/><br/>Namibia's capital is Windhoek is comparatively small but extraordinarily eclectic and progressive place. The hub of Namibia's economic system individuals from throughout Africa and Europe might be seen questioning the streets. Numerous high class bars, restaurants, cafes and boutiques are scattered across the world providing tourists a relaxed and really civilised retreat from the exhilaration's of exploring the rugged Namibian countryside.     \t1"
b'It\'s easy to upload and share images on Instagram and a few customers are just contented with doing just that. However there are more methods to boost your presence and entice more followers on the platform.<br/><br/>Engagement remains to be key in social networking and on unfollowers instagram, customers of all types including enterprise house owners who wish to enhance engagement on the site can achieve this through various strategies.<br/><br/>Tag Photos<br/><br/>Tagging a photo is a sure method to gain likes and comments on the picture sharing app, Instagram. This was confirmed by a study performed by Dan Zarrella entitled "The Science of Instagram."<br/><br/>It\'s potential to tag people on Instagram photos. Actually, a person can tag up to 30 individuals in a single photo.<br/><br/>And other than individuals, you too can tag your location.<br/><br/>When you tag people, you might be exposing your photograph to more people. The folks you tag can be notified increasing the probability of your picture getting a like or comment. The chums and followers of the people you tagged will also be able to view the picture while folks searching for particular places will even be able to see it.<br/><br/>Use the Words Like and Remark<br/><br/>One other strategy that may acquire your photos more likes and comments is by utilizing the words like or remark in your caption. Remember that as an Instagram person, you possibly can add a caption to your photo. This step is vital because it provides your followers an idea of what your photo is all about.<br/><br/>Add Filters<br/><br/>Filters make photographs on Instagram more captivating. There are different types available corresponding to those that brighten your images, add saturation and desaturation and one that allows you to create the traditional black and white photo.<br/><br/>The examine, nonetheless, noted that the most effective filter to use is the "regular filter" which lets you put up a photograph as it\'s with no particular effects.<br/><br/>Based on the research, the images with normal filter gained probably the most number of likes and comments. The opposite in style filters have been the willow, valencia and sierra.<br/><br/>Topic of Photo<br/><br/>The topic of your photograph is at all times a serious factor in attracting attention from Instagram users and getting likes and comments. Those who function faces were discovered to be more standard compared to people who show objects, places or scenery.<br/><br/>Photos that function a selfie or a bunch of people acquired more attention. They obtained a 35 improve in likes compared to footage with no faces.<br/><br/>Now that you recognize these steps, ensure that to practice them everytime you log in to your Instagram account.     \t1'

b"Here is a break down of the Atkins food regimen, by way of three good factors to the Atkins diet and three bad factors of the Atkins diet.<br/><br/>The Atkins food plan three good points.<br/><br/>1. The Atkins weight loss plan burns fat. When you begin the Atkins food plan your body is switching from burning carbs for energy to burning ketones which come from fat for energy. The Atkins weight-reduction plan is designed to do this so your body becomes a fats burning machine.<br/><br/>Conventional diets use the concept of eat fewer energy than you employ in a day which causes your body to burn fat reserves. The Atkins weight loss plan strategy burns fats faster because you absorb less carbs and your body is compelled into burning ketones.<br/><br/>2. You are not hungry on the Atkins diet. The Atkins weight loss program has you consuming your essential source of protein from meats at each meal. By using meat as your foremost source of protein your body feels full longer. Meat takes longer to digest which retains you feeling full longer.<br/><br/>3. The Atkins weight loss plan has well being benefits. In research the Atkins diet has been shown in some people to reduce cholesterol, triglycerides and blood pressure. Also the Atkins weight loss program may help to relieve the signs of acid reflux, diabetes and sleep apnea.<br/><br/>The Atkins weight loss program three bad points.<br/><br/>1. The Atkins food regimen burns fat fast. Toxins that have built up in your body and stored in fats cells could also be burned off too quick once you first begin the Atkins diet.<br/><br/>2. You may feel tired on the Atkins diet. When your body switches its fuel supply from carbs to ketones in the first few days of the Atkins weight-reduction plan chances are you'll feel some type of fatigue. The tired feeling ought to begin to settle out as your body begins to adjust to the Atkins diet.<br/><br/>3. You eat fewer vegetables on the Atkins diet. The Atkins eating regimen promotes more meat and fewer vegetables. Vegetables are an necessary source of minerals, fiber and calcium. When your body shifts to the Atkins diet you might suffer a loss in vegetable intake.<br/><br/>After you read the three good points of the Atkins weight loss plan and the three bad points of the Atkins eating regimen it's as much as you and your doctor to decide if the Atkins food regimen is your best nutrition advices (is.gd) option for you.     \t1"

b'Many people strategy a divorce with the mindset that there are just a few ways in which attorneys are noticeably completely different from one another, and that the only way that affects your case is whether or not or not you "win" or "lose".<br/><br/>In reality, there aren\'t typically winners and losers in divorce, and it\'s necessary to not view the proceedings in that light. Additionally, attorneys are completely different in lots of different ways as effectively, including very important ones. Listed below are a couple of of the important thing methods why discovering the best divorce lawyer is a crucial step.<br/><br/>Match Your Model and Choice<br/><br/>Some attorneys might have the fame of "courtroom bulldogs", going hard and aggressive. Other attorneys may concentrate on out-of-courtroom mediation, working to search out comparatively amicable and clean outcomes. Which sort of attorney you need depends not solely on who you are going up towards and the way a lot anger you have towards him or her, but also your preferred style and approach.<br/><br/>Do you need to settle things with as little conflict and added stress as attainable? Do you wish to skip proper previous mediation and head into a courtroom showdown, and if that\'s the case, why?<br/><br/>Evaluating for yourself the way you want the case to play out will give you a head begin in deciding on an legal professional who is properly-outfitted not just for any divorce, however for you, and your case.<br/><br/>Consolation Degree<br/><br/>Your divorce lawyer is going to be learning an awesome deal about you, your spouse and your family, and the entire circumstances involved. They will be aware of a range of knowledge and details, and also you want to feel absolutely comfortable with him or her.<br/><br/>You shouldn\'t only utterly trust your attorney with all of that info, and along with your case, but in addition feel open to sharing everything with them and all of the essential particulars or info -- if you believe them to be ugly or embarrassing. You\'ll be able to\'t withhold anything from your attorney if you would like a positive final result along with your case, and you absolutely must be consolationable with them.<br/><br/>Expertise and Track Report<br/><br/>There will not be winners and losers, however experience and track record do are likely to lead to superior, chooseable outcomes. It\'s important to consider that there is courtroom experience, mediation expertise, and more, which additionally performs into selecting the Lawyer Morristown New Jersey with the proper style for you, as talked about above.<br/><br/>Price<br/><br/>There\'s an enormous spectrum for how a lot different attorneys and corporations may charge, and for a way much a divorce could value you. You never wish to go bargain-basement shopping, nonetheless, that doesn\'t imply it\'s essential to spend excessively, either.<br/><br/>It is also important to consider a sometimes dirty trick of divorces - one side dragging out the proceedings to run up the payments for the opposite, and thereby placing pressure on them to settle and move on. So should you hire probably the most expertise legal professional on the town, because you think she or he must be the perfect, but you can only afford to pay their fees for one month before you don\'t have any more funds, then you\'re going to be out of luck. b'Overview<br/>The Achilles tendon is the largest and strongest tendon in the human body. It is the\xc2\xa0?cord? in the back of the leg that inserts into the back of the heel. The Achilles tendon got its name, according to Greek legend, when the Greek warrior, Achilles, was dipped into the River Styx by Thetis, his mother. This rendered him invincible with the exception of his unsubmerged heel. Unfortunately, he went on to get mortally wounded during the siege of Troy when he was struck in that heel by an arrow. Achilles tendinitis is inflammation and partial tearing of the Achilles tendon. It can occur with overuse of the tendon such as when starting or increasing the intensity of an exercise program or performing impact loading activities that include a lot of running and/or jumping.<br/><br/>Causes<br/>Tendons are the tough fibres that connect muscle to bone. Most tendon injuries occur near joints, such as the shoulder, elbow, knee, and ankle. A tendon injury may seem to happen suddenly, but usually it is the result of many tiny tears to the tendon that have happened over time. Health professionals may use different terms to describe a tendon injury. You may hear, Tendonitis (or Tendinitis): This actually means "inflammation of the tendon," but inflammation is rarely the cause of your tendon pain.<br/><br/>Symptoms<br/>Morning pain is a hallmark symptom because the achilles tendon must tolerate full range of movement including stretch immediately on rising in the morning. Symptoms are typically localized to the tendon and immediate surrounding area. Swelling and pain at the attachment are less common. The tendon can appear to have subtle changes in outline, becoming thicker in the A-P and M-L planes. With people who have a tendinopathy of the achilles tendon that has a sensitive zone, combined with intratendinous swelling, that moves along with the tendon and of which sensitivity increases or decreases when the tendon is put under pressure, there will be a high predictive value that in this situation there is a case of tendinosis.<br/><br/>Diagnosis<br/>A podiatrist can usually make the diagnosis by clinical history and physical examination alone. Pain with touching or stretching the tendon is typical. There may also be a visible swelling to the tendon. The patient frequently has difficulty plantarflexing (pushing down the ball of the foot and toes, like one would press on a gas pedal), particularly against resistance. In most cases X-rays don\'t show much, as they tend to show bone more than soft tissues. But X-rays may show associated degeneration of the heel bone that is common with Achilles Tendon problems. For example, heel spurs, calcification within the tendon, avulsion fractures, periostitis (a bruising of the outer covering of the bone) may all be seen on X-ray. In cases where we are uncertain as to the extent of the damage to the tendon, though, an MRI scan may be necessary, which images the soft tissues better than X-rays. When the tendon is simply inflamed and not severely damaged, the problem may or may not be visible on MRI. It depends upon the severity of the condition.<br/><br/>Nonsurgical Treatment<br/>Take a course (5 - 7 days) of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs(ibuprofen/voltaren/cataflam/mobic) available from your general practitioner or pharmacist. Apply ice to the Achilles - for 10 minutes every 2 hours, in order to reduce the inflammation. Avoid weight-bearing activities and keep foot elevated where possible. Self-massage - using arnica oil or anti-inflammatory gel. Rub in semi-circles in all directions away from the knotted tissue, three times a day once the nodule is gone, stretch the calf muscle gently do not start running until you can do heel raises and jumping exercises without pain return to running gradually full recovery is usually between six to eight weeks.<br/><br/><br/><br/>Surgical Treatment<br/>Surgery can be done to remove hardened fibrous tissue and repair any small tendon tears as a result of repetitive use injuries. This approach can also be used to help prevent an Achilles tendon rupture. If your Achilles tendon has already ruptured or torn, Achilles tendon surgery can be used to reattach the ends of the torn tendon. This approach is more thorough and definitive compared to non surgical treatment options discussed above. Surgical reattachment of the tendon also minimizes the change of re-rupturing the Achilles tendon.<br/><br/>Prevention<br/>Wear shoes that fit correctly and support your feet: Replace your running or exercise shoes before the padding or shock absorption wears out. Shock absorption greatly decreases as the treads on the bottoms or sides of your shoes begin to wear down. You may need running shoes that give your foot more heel or arch support. You may need shoe inserts to keep your foot from rolling inward. Stretch before you exercise: Always warm up your muscles and stretch gently before you exercise. Do cool down exercises when you are finished. This will loosen your muscles and decrease stress on your Achilles tendon. Exercise the right way: If your tendinitis is caused by the way that you exercise, ask a trainer, coach, or your caregiver for help. They can teach you ways to train or exercise to help prevent Achilles tendinitis. Do not run or exercise on uneven or hard surfaces. Instead, run on softer surfaces such as treadmills, rubber tracks, grass, or evenly packed dirt tracks.     \t1'

b'<br/>  Sommaire  1 Description 2 Exemples 3 Performances 4 Code   Description Le bot r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa8re toutes les donn\xc3\xa9es des Datafications Biographiques ainsi que toutes les pages cr\xc3\xa9er par des Bots et d\xc3\xa9tecte pour chaque page, l\'absence \xc3\xa9ventuelle d\'une source dans une ligne biographique et la signale. Il met \xc3\xa0 jour une page FactChecking qui liste les entr\xc3\xa9es non sourc\xc3\xa9es en associant une r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence particuli\xc3\xa8re \xc3\xa0 cet inconnue: cette r\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9rence est la date associ\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 l\'entr\xc3\xa9e non sourc\xc3\xa9e. Il scanne r\xc3\xa9guli\xc3\xa8rement (toutes les heures) toutes les datafications biographiques ainsi que les autres pages de wikipast et met \xc3\xa0 jour la page FactChecking. Pour chaque datification biographique ainsi que pour toutes pages cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es depuis le d\xc3\xa9but du cours, notre bot check si toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es de ces pages sont sourc\xc3\xa9es, si c\'est le cas alors on passe \xc3\xa0 la suivante datafication, sinon le nom de la datafication ainsi que les diff\xc3\xa9rentes dates des entr\xc3\xa9es non sourc\xc3\xa9es sont ajout\xc3\xa9es au contenu de la page FactChecking. Si une entr\xc3\xa9e non sourc\xc3\xa9e est mis \xc3\xa0 jour et devient sourc\xc3\xa9e, alors la date de cette entr\xc3\xa9e disparaitra de la page FactChecking. Les entr\xc3\xa9es non sourc\xc3\xa9es comprennent aussi les entr\xc3\xa9es qui ont une source qui n\'est pas letemps.ch.  Exemples Daniel Br\xc3\xa9laz\xc2\xa0:   1975 / Lausanne Dipl\xc3\xb4me en math\xc3\xa9matiques \xc3\xa0 l\'EPFL. [1]  1978 / Lausanne Election de Daniel Br\xc3\xa9laz \xc3\xa0 l\'Assembl\xc3\xa9e f\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9rale. Notre bot recup\xc3\xa8re la page de Daniel Br\xc3\xa9laz et elle retourne les dates de toute les entr\xc3\xa9es non-sourc\xc3\xa9es ou avec une autre source que letemps.ch . La premi\xc3\xa8re entr\xc3\xa9e poss\xc3\xa8de un lien vers wikipedia qui n\'est pas valide, et la deuxi\xc3\xa8me n\'a pas de source. Ce bot \xc3\xa9crit sur FactChecking\xc2\xa0: Daniel Br\xc3\xa9laz  The wrong entries in this page are the sources with the following dates: [ 1975 , 1978 ]  Paul Maillefer\xc2\xa0:  1911/Suisse Deuxi\xc3\xa8me Election de Paul Maillefer dans le Conseil National et succession en 1912 au Grand Conseil Nationnal. [[2]] Ici le lien est un lien wikipedia qui n\'est pas une source valide. Dans le cas de cette entr\xc3\xa9e il \xc3\xa9crit sur la page FactChecking\xc2\xa0: Paul Maillefer  The wrong entries in this page are the sources with the following dates: [ 1911 ]  Performances Notre bot rep\xc3\xa8re toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es des pages des Datafications Biographiques qui ne sont pas ou mal sourc\xc3\xa9e:  Ensuite celui-ci met \xc3\xa0 jour la page FactChecking en \xc3\xa9crivant les dates o\xc3\xb9 les sources sont manquantes.  Nous avons commenc\xc3\xa9 par afficher le num\xc3\xa9ro de la ligne o\xc3\xb9 il n\'y avait pas de source, puis nous nous sommes rendu comptes que quelques unes des entr\xc3\xa9es qui \xc3\xa9taient sourc\xc3\xa9es l\'\xc3\xa9taient mal, nous avons donc d\xc3\xa9cid\xc3\xa9 de rajouter \xc3\xa0 FactChecking toutes les entr\xc3\xa9es qui n\'avaient pas une source provenant du site letemps.ch.  Une fois que nous avions r\xc3\xa9cup\xc3\xa9rer tous les num\xc3\xa9ro des lignes mal sourc\xc3\xa9es/non sourc\xc3\xa9es, nous avons fait en sorte d\'afficher la date associ\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 l\'entr\xc3\xa9e non sourc\xc3\xa9e, car les indices ne permettaient pas de savoir directement quelles entr\xc3\xa9es \xc3\xa9taient mal sourc\xc3\xa9es .  Ensuite nous avons rep\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9 plusieurs types de formats de date existant.  Notre bot permet de rep\xc3\xa9rer les dates sous les formats suivant\xc2\xa0:    *1999.02.01/ , *1998.03.01: , *1998.03.02 / le format standard * 1998.05.08 /   Si la date ne correspond a aucun de ces mod\xc3\xa8les alors l\'affichage des sources mal sourc\xc3\xa9es sur  FactChecking sera moins performant: il n\'affichera pas la date, mais la ligne o\xc3\xb9 l\'entr\xc3\xa9e est mal soourc\xc3\xa9e. Pour r\xc3\xa9aliser tout cela nous avons utilis\xc3\xa9 des regular expressions afin de rep\xc3\xa9rer la date et le lien dans chaque entr\xc3\xa9e. Cependant, si le format d\'une entr\xc3\xa9e n\'est pas respect\xc3\xa9: si la date n\'est pas le premier Hypermot alors il y aura des baisses de perfomances puisque l\'affichage ne sera plus celui de la date:   ex: *Johny/Lausanne Election de Daniel Br\xc3\xa9laz \xc3\xa0 l\'Assembl\xc3\xa9e f\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9rale.   Ceci \xc3\xa9crira pour Daniel Br\xc3\xa9laz\xc2\xa0:  The wrong entries are the sources with the following dates: [ Johny ].   Cela peut-\xc3\xaatre assez probl\xc3\xa9matique mais si le format officiel a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 respect\xc3\xa9 alors cela ne posera pas probl\xc3\xa8me. Finalement nous avons aussi ajout\xc3\xa9 toutes les pages qui ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 cr\xc3\xa9\xc3\xa9es par des bots, afin que notre Bot ai acc\xc3\xa8s \xc3\xa0 toutes les pages de wikipast.
